Body:
Fellow Patriot,

As a loyal supporter of The Heritage Foundation, I wanted to take a moment to say thank you for your support. It means more to me and my team than you could ever know.

With that said, I have a special gift for you today.

If you’re like me, you know that the battle for the future of our country hangs in the balance and that none of us can afford to stand on the sidelines any longer.

That’s why I’ve asked my team to step up our efforts and get as many teaching resources into the hands of as many Americans—especially young Americans—as possible.

So today, I wanted to give you access to an online course that was first created exclusively for our President’s Club members, and that I now want to give to you.

It’s one of our first online courses called “The Case for Conservatism.” And I’m making it available to you for free when you activate your instant access today!

We asked world-class speaker, educator and researcher David Azerrad to walk you through his research and unique perspective on what he calls the “Two Regimes” in our society today—conservatism and progressivism—and their primary differences.

Click here now to get access and start learning now! <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKeblZ8uPYMqOq0E6Gpj-VyWzMLro5VpEYhdgYgh35GTUB-sSIORYjJiMIvyMY1GXLbZ2P2-Y=>

When you do, you’ll learn key takeaways like:



	- What does it mean to be a conservative?
	- What is “Modern Progressivism?”
	- How does a conservative worldview differ from a progressive one?
	- How do these two regimes understand the meaning of liberty, equality and the promise of America?
	- What ideas shape Americans’ minds and characters today, and who produces these ideas?
	- What’s at stake in the battle over what it means to be an American?
	- What American institutions are controlled by progressive ideas?
	- What are the key points in the “Right vs. Left” argument?
	- And much, much more…



This 5-part video series is a fascinating and enlightening watch. And you can start the first video today at no cost to you.

Once you’ve taken the course, I want you to share it with all of your friends and family—young and old alike—so they can begin to understand what is truly at stake, how we arrived where we are today, and how to win the battle of ideas in the minds of young people today.

Stand up and fight for your principles today. This online course will help you equip yourself for the battles ahead. All you need to do is register on our course platform to gain access now.

Don’t wait—start The Case for Conservatism right now. Please click this link to get the first course video sent to you right away. <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKeblZ8uPYMqOq0E6Gpj-VyWzMLro5VpEYhdgYgh35GTUB-sSIORYjJiMIvyMY1GXLbZ2P2-Y=>


All the best,

Kevin D. Roberts, Ph.D.
President, The Heritage Foundation

Subject: Who Are Winners and Losers in Biden’s Bailout of Silicon Valley Bank Depositors? Economist Explains
Body:
* ARTICLES *


** Who Are Winners and Losers in Biden’s Bailout of Silicon Valley Bank Depositors? Economist Explains
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/13/who-are-winners-and-losers-in-bidens-bailout-of-silicon-valley-bank-economist-explains/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

“What we’re seeing is that if you have rich depositors, if you have rich friends, if you’re a part of the in crowd, we will change all of the rules in order to bail you out,” says Peter St Onge.

=======================================


** DC Joins Parts of These 5 States in Allowing Noncitizens to Vote
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/13/dc-joins-parts-of-these-5-states-in-allowing-noncitizens-to-vote/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

“We have to stop this real foreign interference in our elections,” says J. Christian Adams, president of the Public Interest Legal Foundation.

=======================================


** Did Silicon Valley Bank Prioritize Social Justice Over Risk Management?
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/13/silicon-valley-bank-collapse-shows-banks-need-risk-management-not-environmental-and-social-justice-policies/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Bank documents indicate that corporate leadership may have been more interested in environmental sustainability, climate change, and diversity initiatives than risk management.

=======================================


** Angry Federal Judge Orders Biden's DHS: End Mass Parole of Illegal Aliens
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/13/federal-judge-castigates-dhs-orders-stop-mass-paroling-illegal-aliens/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Federal immigration law could not be clearer about the illegality of what the Department of Homeland Security is doing.

=======================================


** Time to Declare War on Mexican Drug Cartels
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/10/time-declare-war-mexican-drug-cartels/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Deaths by drug overdose in America last year reached an unconscionable 106,000, or more than 290 daily.

=======================================


** Naomi Wolf Apologizes for Believing Media’s Jan. 6 Narrative
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/13/farrago-of-lies-naomi-wolf-apologizes-for-believing-medias-jan-6-narrative/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

“I am sorry for believing the dominant legacy-media ‘narrative’ pretty completely from the time it was rolled out, without asking questions,” writes author Naomi Wolf.

Subject: Heritage Take: Federal Judge Castigates DHS, Orders Stop to Its Mass Paroling of Illegal Aliens
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

Federal Judge Castigates DHS, Orders Stop to Its Mass Paroling of Illegal 
Aliens <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KKSxzX0F_K-MCkpXk0HvulwDWdujG8DMddK0NCtsoG_75ck92kCj7IDa1ibBeBKFQeY=> - In a scathing opinion on Wednesday that questions the credibility of the Department of Homeland Security, U.S. District Court Judge T. Kent Wetherell II for the Northern District of Florida has ordered a stop to the Biden administration’s “Parole Plus Alternatives to Detention” (“Parole+ATD”) policy that has been illegally releasing hundreds of thousands of aliens into the U.S., concluding that it violates the Administrative Procedure Act, which governs rulemaking by federal agencies. Heritage Expert: Hans von Spakovsky <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KN81eMMWsS3qe6KuLCbkuFDmit3R_piHA_yL2C4nKlnFAmBBBnvlz29oYaKUEOFjVbI=>
I Was Assaulted by Antifa at a Detrans Rally <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KCVQC1OdrPiNOgI-Va7f0uQT5dkucc4eue3_cf_Ml5DDXezVjkIztX0hz96KYcfAVaI=> - Members and allies of the detransitioner community met in front of the California State 
Capitol here Friday ahead of Detrans Awareness Day <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KNFySAl4DdApUvwqyPI9S1q_R8zOI64oiBJpreELHG6bzzf9_P5Mipyn_QJ9xgVucGM=>. Attendees included notable detrans activists, such as Abel Garcia <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KBlEeDMW22ApLQBGGeLs1GdTOXnHBVCCIGl0IRL8oyjAF9PiwV-4hwhH7B-jCBIRUYs=>. I was in Sacramento covering the rally when I saw the crowd of Antifa members over in the distance. I approached the “black bloc” right before the event began and started filming. Within less than five minutes of arriving on the scene, a man, dressed head-to-toe in black clothing, wearing a baseball helmet, goggles and mask, lunged out from the crowd. He hit me <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KAblpZXrS854lzaPXMWvDPns-zkL_8u8n2owcz_BLGvMPeXvVJl79J8XFdOM9WR1u5g=> in the arm with what I assumed was a bat or some other blunt object. Most of the events were caught on tape <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KAblpZXrS854lzaPXMWvDPns-zkL_8u8n2owcz_BLGvMPeXvVJl79J8XFdOM9WR1u5g=>. Heritage Expert: Tim Kennedy <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KIg8znipun12CZT42dSiMwhWReoB7h8ixiI1e0ljf5floDqLmNZr8s5dSNUpuZBn_Rk=>
The Costs of Biden’s Border Crisis: The First Two Years <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KJ9_71GGO_9U9_VnXKm_nRWJX2l0yGW-L9NYU6bL4dmePPXYigvW6LAAPBEENxVTdP0=> - In President Biden’s first two 
years, the Administration requested and received significant funding to further its open borders agenda. The Biden Administration is using hundreds of billions of federal dollars to shift federal agencies and personnel further away from enforcing the nation’s immigration laws and toward processing and accommodating millions more illegal aliens. This policy agenda defies federal law and abuses American taxpayer dollars, and Congress should act to halt it. Heritage Experts: Erin Dwinell  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KPmuVuK3mDAEmMwKR2qJICZ3rQHoQJmLbFwtTpBp91vNy80jMsKupbjGzEJsJfxli_Q=>and Hannah Davis <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KCeqjYmSZGglljuvGzHgnFoDbOZ-OJzs0FY3VU2iE_sf-HjD_bboee9qf8tKgU9kd_I=>
The U.S. and Its Allies Must Understand and Respond to Russia’s Nuclear Threats <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KOBiBH4fitSbgNpjHk-oKcdwgPPRQcUSTW6F2GeMIqzF4MpzmIyIM9nwsP-q11QC8z8=> - Vladimir Putin’s dreams of Ukraine re-incorporated into Russia, of breaking up NATO, and of Russia leading a global anti-Western alliance are collapsing about him. Disaster for Russia’s imploding armed forces may well await, and, eventually, Ukraine’s armed forces will likely threaten to break Russia’s land corridor linking Crimea to the Donbas. At that point, Putin will make one of the most fateful decisions of the century: to use nuclear or chemical weapons or not. The U.S. must minimize that threat and ensure the protection of the American public and of U.S. allies. Heritage Expert: Ted Bromund <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KE_zIsWSpq4qhB0eZEfVHGkWE2Y6oYj7eSVfmjO8OnEvqmOuF5-CISKzdefxkr-8VNU=>
This crazy law opens voting booths to 
aliens <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KNPj6ntCRXS464qWwaCZtZyYiVUvgRn_iG8HKA2YmuSSfE1qGKdlu7RMW4uhgVhH4kw=> - The cherry blossoms aren’t the only things blooming early this year in Washington. Radical ideas have been blossoming in the D.C. City Council, too—ideas that will both disenfranchise and endanger the city’s citizens. The Council’s radical rewrite of D.C’s criminal code has received a lot of attention—and rightfully so. Crime is so bad <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KDSpe6By_MfCxQLDlHaY9ZuiP0ndWCUwIcXWKont8bqs-_s61zTh98i2sGki-zlIAd0=> in the District right now, robbers are demanding the coats off of their victims’ backs. Seemingly no one is safe. Rep. Angie Craig was literally assaulted in her apartment building on the way to vote on whether to override the Council’s irresponsible criminal code revisions that will give criminals a get-out-of-jail free card. (Needless to say, she voted to override it). Heritage Expert: Zack Smith <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KIe09J-d0fDzQ853OWb_N-8j8UXKKbhz0FEQCH7EY62veoGZQvPpCwupPq9RmcVubKU=> and Hans von Spakovsky <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKfs37KN81eMMWsS3qe6KuLCbkuFDmit3R_piHA_yL2C4nKlnFAmBBBnvlz29oYaKUEOFjVbI=>

Subject: Heritage Take: Inflation, Banking Crisis Being Fueled By Runaway Federal Budget
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

Inflation, Banking Crisis Being Fueled By Runaway Federal Budget  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZNsxQHGXFR2ckUYuWDk6wzAceUYKJTNdzU3Jj9RvAkSsb_IECYzHK1BnV695YAbpaEc=>– New data released Tuesday showed that inflation, as measured by the consumer price index (CPI), was 6.0 percent over the last twelve months and 0.4 percent for the month of February. Core CPI, which excludes food and energy, rose 0.5 percent in February and 5.5 percent over the last twelve months, nearly three times the Federal Reserve’s target rate of 2.0 percent. The prices of many consumer staples have increased significantly since January 2021, like roasted coffee up 24%, peanut butter and flour both 34%, eggs 187%, dairy products and cookies both 26%, ground beef 21%, frozen vegetables and butter both 29%, propane 35%, gasoline 51%, electricity 24%, home heating oil 72%, natural gas service 45%, and car insurance 20%. Heritage Expert: EJ Antoni <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZZ4xr6JPCdBQFZZfFLBCvTzj2Z46pUtCIZhxO9X_B9SYsOOI-iG1FcSxQUTBuezBWS0=>
 
Will Congress Finally Take Back Some Power and End Outdated Iraq War Authorizations? <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZVabgWRsncwRWwk7o-bP9phYO5YooV3qHHVUY7e-NXXvoiW3bg8qPrZrUWxDXhX0zks=> - A large bipartisan group of 22 Senators introduced <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZCevD3pjaA1BdGWAieIBuzAmylKjU2KjqJx732-GWt1v83FB4zizg8sFxuvCpJOxrNo=> legislation to repeal the 1991 and 2002 Iraq Authorizations for the Use of Military Force, or AUMF. Repealing the two AUMFs is sound policy <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZBc8As3VoSRBUJMBQV7GRBM59iv8ZzY45z5m-T2_7o4nWOygbOerxZ_SvvdR6UvhBrk=>. As we have written <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZXfHfRopwUUB5UGGEnbx-BlJsrDAPbmVGkchjd9GTSHJBh91AYnFHveyT-42XAwEeJs=> previously, these two war authorizations remain in force, even though their purposes were accomplished a long time ago. Sources inform me that the votes to repeal both AUMFs are secured so that the measure will pass the Senate. Similarly, in the House, Reps. Tom Cole, R-Okla., and Chip Roy, R-Texas, have joined forces with Abigail Spanberger, D-Va., and Barbara Lee, D-Calif., to repeal the two vestigial war authorizations as well. It’s remarkable that these four House members could agree on anything, yet commendable that they agree that reclaiming war powers for authorizations that have outlived their usefulness is important. Heritage Expert: Cully Stimson <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZelca-iLPS5ZvJyl_HJRccWwD8o8tI-i0vvDYDdkm1tm2a3p1Wit1L5v7Y8HvLl10-E=> 
 
6 Takeaways From China’s National People’s Congress  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZKLsy9knLfdcTyzC0zADO9n_doAjlylSmE25lz48bmAiindhmYyedI4MXuXfhRC8qmI=>- The People’s Republic of China wrapped up its annual National People’s Congress session on Monday as tensions remain high between Beijing and Washington. “China’s legislature meets for one or two weeks each spring to outline the nation’s policy direction and set economic targets for the year ahead,” Michael Cunningham, 
a research fellow in The Heritage Foundation’s Asian Studies Center, explained recently for The Daily Signal <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZJEUafjBgpQRUqJq9EqLV4VN2gejG4_6o4GqGZukN8WG7cBeNgfO6GcpnaxgguFkTQo=>. (The Daily Signal is the news outlet of The Heritage Foundation.) In October, the 20th Congress of the Chinese Communist Party held its weeklong, twice-a-decade meeting, at which Chinese President Xi Jinping secured his third five-year term as party general secretary, The Daily Signal previously reported <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZMWE6R9Rwli-hZcA2KxSKhpipWI9cseVz7xtEIavmjTD-rrivW2yvrveOxo7D4wQpJk=>. Heritage Expert: Sam Aschieris <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZJvWHBuSPKyRe-6JqFujnCrJ3D_Iu_CBwwcGF51QL45z1LbNjOEPjyF-bVUrniWm7bw=>
I Went to the Southern Border at 3 A.M. This Is What I Saw. <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZTxiK9dzS7OdQIfdqwNveTjTlmhNlLzg2JhFtEU3abeDGXVDeJFxLUT2I9IlBMuppso=> - It was 3 a.m. and a line of about 40 illegal aliens stretched along a section of the border wall waiting to be transported to the local processing center. Behind the group stood another 50 people who had crossed the border illegally into Yuma County, Arizona <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZc3kR1ZcXJsnIDheVTbupJ_2Tzqj5oAZco-LQXx9stT9f4X78KjRPo3BvBmWy4QqdCo=>.  A large white bus full of illegal aliens had just departed for the Border Patrol station <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZNanxBmTTz5dcOMgtOmn2mtEtbKnFqdBFuDnBaq9HypXlF5I9iXWKbLlH5ycqNNdYrA=> in Yuma, about 185 miles southwest of Phoenix, and would return in an hour to take the next 40.  “Your country of origin?” I asked, moving down the line.  Peru, Dominican Republic, Ecuador, Colombia, Georgia, China, India, and Cameroon – nine nations were represented in a group of 50 illegal aliens. Heritage Expert: Virginia Allen <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZMogRjH5-C8FTO-GT8HkKQNySodKsyOYUPlknMe3XrL2tHB4_M9cuebt5VkR4Qb70uI=> 


That Tantrum at Stanford Law School and What to Do About It <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZRvnbzhVyIvzoqi00-6SDZ-FUAJR1tW3DpnQdScPDSBHTAGmXSVqhxsDCUTQuyUTn1k=> - Another 
day, another tantrum at one of the nation’s top law schools. On Thursday, law students at Stanford (the No. 2 law school in the country) followed the example set by their peers at Yale <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZUBaYGDa_f8cbYNPEG2SyYpzVfAxvWzilJtzUhAnW-tHLbZ0xzV1TSVNxZFXz7fzfmU=> (No. 1) by shouting down <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZRi6QQoIzBdj8zUga7XMmWSwYEZGXjGHD_iXZbiqQSrEuOFhkZ4nb7AnEPqa9JDIX4A=> U.S. Circuit Court Judge Kyle Duncan, preventing him from delivering a lecture to other students who had invited him.  Student members of The Federalist Society invited Duncan, who sits on the 5th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals, to talk about how the decisions of his court have affected Supreme Court decisions. He didn’t get the chance. Heritage Expert: GianCarlo Canaparo <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKg_ROZNX3sp-OveLyFPEK2OmADWnh0FFBneItJzouoJZv0TtKbJVjZTMXRJrhdT1FfhlcCus=>

-

Subject: Let’s look for health answers together
Body:
Research holds the key to understanding many health conditions 

View on the Web 
<https://links.meredith.com/e/evib?_t=36ba8fa8372241d58b3bfc06997a4332&_m=57959171599e495bbfcb17a9dddda8ba&_e=4i1z4pDtRZMD3Cw-vFdxOrYxMSsY9MjBlQMeMO4XIJ4WoolFDYHTnoOlrDat0a2a>

 
<https://www.health.com/?hid=55265611e40a4ef903653c514ab3877881465d9e&utm_source=hth&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=hth-partner-offers_newsletter&utm_content=031523&did=8120993-20230315>
 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=healthier_future_3>

Dear Health member:
 We're always searching for special offers to benefit Health members. Here's 
an offer from one of our partners that we thought might interest you. 

 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=healthier_future_3>
Research holds the key to understanding many health conditions 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=healthier_future_3>

Health research is most effective when people from all walks of life 
participate. TheAll of Us 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=healthier_future_3>
 Research Program from the National Institutes of Health (NIH) is the biggest 
and most diverse research program of its kind, and it includes people like you. 
By taking part in the program, you’ll help power research that could find 
better ways to keep us all healthy. 
Make a difference 
All of Us is looking for one million or more volunteers from diverse 
backgrounds to help researchers understand health and disease. Sharing your 
information could help researchers one day create better treatments. 
Share as much or as little as you want 
If you choose to participate, you’ll decide when, what, and how much to share. 
That can be anything from basic background details to electronic health records 
and physical measurements. 

 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=healthier_future_3>

Benefits of participating 
The goal of the program is better health for everyone. By taking part, you can 
learn new things about your health. You can choose to receive genetic results, 
such as your genetic ancestry, traits, and health-related information. For 
example, you could learn helpful details you can share with your doctor, such 
as how your body might react to certain medicines and whether you’re at greater 
risk for certain diseases. 

 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=healthier_future_3>

Your privacy is protected 
The All of Us Research Program will store your information securely. 
Researchers won’t sell your data or share any information with anyone outside 
the program. 
Want to learn more? 
Learn more about the program and how you can make a difference in health 
research. Join researchers who are looking for answers to some of our toughest 
health questions. 

JOIN TODAY 
<https://participant.joinallofus.org/signup?lang=en&utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=healthier_future_3_join>

Subject: Heritage Take: FDA Lacks Authority to Approve Abortion Pills, Claims First-of-Its-Kind Lawsuit. The Left Is Apoplectic.
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

FDA Lacks Authority to Approve Abortion Pills, Claims First-of-Its-Kind Lawsuit. The Left Is Apoplectic. <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1Fe2yccYS30gMpuVGp6ohRpsJa941II8rdPD_0jBmBrTYaoFbYb3GVT2_XvpZD93Gwoo=> - In the lawsuit, the plaintiffs—a coalition of national medical associations and doctors experienced in caring for pregnant and post-abortive women—have requested that the court find the FDA’s approval of the pill and its years of subsequent loosening of restrictions on its 
use to be unlawful. They have requested that the court order the FDA to withdraw its approval of the drug. That outcome would have an unprecedented impact on the availability of the drugs that are part of the FDA’s two-drug regimen for chemical abortion <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1Fj8JlJnoJKsYnj7LGoAow-prQDrkqnGrxbSE0vNs0rnTvnoevmPqrfgXrFc9gFVfjjc=>: mifepristone and misoprostol. Those drugs are responsible for nearly 50% <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FvgLDZhO44pYJhsjS-fGy9y8euOzuvM8NyQgIh3VHUMK1h1b-7QxlTXMcWr0XraR6Q0=> of American abortions annually and represent the most common way to terminate unborn life in the U.S. Heritage Expert: Sarah Parshall Perry <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FSR_Q_s9VSSRQh41hpgDH7mdsjzzVqmTDPXdOeIr6PxxOWG5PqRVbzwvaha7U9Mthys=> and Roger Severino <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FQGCu1DJafrs7ZDCizUZRQ_lPoFS-LS3vk14x1H3AuAngTUhm4MxYHlY-BlA9kiXHEY=>
Biden’s $7 Trillion Budget Shell Game Takes More of Everyone’s Money, Despite His Promises <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FWoZXYvPNpsZ8WcW0JPV20RmlWeQOsD0uUFsq_VuaNEJ3cs5_CCoKe1pYnAeep39Ohc=> - Fundamentally, the nation does not have a revenue problem; it has a spending problem <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FbwjWEwSyF3ZIgFrTZUzLyMaELZtGhDsVn5cjFCECuU1iGXYwo2HeA7l_fmtfoaKX9U=>. Tax revenue has never been higher, whether measured in nominal terms or adjusted for inflation, or as a percent of gross domestic product, or as a percent of income. Rather, it is government spending that has ballooned to unsustainable levels and created record-breaking deficits. Consider that federal expenditures were about $4.8 trillion in 2019 but were over $6 trillion in 2022. That’s a 25% increase in three years—far outpacing economic growth—and it doesn’t even include the $6.7 trillion spent during the pandemic in 2020 or the record-breaking $7.2 trillion spent in 2021—Biden’s first year in office. Heritage Expert: EJ Antoni <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FYs4zMPrbEyjznI6kQ8Rz5Ag-ultchI2JuhA5hGqq70qbb1owQouunnE3aUG7AJYdX8=>
 
First-Year Med Students Told to Call Women ‘People With Cervices’; Professor Slams ‘Anti-Biological’ Lesson <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FccWcCKDzJjzlrioqx0J0isVZMoVSDiSfdhJQUSIM7MUdEWLAGVQ8N5L_X3rfoS0OGM=> - A professor at Indiana University School of Medicine <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FU-qkbXO5SntWPmLboLXlMAqbJAmglvCH_UtzmxteJfLVpVVLBpxeV-bU79N5NYA-y8=> condemned a lesson inculcating gender ideology among first-year medical students as “anti-scientific” and “anti-biological,” warning that it would have “very detrimental effects to the 
health care profession” and stating that he had not heard of any internal discussions about the lesson before professors implemented it. “I did not hear about it until it came out in the news,” the professor, who spoke with The Daily Signal on condition of anonymity, said in a phone interview Wednesday. He said the transgender lesson <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FcbYJNxLpVMb20r4874nxyJN0hg7xYlnw90xDyo9uHL3tByZZJsr2-uNDbQu5jqOlgY=> did not surprise him, however, because “the entire biomedical profession has been conquered by this aggressive ideology that inculcates a certain worldview.” Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FY74DYXViK-5DfVeyr3UWCmtNkTstcQDhIN2h0JNVVRnOIiyJwbCWOFviQ4v3WJdvHk=>
 
Massachusetts Mapping Project’s unseen dangers - <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FZ7UxkPXZUnexuCvyLberi1GnSZ21QYxqO-tjxyRgcGoXOyv3UwoyTPnDEHWk27HZo0=>Launched last June, the Massachusetts Mapping Project has called to “dismantle” dozens of Jewish American organizations, including synagogues, schools, and homes for people with 
disabilities. But a new investigative report suggests that the project is run not by local antisemites but by foreign state actors. Heritage Expert: Jim Carafano  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1Fil-4PqNIZGhAx5rNKReOdas1nh0ZaVwIUZ8YnurEBabnux956bwPlfBanDXGPxv0Bo=> 
 
6 Takeaways From China’s National People’s Congress  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FcivnyQBshEGRBqS4qXH8G_DPZlnitbFkVnWSRQ-3vvWyELX71hDB497AzJ6TeU8w0M=>- 
The People’s Republic of China wrapped up its annual National People’s Congress session on Monday as tensions remain high between Beijing and Washington. “China’s legislature meets for one or two weeks each spring to outline the nation’s policy direction and set economic targets for the year ahead,” Michael 
Cunningham, a research fellow in The Heritage Foundation’s Asian Studies Center, explained recently for The Daily Signal <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FXTJEYdzpxDJ8UhQMQo4JnqF9-vRVcUX49M7blWjyGaaBT5T32s0tVRBsu1Q54kkmdg=>. (The Daily Signal is the news outlet of The Heritage Foundation.) In October, the 20th Congress of the Chinese Communist Party held its weeklong, twice-a-decade meeting, at which Chinese President Xi Jinping secured his third five-year term as party general secretary, The Daily Signal previously reported <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1FekpnyyT_bQaSz_s2JlSQdOqbRxV0VEPF1J-ARinPgHPxvaduk7-pskWtTK4U6r6FrM=>. Heritage Expert: Sam Aschieri <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKiRp1Fu-ZQvX-UqjeIn2oQJeFFu5AlYN6n5kiHvvqjnIkB-aktLaZXbrb-BSm73Wb68PeN64=>

-

Subject: Heritage Take: Biden Bails Out The Rich And The Reckless
Received: by 2002:adf:dd51:0:0:0:0:0 with SMTP id u17csp405639wrm;        Fri, 17 Mar 2023 04:15:35 -0700 (PDT)
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.


Biden Bails Out The Rich And The Reckless <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb-6Rd_AJ7D2wFOZa-QBFDnK-5c3NlMMbg2-u4nKzz4g4fPiqmtFnJJcjujchFWNad5I=> - Just a 
few days ago, Silicon Valley Bank (SVB) became the second-largest bank failure in American history. This was followed shortly by Signature Bank — now the third largest bank failure — with possibly more to come. While these banks have been reckless, government intervention set the stage for this disaster and threatens to compound it with bailouts. Heritage Expert: EJ Antoni <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb5J2dZjFyxA8VL1TktDNgDMwtb1F-m_JVgGoHHS3UDm3WLm9869K845r7v0diRDNkcM=> and Peter St. Onge <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb2s6W-dbDB1-g_G_071bbO67pJxl7ISZ2XiCpg17evZNygt5ly5i35OAO-xM1UR7jlE=>
The Biden administration demands that TikTok be sold, or risk a nationwide ban <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb6oHH6O-5s7Rf051z6XnGw1tQlq_dQHNof3R-e6QpCcDUcPK9Hy6D-VDSt2ApmoxgqU=> -“ByteDance's purported backup plan of divesting from TikTok is nothing more than a distraction 
intended to derail the growing momentum towards a nationwide ban on the application. Since President Trump's attempt to ban TikTok in 2020, the company has persistently misled the American people and our lawmakers regarding its business practices, all to ensure their continued presence in the United States. This is more of the same from the China-based company. Our lawmakers should disregard the attempts of TikTok’s lobbyists to further delay what needs to be done. A nationwide ban on the application is the only viable option.” Heritage Expert: Jake Denton <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb5hRqSWiOgItRt3fxEkiLkMGOMG14BP678UbNit1wbUh7Snr3bxFZnOuIKJvB89Elt8=> 
How Congress can help open up America’s healthcare markets <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb4qkJI-MZ5dR3RkULl1de8LTRuq0t-Jn-3ZDWODjb2tMTP-M1efwt5PzCV5JtiNNy8c=> - Highly concentrated healthcare markets, regions where a relatively small number of big insurers and giant hospital 
systems dominate, are now the norm. This lack of competition leaves patients with fewer choices for medical services, higher costs, and lower quality. Heritage Expert: Bob Moffit <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb_Hi0t2YVOaXbe_nS_Q5YaXkScYVpf5KXOLv2mPfMWLtiVa9qaI8EWFK2y-MADB3zzg=>
 
Six strategies to curb violent crime <[[ttps://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2023/mar/15/six-strategies-curb-violent-crime/]]> - Far too many of the people tasked with formulating good public policy on violent crime fail to understand violent crime. As a result, they end up pushing for laws that are ill-designed to address actual problems and that, even worse, sometimes exacerbate them. Heritage Expert: Amy Swearer <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb7bci3v0RyJXFxUPpkBeJgwv5nNFWxrrqYPTOrLVvw-AQ9eJ-gzVMxf6d4mR3nlBep0=>
 
Trump-allied group trained congressional staff on how to go after Biden <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb2hSXvTpfFgRBpQ5Az2DuqLqR4pFX5nS6dzj7FIAuE42PSxpeCzYokZnEQBSthF5AzQ=> - The two-day event, which took place on Maryland’s Eastern shore, illustrates how Trump-allied activists are quietly shaping 
House Republicans’ investigations of the Biden administration right as Trump himself mounts another White House bid. Topics discussed at the bootcamp included tutorials on obtaining records and deposing and interviewing witnesses, according to a flier in the filings. Among those who briefed the congressional aides was a former Trump administration official, an energy lobbyist <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb8GXjmESu3cudMV3qNwy2uCxTMCKk4-2-exI09CRAN58rYL6UhogxZjmWyqoho_2FPg=> and a reporter from Epoch Times, a nonprofit media company <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb-bA9z-tv1dZhovjJ64Gs_PKfgYUGzlzlSzE8p1kwV7RQTZv-AFbS0DWVymv56nh2Wg=> tied to the Falun Gong Chinese spiritual community and known for its conspiratorial <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb8o3ksv6tUY8_OiUTMZO_rRzN54hv2GQKrS-qzanVvikj_p062UwGBDj6VLAb7Iuk-U=>, pro-Trump views. Heritage Expert: Paul Dans <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWbx-Vk00Pi7h1CQEw-blB-TKLsuXvfdSIHWph8yb7V9NBGVGC5l2qLFJTxFSPJoIRN7Q=> and Spencer Chretien <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKjkDWb66dVJmwoKiarIAkq3B-AP2n-IEzAv5Z3_LpiyuZNP0FQN5IZypNS9pbii0xoAqyacg=>

40 Years Later

Subject: New Year, New Hope
Body:
Let’s look for health answers together. 

View on the Web 
<https://links.meredith.com/e/evib?_t=36ba8fa8372241d58b3bfc06997a4332&_m=ace5318abff44fc499c81af9e8d720cf&_e=xwyKBdtpyYJfIdpF_YuxqMGGkC9MVOE_RYI8Fze9FPIc0Z3Dm8foRKR2DmW9Fvu2>

 
<https://www.health.com/?hid=55265611e40a4ef903653c514ab3877881465d9e&utm_source=hth&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=hth-partner-offers_newsletter&utm_content=011923&did=7983109-20230119>
 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=new_year_3>

Dear Health member:
 We're always searching for special offers to benefit Health members. Here's 
an offer from one of our partners that we thought might interest you. 

 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=science_diversity_3>
Happy New Year from All of Us 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=new_year_3>

It’s that time of year again: time to think about what we might want to do 
differently in the new year. Resolutions can be hard to keep if they are too 
vague:I will exercise more! I will stop smoking! 

 Maybe instead of resolutions, we can try New Year’s goals. Goals are specific 
things that you can achieve. In 2023, you could make a goal of taking part in 
theAll of Us 
<https://joinallofus.org/?utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=new_year_3>
 Research Program to receive your DNA results and help researchers learn more 
about how to keep us healthy. 
This is bigger than just science 
The All of Us Research Program from the National Institutes of Health isn’t 
just any research program.All of Us is combining science and diversity on a 
scale that no one has even attempted before. 
Equal representation in health research 
We’re including groups of people who have been left out of health research in 
the past, which means we’ll help researchers learn more than ever before about 
why ALL types of people stay healthy or get sick. More than 550,000 people are 
already participating inAll of Us. 

 Plus, by sharing a little saliva or a blood sample, you could get your DNA 
results at no cost.

 Here’s to a healthy and happy 2023 for all! 

Join Today 
<https://participant.joinallofus.org/signup?lang=en&utm_source=walgreens&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=tpc-y5&utm_content=new_year_3_join>

Subject: Help us bring fair and effective voting to the United States
From: Green Party of the United States <funcom@gp.org>
Body:
Dear Friend,

As a supporter of the Green Party of the United States, you know how important it is to have a political system that truly represents the will of the people. Unfortunately, our current voting systems are riddled with problems that make it an up-hill battle for Greens to win against the parties of War and Wallstreet. That's why we're asking for your support on this Ranked Choice Voting Day!

"Ranked choice voting is an idea whose time has come. Since 2020, the number of jurisdictions that have approved ranked choice voting has grown from two dozen to OVER 100! It is a reform we are winning. NOW is the time to build on this momentum."


-Howie Hawkins, 2020 Green Party Presidential Candidate

Ranked choice voting (RCV), puts to rest the duopoly's favorite attacks to use against the Green Party. With ranked choice voting there is no "spoiler effect" or "wasted vote" argument they can wield against us. Under RCV, everyone can vote their values. We've seen in races like Lisa Savage's 2020 Senate run in Maine and Cameron Gordon's several City Council elections in Minneapolis how this voting system can reduce negative campaigning, increase turnout, and help Green Party candidates win.

"Public polling shows 70% <https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2022/08/09/as-partisan-hostility-grows-signs-of-frustration-with-the-two-party-system/> of voters say they want more political parties to choose from on their ballots. Educating the electorate and popularizing ranked choice voting, along with other electoral reforms, in order to make RCV a reality, is an important first step in helping to repair, strengthen, and expand our democracy. We need YOUR SUPPORT <https://www.gp.org/donate_stripe> to do this."

-Matthew Hoh, 2022 North Carolina Green Party Congressional Candidate

RCV has been proven to work in cities and states across the country, and it's time for the rest of the United States to catch up. By supporting the Green Party, you're helping support our platform and values. With your support we can help end the stigma of voting your values and bring new voters into the ballot box.

Together we can show the parties of War and Wallstreet that they can't "steal" a vote that was never theirs to begin with.  Please consider making a donation today to help us advocate, agitate, and educate until we can give every voter a voice. <https://www.gp.org/donate_stripe> <https://www.gp.org/donate_stripe>

 <https://www.gp.org/donate_stripe>

Thank you for your support,

The Green Party of the United States
 <http://www.gp.org/> <http://www.gp.org/> <http://www.gp.org/>http://www.gp.org/

P.S.Our monthly sustaining donors are the unsung heroes of our party. Their generosity and commitment make our on-going work more and more possible. If you haven’t already,consider joining the ranks of our Monthly Sustainers today. <https://www.gp.org/donate_stripe_monthly> <http://www.gp.org/>



-=-=-
Green Party of the United States - PO Box 75075, Washington, DC 20013, United States 
This email was sent to evelperson6+partygreen@gmail.com.  To stop receiving emails: https://www.gp.org/unsubscribe
-=-=-

Welcome to Serious Eats! 

Welcome to the official Serious Eats newsletter! Our audience comes to us for rigorously tested recipes, science-driven cooking techniques, robust equipment reviews, and stories that offer cultural and historical context to the foods we love to eat. Our approach to our work in the kitchen is serious, but the results are for everyone, whether you’re a hardcore food nerd making a special-occasion feast or a casual, once-a-week cook who’s just looking for your next dinner.

Whatever your interests and cooking style, we’ve got a new recipe, technique, or thought-provoking perspective on food for you. We believe food can and should be a fun and engaging topic for everyone.

Subject: Welcome to Health!
Body:

Subject: Heritage Take: Joe Biden Should Be Embarrassed By That Chines Spy Balloon
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.


Joe Biden Should Be Embarrassed By That Chinese Spy Balloon <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTpKs2o5SLmP8uDAcc5kI11FZcxUq6GyOecksZViQ9uvWfJf4rvCec6fmJE5Mv4P0p40=> - The president looks as serious about the protecting the sanctity of American airspace as he is about securing the border. For the Administration, this is 
as much a political issue as it is a security issue. The initial response downplayed the incident. Apparently, Biden said just shoot the thing down—and the Pentagon said hold on, maybe not. By mid-morning, however, when the administration figured out that the incursion was unsettling to Americans, they decided this was a big deal after all. Things then shifted, with Secretary Blinken cancelling or postponing a planned trip to Beijing. China’s response to the incident is equally troubling. Beijing appears to assume that Americans are just stupid. They assert the balloon is a civilian weather-tracking aircraft—a claim that is clearly nonsense <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTyNYDIANLBSzWOWercCg1mjegoVhbVJlcl1co4rGNMAzOAKYwSmYamNRQgskA5_GTzU=>. The Chinese Communist Party (CCP) is playing our leaders for fools. Heritage Expert: Jim Carafano <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT6KyMn4k1hYU__F7_jqDexK1TC2uq-4KQw0HwJBwCR3qVb7xEmGApLqilRsvs3puVL4=>
 
What’s Behind the Recent Surge in School-Choice Victories <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTmI0-hI-7wJ3KASOyZci1Ra0nQmYuvdF2nl4TlmfyZyYcK8-RtvI2TwLiyu3QKrEQPw=> – After making 
incremental progress for three decades, the school-choice <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTrx_Q_AEZHpInoIQQachTVfSJQPwrbqdIF4Fvxm2FZkJl-WySO_uXKrey6ckoozI2tc=> movement is now rapidly achieving massive victories across the country. A key factor in this sudden success is the adoption of a new strategy <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT92MR_eyj7AimRTyiv13wJ28DjifnimsDwzejSyy4AmofInxw9UEnzlj5-GiX0hs1mQ=> to highlight the gap between the values that parents espouse and what’s going on in public schools. Programs spread around the country through the 2000s and 2010s but, with a few notable exceptions, mostly in dribs and drabs. It wasn’t until 2021 that West Virginia adopted the first universal, publicly funded education-choice policy, followed quickly by Arizona in 2022. Now, just a few weeks into this year’s legislative session, we’ve already seen Iowa and Utah pass universal education-choice programs. Passage of similar universal programs this year seems likely in Arkansas, Florida, Indiana, Ohio, Oklahoma, and Texas. Heritage Experts: Jason Bedrick <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTxNyBHdyoKFcUG-npgVeNvBPBBGXcNT5uF11Pk_Vt4IIXcj_cwOWVGofnO9xt6EKY8g=> and Jay Greene <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT2iYIhjqxvspzYDSaBekHiwo0azE4GQRFRHX7H6hzZRSn_gni3DXiFft8lt16CinT5g=>
 
Clean Energy’s Dirty Little China Secret - <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZThyo0mostUQNX9zEHZ9Yh34ElnryeDGMECaLjm97Vejt_rrJyDpsAIIxhhJJW3Bp2PA=> If companies like Microvast wish to receive U.S. government contracts and subsidies, they should divest Chinese entanglements and submit a clean bill of health to the Energy Department before they receive the funding. The Biden administration should not be in the business of trying to tempt the company away from China with handouts, no matter how desperately it desires cheap lithium batteries. If the Department of Energy cannot do this on its own initiative, as appears to be the case, Congress should require it to certify that no recipients of grants or subsidies have any ties to the PRC. Heritage Expert: Victoria Coates <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTsGTOiP4rtI8wwBD96WddTVxSKxoNmlBwqlFRBECUpVZJwd9G99DmP78-3iSZDpcY-U=>
 
An Effective Maritime Campaign Against China Requires a New Fleet-Centered Approach <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTlU5MgdLlIw-_rKr99CG46ZMMQZIJSuOADY0Pog4Yc74cNIeLqOFKltwky3RqTlAdJs=> - Today at sea, China is competing to overturn the norms governing commerce and naval operations to its benefit—a rules-based reordering—with far-reaching implications for the 
United States’ security and prosperity. To counter this, the Navy should better organize its forces and headquarters. Centering the global maritime competitive arm of the National Defense Strategy on the numbered fleets makes sense from an operational standpoint: Numbered fleets are organized for sustained maritime operations. However, achieving the full benefit of this strategy requires reorganizing the numbered fleets according to narrow strategic objectives bounded by common sense and maritime geography. Heritage Expert: Brent Sadler <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTnEV94UAYhPuNpmUekVQ4DNTnQ1zw3nUPu-iWFAh0QjW8RERwagw7GvsKRUh8ZtJm3Y=>
Is US monthly jobs report still reliable or the last domino to fall? - <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT7u-glRGeXkmQl90pML_s5anFEHUc9x9so8ygxxQHi2M2ivg2W1z8S8P_XqEeVUmfKw=> The normal lag in the labor market is likely being exaggerated with some 
businesses still trying to catch up to the changes from the last major economic disruption. The ultimate question now in determining the economy’s present state and divining its future is which information do you trust more during these periods of anomalous data: the monthly jobs report showing robust growth, or almost everything else showing a 
slight decline? Heritage Expert: E.J. Antoni <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTwIgvrSPoTjylxq-0MakcAhsBuuItrnQ97WqFBQSKvrSD6Z1gqgVtrCgMHUlfTSCLMM=>
'1619 Project' is back and as slanderous as ever! <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTlZ_3SUnjdTtcEh-07SEIi_6vrYdS2SUs-wQjTdWrUnb6fBYNulOeOVGPjdTSsTyBnA=> - Hardcore woke leftists think that if they can alter America's perception of the past, they can control the present, own the future… and make a whole lot of money in the process. Just pay close attention to Nikole Hannah-Jones. It is pretty hard not to, in fact. Her 1619 Project is now on Hulu, <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTn7H_zfRn0w0ulYlBn_JLew9L-rXOdfT3Px2Tun-6pkiKwrqbXVsqfIRMWyoF5NUCr4=>so you can't avoid seeing advertisements for it when you are looking for reruns of Frasier after a long day. Or, the ubiquitous Hannah-Jones may be coming to a library near you, one you pay for with your taxes. Heritage Expert: Mike Gonzalez <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT_JAzv7HZe-QqcYdtSDXCNdLRDwLJ6FAJJvNbOVqRuzCbOzrBpMM6ZmHbz5opOpu29I=>
Congress Must Get Clarity From Pfizer Execs on COVID-19 Viral ‘Mutation’ Experiments <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTx_f4NKD4vVWgpztkmyb90CDPrzwOVnd9LBQTkwPq0Q8u4lYwrHTiqUNUhurD5YnM4k=>—Dr. Jordon Trishton Walker, a director of research and development for the Pfizer Corp., recently became an overnight internet sensation. The reason: In a set of rambling remarks <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT4BUxbEQ1xgRf5IM8vX70UWFM0ryBFZHnN_uqbrc2KAk64ILbuyUKtX2uwMBAem07Gw=> to an undercover Project Veritas reporter, Walker outlined how the company 
could mutate viruses in a lab and do so to create new vaccines, while speculating on the potential of such a process to be a “cash cow” for the pharmaceutical giant, and presumably others in the industry. Then, realizing he had been recorded, Walker had a meltdown. It’s not hard to see why. Said <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT4BUxbEQ1xgRf5IM8vX70UWFM0ryBFZHnN_uqbrc2KAk64ILbuyUKtX2uwMBAem07Gw=> Walker: “One of the things we [Pfizer] are exploring is like, ‘Why 
don’t we just mutate it [COVID] ourselves so we could create—preemptively develop new vaccines, right? So, we have to do that. If we’re going to do that, though, there’s a risk of like, as you could imagine, no one wants to be having a pharma company mutating f—ing viruses.”  To lay persons, research to “mutate viruses” does sound inherently dangerous—suspiciously like viral “gain of function” research, the kind of research designed to genetically enhance the 
transmissibility and lethality of the virus and the kind of notorious lab work in Wuhan, China, that may have been the source of the global COVID-19 pandemic. Heritage Expert: Bob Moffit <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT5WnkWzv_ontJTYeTefV1tsZiiotadMPHZGy8Rhq0UEKPvgXZx-hcejOKk0yDe9yEHA=>
Little Evidence’ Biden Is Requiring Colleges to Report Foreign Cash, Betsy DeVos Says <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTvK6xliW4nKzsXvxDTb_ZYytlBhGQo9WPTatEVpcNabAZFNIMOGBBC-rEM9dvZrPbTM=>—Former Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTozKmKBcGmYHt1tMPGn8WGHeMAlvIusmkAO-TBF8_gK7oEdgL6_6NgblsSxLdkvzhLI=> says “there’s little evidence to suggest” the Biden administration and the Education Department are enforcing the law on foreign funding for colleges and universities. “The colleges complained vociferously when we asked them to simply do what they were supposed to do under the law and report their funding,” DeVos told The Daily Signal <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTmpN6inUlPqwUHIqp0XcIEpjxAiaXlQ_ubMEyU_hMc9aJXRy7te1QoMwcCkQjVNR2SQ=> in a phone interview. “But I think the Biden administration has, it appears, they just acquiesced to their requests to keep the money hidden.” Section 117 of the Higher Education Act of 1965 requires colleges and universities to report “contracts with and gifts from a foreign source that, alone or combined, are valued at $250,000 or more in a calendar year,” according to the Education Department website <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT5H5Q-T_Pzv0A8mV11zRqVOsMXD9QBLBRJ62pG2qMCmZzQ1dqn5sqchJ8AfiAp0r7Hs=>. Daily Signal Reporter: Samantha Aschieris <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTmpN6inUlPqwUHIqp0XcIEpjxAiaXlQ_ubMEyU_hMc9aJXRy7te1QoMwcCkQjVNR2SQ=>
Anglican Bishop Reports Elected Church Leader to Police for ‘Hate Crime’ of Speaking Against Queer Theory, Sexualization of Children <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT2O3ksj25iU5_AL4q2tM6Mv7YaJ7Gb24RSAMeWyLAc6fxcRI7KSZ1TiCp314qxToFKU=> - A Church of England bishop reported an elected church leader to the police <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTnnjalQROW6DxNfXAIl-PpDe_Hz1iMjpJ3O6rlo5i-H5z4S5xZJ22jgwdmCCJfEZPV8=> over his tweets condemning so-called queer theory and the sexualization of children. Last week, the head of the entire church also sent a letter seemingly threatening to remove the man from leadership over his remarks. “There’s a vocal minority that control the church and are using its resources to bully me into silence,” Sam Margrave, an elected member of the Church of England’s General Synod, told The Daily Signal <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZTqDMujeC5UzwEmKxFu0Gcz-ASNNztjFLfIgDc9rvOjJsHNpiKjNF3rdO2wPuY3x6I5I=> in an interview last week.” Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJysZZT1e_JK_BBWe_y6JVR4brUz5JipWvqrikOBb36qEpfs4ASvqwLTrk_DiXn23fGgHTLcg=>

-

Subject: Heritage Take: Joe Biden Should Be Embarrassed By That Chines Spy Balloon
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.



Joe Biden Should Be Embarrassed By That Chinese Spy Balloon <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqtuzwksfCrQcrY4mwfoh0wMKhRjKURxWW5XF9X89lDbmBdA8cLNEgFchOJEefmrJzN0=> - The president looks as serious about the protecting the sanctity of American airspace as he is about securing the border. For the Administration, this is 
as much a political issue as it is a security issue. The initial response downplayed the incident. Apparently, Biden said just shoot the thing down—and the Pentagon said hold on, maybe not. By mid-morning, however, when the administration figured out that the incursion was unsettling to Americans, they decided this was a big deal after all. Things then shifted, with Secretary Blinken cancelling or postponing a planned trip to Beijing. China’s response to the incident is equally troubling. Beijing appears to assume that Americans are just stupid. They assert the balloon is a civilian weather-tracking aircraft—a claim that is clearly nonsense <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqsUJBu9xjm_cke1Kvi-HQitHyd6YVR8-ExyYO99hz1qp6d307INg-eMeXOfQQIs2PDk=>. The Chinese Communist Party (CCP) is playing our leaders for fools. Heritage Expert: Jim Carafano <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqtduq6hfLcYhwBxLHvlKMi53JGqXuSLAlKC742TYbR-gsBbyHt8OglJ7C9PmYBe_fY0=>
FDA Lacks Authority to Approve Abortion Pills, Claims 
First-of-Its-Kind Lawsuit. The Left Is Apoplectic <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqgVmx_NPFK5FzbjtOQMdfu3oxacv9A8P1zTnUBXTKO2lr3TMeGGVUmzBCBbRvKnVVLU=> - In the lawsuit, the plaintiffs—a coalition of national medical associations and doctors experienced in caring for pregnant and post-abortive women—have requested that the court find the FDA’s approval of the pill and its years of subsequent loosening of restrictions on its use to be unlawful. They have requested that the court order the FDA to withdraw its approval of the drug. Heritage Expert: Sarah Parshall Perry <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhquC8KLUqV6UMyx1-PYshDNcL5wrTyyIc053L6yl5flRsufJbZjl8ajqQUV7tp3FLFHg=>
Female Swimmer Who 
Competed Against Male Will Attend State of the Union, Force Biden to Acknowledge He Has Said ‘I Don’t Matter’ <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqrXv2B4C90msDTescxnqE_YdHs_0sP5XXpBwzezlzn24vbTqXdoMjGY6YKVsNBMRxcw=> - Swimmer and women’s sports advocate Riley Gaines <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqsM3xgHWakDYgcKuZQjbeXLSHPFQwHrvh43a1xX5AAy5kPC-4qyHki-3M1gfhh90Ns4=> will be one of faces President Joe Biden will see in the crowd as he delivers his second State of the Union address Tuesday night.  “I think my presence here gives a face for Joe Biden to look at and tell me,… in my eyes with me being in the room, that I don’t matter,” Gaines told The Daily Signal, adding “because at this point, that’s essentially what he’s saying, is that biological women, our feelings, our existence, it doesn’t matter. We simply exist to validate the feelings and the identity of a man.” Heritage Expert: Virginia Allen <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqhEbRmJsoUPxLle8DDgZhojJ0XZ40-vuMtbR0b8ALtXTIt97j7GSrdD_7MB_m-_rnH4=>

The Case for Impeachment of Alejandro Nicholas Mayorkas Secretary of Homeland Security <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqpFFgVX_Yg873mNEhqN9kFMTVhzt4YhiC4kk59SMaZkN3nVXBKcMEObfda-deBA4kHI=> - Secretary of Homeland Security Alejandro Nicholas Mayorkas has 
been deaf to the voice of Americans, blind to the chaos and consequences of his policies and actions in violating the law, and untruthful in his statements to Congress and the American people. Secretary Mayorkas has intentionally undermined the sovereign interests of the United States by evading or violating the law and embracing policies he was warned would result in disaster. As Secretary of the Department of Homeland Security, he bears responsibility for this catastrophic failure. It is time for him to resign or be removed from office—for the protection and good of the men and women of the Department of Homeland Security and the American people and for the preservation of national sovereignty. Heritage Expert: Hans von Spakovsky <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqju5ovbCzP-ozsfheW65Txg3Ljum6Pbu2uQrqt6_qtHJLj5WgEpfjnG1zVgA6p7H7Nc=> 

Is Biden’s Pentagon a warfighting organization? Amid China threat, you have to wonder <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqqPN_N-0zqTNmANrjydX3dD1yD39aW147b3aNqht0RIAhjFLIrcjdmWxR8cTA-wg7cY=> - In a recent memo, Gen. Michael A. Minihan, commander of the U.S. Air Force’s Air Mobility Command, said he has a "gut feeling" that the U.S. will be at war with China in 2025. Written to the men and women under his command, it was clearly meant to spur them to "attain higher readiness, integration, and agility" deemed necessary to win in such a fight. Minihan’s blunt talk, aggressive instructions to his troops, and sense of urgency differs starkly from the Biden administration’s approach to the threat posed by China <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqteesVQMYc8k5pWt3je7GnNxevfl13j9_QTipDyEKu0IHGATojQtQUBtcpmKcLoNPgk=>. Heritage Expert: Dakota Wood <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJz-xhqmusiIqcKN2lFu5HXYO_YQWeDhf_AOSRYg10eSAymmZFwrhi1JIkRzJh16ShvAQPuLg=>

-

Subject: YOU'RE INVITED: Bishop Robert Barron Delivers the 2023 Russell Kirk Lecture (Mar. 14)
Body:
The 2023 Russell Kirk Lecture
Featuring Bishop Robert Barron
Tuesday, March 14, 2023
Reception: 5:00 - 6:00 p.m. ET
Program: 6:00 - 7:00 p.m. ET
The Heritage Foundation
214 Massachusetts Avenue, NE
Washington, DC 20002
REGISTER >> <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ0MikzRflYCerEEJ0vYzCnn9_U8W93WSBK1Fh93rxysvD0ujtCROH53YC7UihWLMbXtrBSWI=>
Featuring
The Most Reverend Bishop Robert Barron 
Bishop of the Diocese of Winona-Rochester (Minnesota) and Founder, 
Word on Fire Catholic Ministries
Hosted by
Kevin Roberts, Ph.D.
President, The Heritage Foundation
With Introductory Remarks by
Richard Reinsch
Director, B. Kenneth Simon Center for American Studies and 
AWC Family Foundation Fellow, The Heritage Foundation
The Heritage Foundation’s B. Kenneth Simon Center for American Studies is honored to announce that the Most Reverend Bishop Robert Barron of the diocese of Winona-Rochester will deliver the 2023 Russell Kirk Lecture for his speech titled, “The Breakdown of the Tocquevillean Equilibrium.” 

 The namesake of the lecture—famed scholar Russell Kirk—was a pillar of the conservative movement, 
bringing like-minded individuals under the very name conservative. Through his well-known books, The Conservative Mind and The Roots of American Order, Kirk provided a philosophical foundation for the conservative movement. 
 
Helping to establish the influential publications National Review and Modern Age, Kirk strove to consolidate a rich, academic bedrock for conservatives, developing the six canons of conservatism which defined the tenets of the movement. 

 Following the path of the America’s greatest conservative intellectual, the Russell Kirk Lecture series recognizes those individuals who exemplify Kirk’s commitment to conservative scholarship. 
 
Previous Russell Kirk Lectures have been delivered by Robert George, Roger Scruton, Shelby Steele, George Nash, Robert Reilly, David Goldman, Roger Kimball, and Gary Saul Morson. 

 Bishop Robert Barron: This year’s Russell Kirk Lecture speaker, Bishop Robert Barron, is known for his highly influential Word on Fire ministerial organization, which seeks to “proclaim Christ in the Culture” by “utilizing the tremendous resources…of art, architecture, poetry, philosophy, theology, and the lives of the saints 
in order to explain and interpret the event of Jesus Christ.” Bishop Barron is one of the most followed Catholics on social media and is frequently featured on FOX, NBC, and EWTN. He is an #1 Amazon bestselling author and has received acclaim for two documentary series, Catholicism and Pivotal Players. Despite his international prominence, he remains committed to the faithful of his Diocese of Winona-Rochester, MN.

Subject: 6 Takeaways From Hunter Biden House Hearing
Body:
* ARTICLES *


** 6 Takeaways From House Hearing on Twitter’s Suppression of Hunter Biden Laptop Story
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/08/6-takeaways-from-house-hearing-on-twitters-suppression-of-hunter-biden-laptop-story/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

“I think you guys wanted to take it down. I think you guys got played by the FBI. And that’s the scary part,” Rep. Jim Jordan tells a former Twitter executive.

=======================================


** 4 Reasons Why Republicans Call for Impeaching Homeland Security Secretary Alejandro Mayorkas
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/08/4-reasons-why-republicans-call-for-impeaching-homeland-security-secretary-alejandro-mayorkas/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

“It’s clear Secretary Mayorkas has committed high crimes and misdemeanors,” says Rep. Andy Biggs, R-Ariz.

=======================================


** Oversight Chairman Slams Biden Over Millions of Dollars From China: What Did China Get in Return?
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/07/rep-james-comer-slams-biden-family-over-millions-of-dollars-from-china/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

“We know the Biden family’s received millions and millions of dollars from Communist China. We don’t know exactly what Communist China got in return for that,” says Rep. James Comer.

=======================================


** Former Acting Defense Secretary Doesn't Think China Would Have Flown Balloon Under Trump
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/09/former-acting-defense-secretary-doesnt-think-china-would-have-flown-balloon-under-trump/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Chris Miller discusses some of President Biden's comments on China during his State of the Union address  and his thoughts on how the Biden administration responded to the Chinese spy balloon.

=======================================


** Claremont Institute Heads to Florida, Lauding DeSantis Leadership as ‘Template for Any Red State in America’
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/08/claremont-institute-florida-template-red-state-america-ron-desantis-republican/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

“Gov. DeSantis has shown fearless intellectual and political leadership in the fight against woke leftism,” says Ryan Williams, president of Claremont Institute.

=======================================


** Biden Administration's ‘Stupidity Never Ends,’ Rep. Kat Cammack Says
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/09/biden-administrations-stupidity-never-ends-rep-kat-cammack-says/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

The Biden administration recently announced it's considering declaring a "public health emergency" on abortion in the wake of Roe v. Wade being overturned.

Subject: Heritage Take:‘Economic Plan Is Breaking Records.’  (But Not in Good Way)
Received: by 2002:adf:b31c:0:0:0:0:0 with SMTP id j28csp6486wrd;        Thu, 9 Feb 2023 04:15:30 -0800 (PST)
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.


‘Economic Plan Is Breaking Records.’  (But Not in Good Way) <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe2uzmi9af_mKuTc3hREIzM4OINmWh1hvgUSBqX-8_fbfa80nEmN-UUeTU_u6oOQ16aA=> - President Joe Biden on Tuesday, in a tweet ahead of his State of the Union address, claimed his “economic plan is breaking records <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFeqLYiY9w8uIxkYWZPPjRfUtAz0-WT0UOt9MfA3WciKDHYgoVEeLCF-kVmiVW8PYxmzM=>.” Revolving debt is exploding as consumers wipe out savings to pay living expenses. Revolving debt is nearing $1 trillion <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFerl6e_ejGuNclfA5YgkqRTDmh_X9RLvUf_LjShw5cU-oNWdn7pVCEdcKYfqFiB9jsgE=>, an increase of more than $200 billion since Biden’s first such address two years ago. For a family of four, that represents $2,400+ in additional debt. The personal savings rate <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe3cl_xy2QoenvMBzIQ5-Pj3_j4c55IauHCQ_7C7rKWtxUly38zD2NmSLgmB88eLT6F4=> is near all-time 
lows of below 3%. The hottest inflation in more than 40 years has dwarfed the growth in income. Real average hourly earnings year-over-year fell for the 21st consecutive month in January. That’s an unmatched disaster. Median inflation-adjusted weekly earnings <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFezHKY5454AWW2smyqHJngfXEJA7wiEzvkB5GJx1yyC0UXIA6OTRVlo3sd4fFUBd0PrM=> dropped by 4.7% during Biden’s first two years—the biggest two-year plunge in more than 40 years. For a typical dual-income, married couple earning $60,000 each in 2020, inflation outpacing wage gains has eroded more than $5,600 in their standard of living. Indeed, in 2022, real disposable personal income dropped by a record 6.2%—the largest in history and for just the fourth time in the past 60 
years. Looking to buy a home? It’s never been this unaffordable <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFezHKY5454AWW2smyqHJngfXEJA7wiEzvkB5GJx1yyC0UXIA6OTRVlo3sd4fFUBd0PrM=>. The total median monthly payment on a home (mortgage principal and interest payments, taxes, and insurance) is more than $2,550 today versus under $1,600 when Biden took office—a payment hike of nearly $11,500 a year for a typical home. Heritage Expert: Joel Griffith <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFfFWiMfWso1PHBu9lQohJ1BmowMJ4SofWIzt-6avBvzmfBmjvBfWyMKbmpBdMvdkcXBg=>

Members of the 2025 Presidential Transition Project Coalition Respond to Biden’s State of the Union Address <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe1ttuaS9ph4vn0vnFXw1hd4hMDIph-WujZ2NLhogZsYaKJFhhBsSgHYmFfPuXTR6RjE=> - “The one real accomplishment Biden has a right to brag about is uniting conservatives.  Work to repeal and replace the disastrous legacy of Biden’s Administration cannot start soon enough. We are 50 (and growing) of America’s most prominent conservative organizations, joining forces to develop policies and a new generation of personnel to lead this great nation back on day one – January 20, 2025.” Heritage Expert: Paul Dans <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFexiRVhDTJGtNpXBPTQuPUEHSy3OKFDqYO0SR3Yusq1qN-zjV0pWkcDFtvYGO3vHSpns=>
The Case for Impeachment of Alejandro Nicolas Mayorkas Secretary of Homeland Security <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFeta4IuxOtI2P-JruRFM7SBcw1jiOpuYeDri0I3qeFlY9_ieQEoxe2fSNVMGdpQm8-Lk=> - Secretary of Homeland 
Security Alejandro Nicholas Mayorkas has been deaf to the voice of Americans, blind to the chaos and consequences of his policies and actions in violating the law, and untruthful in his statements to Congress and the American people. Secretary Mayorkas has intentionally undermined the sovereign interests of the United States by evading or violating the law and embracing policies he was warned would result in disaster. As Secretary of the Department of Homeland Security, he bears responsibility for this catastrophic failure. It is time for him to resign or be removed from office—for the protection and good of the men and women of the Department of Homeland Security and the American people and for the preservation of national sovereignty. Heritage Expert: Hans von Spakovsky <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe8rMaRfHsLOSWa3QajV7LkwlC8KmFeBjbp7BBIPnV5DOaxTdJruo_d0acWfD6R2WqyQ=>, Lora Ries <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFeuQA3b2VTxYf-XIVMn1Em8f3karjIKwUkFGFkaQWGdz5DCDwse5girAfkPtcQu8_WzU=> and Steven Bradbury <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFexP-O2-ajOQLYXvixXaVDVEIoEqfQ_ItqvGUHitNt7V-r6OPX7a_dn2chohqgAxfTKI=>
The Justice Department Is Wrong: Federal Law Does Prohibit Mailing Abortion Drugs <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe3Bo-C3VnsObtGMtASo6KR5FZhF3qFQAAAZqQfy7a6aJdLyTtRy1YtShc--2QlVasw0=> - A federal statute, 18 U.S.C. § 1461, prohibits “convey[ing] in the mails or deliver[ing] from any post office” any “article or thing designed, adapted, or intended for producing abortion.” In July 2022, the U.S. Postal Service asked the Justice Department’s Office of Legal Counsel (OLC) whether § 1461 prohibits mailing mifepristone and misoprostol, the drugs used to cause a majority of abortions today. In a December 2022 opinion, the OLC bypassed the established process for interpreting statutes, reading § 1461 so narrowly that it would be virtually unenforceable. While this would advance the Biden Administration’s abortion agenda, the Justice Department is wrong. The plain and ordinary meaning of § 1461 unambiguously prohibits mailing abortion drugs. Heritage Expert: Thomas Jipping <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFezXshqVGiXk7aXQZUPh50G76e3MlQwj4iImx83x1r87abfGq14wAbsUvhD93MTW4FF8=> and Sarah Parshall Perry <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFewG1zDKZh-Uj5lj4_aMbGXfc7dmojO3QVVq-nWCFwc4ZzOW_bmu8dMwZbFrk-F0Z7L0=>
 
Colorado Courts Still Don't Understand Religious Freedom <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe7Id1hayj6_G0foExMEVHHiNlGOylOKy8fi6q_-VUePo1eHlrdfcPf0zXLwryeBo6Cs=> - Phillips and his 
wife, Debra, are Christian co-owners of Masterpiece Cakeshop in Lakewood, Colorado. In business since 1993, Masterpiece sells pre-made goodies in the store, and custom cakes that Jack designs and creates. Phillips has said that he strives to be obedient to Jesus Christ “in all aspects of his life,” including in his business and in exercising his personal skill in creating designer cakes. To that end, the Masterpiece website <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe6ULffX-49cQPY1B647QNm7gz7oE_Yhkj0jz2Ap4DdhVj90VnPfq5qVE39F8tKoJVmw=> states that Phillips “cannot create custom cakes that express messages or celebrate events that conflict with his religious beliefs. Heritage Expert: Thomas Jipping <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFezXshqVGiXk7aXQZUPh50G76e3MlQwj4iImx83x1r87abfGq14wAbsUvhD93MTW4FF8=>


WHISTLEBLOWER DOCS: FBI Cites Southern Poverty Law Center in Report on 
‘Radical-Traditionalist Catholic Ideology’ <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe3_O2x6xkDZyIHw8DJtoD3bdlIZvwxuH70CGzhX4Y6vUHGhNlPOQhdxdDBWhCcUd5dc=> - “We got briefings that SPLC was not legitimate when I was at Quantico,” Kyle Seraphin, who served six years at the FBI as a special agent before getting indefinitely suspended without pay in June 2022, told The Daily Signal in a phone interview 
Wednesday. Seraphin published the document on UncoverDC.com Wednesday <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFepxoLf5GwV_qfdlhBPuA543VqWDYXMh4C3aHPfeR_pTuEzNJ3Uwo0gvxu6rPDk1_ObA=>. The document, “Interest of Racially or Ethnically Motivated Violent Extremists in Radical Traditionalist Catholic <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe2GcQALtkXLSVkzOTiH_qTagWg-yHMY_m6zlFCjqhnkWUnONUhhtFwE-R6eAe0UwdG8=> Ideology Almost Certainly Presents New Mitigation Opportunities,” 
bears markings reading “UNCLASSIFIED/FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY” and “FBI INTERNAL USE ONLY — DO NOT DISSEMINATE EXTERNALLY.” Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Nei <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFeomklXAg02T6_LvJkENQGE2SNeT2iUP3bgegFZQjUjEqbiurP3wDRgBxz5SGAb5yb7w=>


China Surpasses US in Nuclear Missile Launchers; US Unprepared to Deter Growing Threat <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe160ankKozjkT4vLObNMNfXIB_tDSKhw8DjKGd3awIpXuN7LNgMm2raLDAiuQ9-xnIs=> - As China engages 
in a rapid nuclear buildup as part of its strategy to achieve global dominance, the Pentagon announced <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe3H1AqsB9bnY5efDphU-AHevZcx8RDE2xZ10PXfeMlCMf00hj5jS-7Y0gvID0kzbvsw=> yesterday that the communist nation has surpassed the U.S. in the number of intercontinental ballistic missile launchers it has. The U.S. nuclear force was designed over a decade ago to deter primarily Russia, not both Russia and China <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFetReXhorPAy-nR3zBPN1CaT4Dh5eDWzgiJ9u4tCTpuQAKzmvhLV7uz84LOyE17imMSc=>. While the U.S. is modernizing its nuclear capabilities, it’s not to the scale we will need to deter this growing threat. Heritage Expert: Patty-Jane Geller <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ1RLFe0WRgDejubzFbQbl_nc0F2YIK5HnRxTnhi9ePNcou75cp-m8Og8bc1x0uU4BFW7Gi2A=>

Subject: Heritage Take: Policymakers Should Use Supreme Court Cases on Racial Preferences to Launch Reform of College Accreditation
Received: by 2002:adf:b31c:0:0:0:0:0 with SMTP id j28csp716083wrd;        Fri, 10 Feb 2023 04:15:25 -0800 (PST)
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.




Policymakers Should Use Supreme Court Cases on Racial Preferences to Launch Reform of College Accreditation <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwe7R5JpsqfPdrXryxl2o-gZBVMzINkAdmbJcXYcQgMT2LwRnWAmxYtCTrMb30s96bp8=> - The U.S. Supreme Court is expected to issue an opinion on Students for Fair Admission v. University of North Carolina and Students for Fair Admission v. Harvard in 2023, potentially rejecting race-based college admissions policies. If the Court rules that postsecondary institutions may not use race as a factor in school admissions, that decision will be a crucial step away from racial prejudice and toward meritocracy and colorblindness—two pillars of the civil rights movement. Some schools may ignore the ruling and unlawfully continue race-based policies because many employ dozens, or, more than a hundred, administrative staff who enforce racial bias, including critical race theory, on campus. State and federal lawmakers should restructure their college accreditation processes to give schools more autonomy in choosing the organizations that accredit their institutions, thereby weakening the federal accreditation cartel. Heritage Expert: Jonathan Butcher <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwHOKV0EqfIMZkwyaRAdJBNOouvG6wKbk_mQ82M1Wvmuinaz19enAvu7roj16Zisrxnk=>
China’s Spy Balloon Proves The U.S. Homeland Is Vulnerable <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwFdSxlCyGl7Rc7X_nnqHMPaVou3LEA_KsZht9Mv08Kz84KVS8VNVLb9r5f6aBd-BsL0=> -  Is there anything Team Biden won’t drag ex-President Donald Trump into as a butt-covering maneuver?  In this case, the embarrassment was the Chinese spy balloon fiasco <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwDVRAKyJ-CX51uj4E3I4OwbENkYasJFnqjfWR9bSBrhuMZsEreQGRYoXIrAVzRK5VKI=>. And the butt-covering was the “leak” from a “defense official” that balloons from Beijing entered US airspace at least three times in the Trump years. Except that Trump and a pack of top ex-Trump officials then all insisted <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwDoOKOWQEwkJqiVL3ivhoYnTG1vK6oVcswoJPMDn-gf2jEiTty1WkjI9gP5Dbe4g-6M=> they’d never been briefed on such incursions — and word came out that the incidents went undetected until the then-prez left office. Heritage Expert: Jim Carafano <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwM0LKztWmO8KbTVIyftEFHngtBtj9jQVjBUDyrxOEJOC0cbef35duyNai5B0cfoFqU4=>
D.C. statehood requires constitutional amendment <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwLeagA_U6iAlznwiDCaEXRe3gHpPY8QT4-y2Ye5sfKTE_Ti4xPHe1rDXF4OJpBWfgx0=> - When Philadelphia served as our nation’s capital, Pennsylvania refused to protect members of the Continental 
Congress against angry mobs. No wonder the framers of our Constitution wanted the new seat of our federal government to be free from the influence of any one state. Heritage Expert: Zack Smith <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwXaVRf9a1RZAE0GPJqPjcAC0LjudFYFqQziLq7c9uDKcjb0fGLLOU7d8fbjpaplKilw=>

Bipartisan Legislation Introduced to End Outdated Iraq War Authorizations <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwK_UTrBk7Tx2oNz0RwNl1YaG3iMjt4Ozx5n3teCjgi5r7YFQmqFlxwopslzj-BkXwoo=> - A remarkable thing 
happened in Washington this morning, especially given the vituperative atmosphere of politics today. Legislators introduced substantive legislation that is good policy, and a policy that The Heritage Foundation has been advocating <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwCf4wpmkm2I1ZU72IgnydMkLxijcKMGlYco2mnWX7qLP8ClqQE6dtbU2rFCT8dYbwt0=> for years. A large bipartisan group of 22 Senators introduced <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwN32XfYtYzfwyf3s99NaX-VGD6KazzOAUlfjf5AIo7YzLRjaatj3OoS5X-igy0WEbH0=> legislation to repeal the 1991 and 2002 Iraq Authorizations for the Use of Military Force, or AUMF. Repealing the two AUMFs is sound policy <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwCf4wpmkm2I1ZU72IgnydMkLxijcKMGlYco2mnWX7qLP8ClqQE6dtbU2rFCT8dYbwt0=>. As we have written <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwfjdhem5IBEFtjB682Whpr75RzpKLfxe5OQYeqIMW81g72omq1BvPcF52Nl46JSyz4k=> previously, these two war authorizations remain in force, even though their purposes were accomplished a long time ago. Heritage Expert: Cully Stimson <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwbBxY_xU8h8P_chwhqDx4doyGagJvmIRPgrFBfNmUZ7xn9QtAK0jUmGC_dHoREDCjtw=>
Why are people fleeing Illinois? <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwFAu5L5q7n0xUpoF3Nd9XqPpXTZrhu88GresoPsOOxTrhzSygCYJqctAzpnBGuDbXQY=> - Lots of people complain. But when they’re really fed up, they “vote with their feet.” And by that metric, Illinois is one of the most unpopular states in the nation. The latest Census Bureau data show that the Land of Lincoln <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwJObTxmG5rK5oEuhSy9jB05ZeUbKRV2AA8ZL-O854og-5KKalnvjGvhDp6T9N-7yFKc=> is hemorrhaging people at an astonishing rate — and public policy is likely to blame. Heritage Expert: EJ Antoni <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwBtblFIbZpLl0nhcipZ8W8asf0U_C8aWaJ2cuBm_PM4x3nLfSvBbGLo8ZHnqIl1bo1E=> 
BREAKING: FBI Rescinds Memo Citing Southern Poverty Law Center After Daily Signal Report <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwZ175cSTQXm2SpzpRpLJdAtn7is5T4IzS4NLGtuD5s73uZJplpW_lB_YCyw4_0Il-Ds=> - 
The Federal Bureau of Investigation rescinded a report on “radical-traditionalist Catholic ideology” on Thursday, one day after an 
FBI whistleblower <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwYp--pEpJTcwCAPqk_eLwx02s560cJfKqkl7IfAtKhTS7il8JqG_9l3ruvq8hyIJkSs=> published the document and The Daily Signal reached out to the FBI for comment. Former FBI agents condemned the document for citing the Southern Poverty Law Center, a left-wing smear factory infamous for branding mainstream conservative and Christian organizations “hate groups” and placing them on a map with Ku Klux Klan chapters. “While our standard practice is to not comment on specific intelligence products, this particular field office product—disseminated only within the FBI—regarding racially or ethnically motivated violent extremism does not meet the exacting standards of the FBI,” the FBI told The Daily Signal <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwItQs2E3i0rECrd7HQYlS0_QQFCraG4a5VS8wljyz5UbSp7jFXdLUM_tNK5YKn5HHz8=> in a statement emailed Thursday. Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil
School choice for rural SC <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwAM2VZ4HYnoMZDiWPvfG3qyZs-cUjY7ggTm4qjDX2bUxN1dhRRpdwkLRRP2a4Hb7-K0=> - possible.” So declared Gov. Henry McMaster in recently proclaiming School Choice Week in South Carolina. To that end, the South Carolina legislature is currently considering a proposal to give families greater freedom to choose learning environments that align with their values and meet their children’s individual learning needs. The proposal would create education savings accounts (ESAs), letting families access about $6,000 in state funds to pay for private school tuition, tutoring, textbooks, online courses, special needs therapy and numerous other educational expenses. Ten states have already adopted ESA policies, including five in the last two years. Heritage Expert: Jason Bedrick <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwNl5Bl69CqPHX77Dsqxa-rcZStQwReTB28IXA4r7urlhVE6tn4pz8MfjFEYfyG_v4Jg=> 

Conservatives Call on States to Close Loopholes Allowing Big Money to Bankroll Election Operations <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwF4w0U6Vedthe0KJvWhaV5mi6_m6E5YW9svSgKR8LoD3hqFOcURqK3rMwP8gTCKLCSI=> - Conservative organizations are calling for state legislatures to close loopholes regarding private funding of elections, after the same organization that distributed the Mark Zuckerberg election grants in 2020 issued a $2 million grant to a county in Georgia, one of two dozen states to ban private funding of election offices. “States across the country have made great strides in promoting election integrity. But now, a new alliance of left-wing partisan organizations led by the Center for Tech and Civic Life (CTCL) is working to influence state election offices behind the scenes,” says a joint statement from Heritage Action for America Executive Director Jessica Anderson and Honest Elections Project Executive Director Jason Snead. Heritage Expert: Fred Lucas <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ2jkbwazKgB7aOXq8Ny6TOssRh3SBHByOngT5lAay8TQcGN-Mf6QzwMZB9RUe_fUDuxWrLHc=>

-
