Subject: Fwd: Welcome
Body:
Fellow Conservative,

I reached out a few days ago to thank you for subscribing, and I just wanted to make sure you saw my e-mail.

I sent you a link to an American Policy Survey so that we could learn a little more about where you fall on the issues central to Heritage’s mission, and your thoughts on these questions are crucial to helping us serve you more effectively.

Your opinions are important—don’t delay!

I’ve re-attached the link here for your convenience: https://pages.joinheritage.org/policy-survey/ <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ5JeKeytvLloPV3t-wyuQbYWYyzunUSX7Jtzm8yEI8tABaJKSWhKeEsctwGeN1e6IkbMQ9Vk=>

Thanks,

Alexander HyattMembership Programs



---------------------------------------------
From: Alexander Hyatt <info@heritage.org>
To:  <evelperson6+partyheritage@gmail.com>
Subject: Welcome

Fellow Conservative,

Hello! My name is Alexander Hyatt, and I work on the Membership team here at The Heritage Foundation.

I just wanted to touch base and say thank you for signing up!

Everyone has a reason they come to Heritage, and I would love to get to know yours.

Will you please take a moment to tell me and my team what you believe about taxes, government spending, illegal immigration, and more by taking this Heritage American Policy Survey <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ5JeKeytvLloPV3t-wyuQbYWYyzunUSX7Jtzm8yEI8tABaJKSWhKeEsctwGeN1e6IkbMQ9Vk=> we’ve specially prepared for you today?

It’ll only take a few minutes, but the information you provide is crucial to helping us learn more about what’s important to you. Your insights will let me and my team keep you updated on the issues you care about most.

Simply click here to start taking your Heritage American Policy Survey now! <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ5JeKeytvLloPV3t-wyuQbYWYyzunUSX7Jtzm8yEI8tABaJKSWhKeEsctwGeN1e6IkbMQ9Vk=>

Best,

Alexander Hyatt
Senior Membership Programs Manager
The Heritage Foundation

P.S.Fellow Conservative, the future of conservatism is too important to leave up to someone else. Please click here <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ5JeKeytvLloPV3t-wyuQbYWYyzunUSX7Jtzm8yEI8tABaJKSWhKeEsctwGeN1e6IkbMQ9Vk=> to take and submit your Heritage American Policy Survey right now!

-

Subject: Heritage Take: Health Insurance Enrollment in 2021 and Its Implications for 2023
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.




Health 
Insurance Enrollment in 2021 and Its Implications for 2023 <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuCXxLwIx3yzAiBmL3u6XCJ7wOxLJKtqB767ZelV0uZcpUUW-pXD4rSyvxErThYHcn54=> - In 2021, enrollment in employment-based group coverage declined while enrollment in individual-market (non-group) coverage and Medicaid increased. Those coverage gains were primarily driven by temporary, COVID-19-related increases in federal funding and subsidies, accompanied by rules that likely kept many no-longer-eligible individuals on Medicaid. Even before those temporary changes, the data show that the main effect of the Affordable Care Act (ACA) has been to increase enrollment in Medicaid. The increased Medicaid funding will phase out in 2023 and lawmakers should also end the excessive ACA subsidies enacted in response to COVID-19. Congress should instead reduce health care costs by expanding competition and price transparency and eliminate anti-competitive regulations and business practices that protect favored health care providers. Heritage Expert: Ed 
Haislmaier <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuGmmGdy1IGVh9jXuABh40TVRHDKxSEEpBPxbSZRy6R9DGcPdMu1TwXz33GtEhck4cGE=>

South 
Dakota Bans Affirming Treatment - “Gender ideology” displaces the sexual binary of male and female—which describes all mammals including humans—with a subjective notion of “gender identity” that is independent of the body. Hence, champions of this ideology avoid references to sex. They typically define “gender identity” as … one’s internal sense of gender. Note that this is both circular and unfalsifiable.

The most toxic fruit of this ideology, however, is in medicine. For minors, it involves refashioning the body with drugs and scalpel to fit a distorted idea in the mind. In the US, gender transition surgeries for adolescents increased 
nearly fivefold <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuMsnt-HX7kXRaCGj7Nn63RwLE8PZu0BhNbP6_oZIiGOlceSKt6taBv1q5D2ckLbi7_s=> from 2016 to 2019. Starting a child down the “gender affirmation” pathway makes it far more likely he or she will go all the way, even if he or she later comes to regret it. Here’s the dirty little secret: There’s no reliable scientific evidence that these treatments improve the long-term mental health of these minors, let alone that the benefits outweigh the many risks. Heritage Expert: Jay Richards <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuPBgU6dyOaxp_136Uxh0IZPP-64mrFAGnug8Jh8l2pn-vHLFkTRKhyPWNsqgMvVgL1Y=>

The American left is Pushing ESG Policies That Would Force Businesses and Financial Institutions To Bow To Their Radical Agenda <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuPn3OjqRGPj17RIL0ZKHFuFiiFYBBFhPFT9AF3FlEYgkZofDOd8w3tlGz3Sb8aqTx1k=>– From requiring NASDAQ-listed companies to appoint board members based on race and sex, to requiring onerous greenhouse gas 
emission reporting, ESG is destroying economic freedom and undermining America’s cultural fabric of freedom. ESG policies are a thinly veiled attempt to radically transform American businesses into social justice warriors that can shut conservatives and others who don’t comply out of the public square. Pro-ESG businesses support the left's “woke” culture war to redefine sex, promote critical race theory, and cancel conservatives. ESG is being weaponized against both businesses and individuals who don’t comply with the left’s radical policies. Low ESG scores threaten law-abiding Americans, with everything from denial of loans to de-platforming from financial services. Heritage Experts: Andy Olivastro <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUt2fn6XF8UAT4N4wgTm8KuDUIdtVqojXpzxJKUEfuUgphQJvmVIgMi3aMbieFz7dXJGw=> and Joel Griffith <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuNtHJ_FeTHGQPfVjj54IUp_id207tsf9WHnwZU2Z82wor_au5naF5IE0r9qbKHvcOd0=>
Another 
Study Refutes Left’s False Claims Against Voter ID and Secure Elections <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuFWIGW5oQXuMDoRq4xGuG2NwnYiLriOyZ8zKKUW6BTTl3OljTyyVDm4YolNbDIaikk8=> - In other words, voter security benefits both parties and all Americans. The new study points to numerous reasons why this is the case. The researchers’ conclusions emphatically demonstrate that Republican support for an issue doesn’t necessarily mean that it’s bad for Democrats. In fact, in contrast to the myth of voter suppression, the study found that both parties saw an increase in voter turnout after implementation of voter ID laws. This mutual increase is itself a benefit worth pursuing. Not only is this a refutation of the Left’s claims that these commonsense reforms amount to “Jim Crow 2.0, <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuAiqB2DzmMU6CY0Glbq8kpta_WvCtLs7jor3c7EWGEe2JBsb2fnlv7A5mC1uk-VYWyA=>” but the increased voter turnout actually strengthens diverse voter representation in our country by including more citizens in the election process. Heritage Expert: Hans 
von Spakovsky <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuLP_BTYbhFnXiN66FYXrDwfd___WAU9RcR-FyHH7onMx3durMPsk-mmxeNaPilvL98c=>

Public 
policy hitting Americans hard <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuM2EKC8K095SvkjXOjZaFZSG-KpaJ0wthkbVPDtQ8TM0cJ3fXMmE1teQZiaxzLG5RWM=> - If you think public policy doesn’t really affect you or your family, take a quick glance at your retirement account – but you may want to sit 
down first. Those accounts have taken a beating lately because of the misguided policies emanating from Washington, D.C., and the result is a dramatic reduction in wealth for the average American family. Heritage Expert: EJ 
Antoni <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuBblpUy4wC-Oa70k5zw13VXibA4h-ZWY1t0EGQ3mmj95VLbvdoGq2HaayLN-dTQaxro=> 

North 
Korea’s Growing ICBM Threat: How America And South Korea Should Respond <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuLzdTvLCNXX7kS3_ujnrXlb6ddpFScT_gZjAXlVSktoNxWJHj6LEelLkcqoj-OV2-fk=> - North Korea’s steadily expanding long-range missile arsenal <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuOQSoV0BYp_Fa0szlbXjGX3jGwk5RDh5KsksZlr_wbjoOKGaNqVeMRfltVW7U1JIqlA=> risks overwhelming the limited number of ground-based interceptors defending the American homeland. This, in turn, will magnify escalating allied concerns that Washington, if faced with a credible nuclear threat from the regime, may not come to their defense against North Korean aggression. Heritage Expert: Bruce 
Klingner <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuOZF5qIMvprAA8z80qz_PIYBha4rZU0K5qedmobkraEmvB02sIzOVFytVXBK2GBsamU=> 

 

Maintain 
Tight Banking Controls On Iraq To Defund Iran <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuEplwgDO0yHaivRzkFpRkZGI8D6iLicULWhwR_s3gWMUzj1X0iO-Z8IfDpdvOyjF2-A=> - Iraqi Foreign Minister Fuad Hussein is in Washington, D.C., to, according to a White House statement <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuDgiGXYeao9yPbh3UX6AWfh395ZdEli3j8NEzSo3ZUxVSPobVbFGBzkTOv2Fawm2hNQ=>, “ensure that Iraq’s economy is delivering for the Iraqi people.” Translation: The Iraqi delegation wants the U.S. Treasury and Federal Reserve Bank of New York to relax stringent rules recently imposed on Iraq’s dollar transactions. Heritage Expert: Max 
Primorac <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuN8x27IUUF-WTwASnE0Z8q8sjXBgzZvuWjqyuqVjH4MKfcvRDgVon4Znm32doHS1C7g=>

Conservatives 
must wake up to the threat of government-endorsed racial categorization <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuLSJmiIEzogzcFqPyaE8hQIdMRbBNuM6JqIuf1xVepVyjmiNJP180Uqvz7zV2Sks6lg=> - Conservatives haven’t been as interested as progressives are in capturing the federal bureaucracy, or at least have been much less successful. That goes double for the Census Bureau <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuORV6QGZQUyibRkUEWmQw5CzfQ87-3T2GMF53KIRMe1KQkDA23GuTvqwzSu-nMXkXFY=> , whose committee on race has long been the play-thing of sociology professors and affinity groups. Heritage Expert: Mike 
Gonzalez <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ7tKUuIMUyUWo1w_u96Pv2lpSTHtG_805cWcv-1uxq66LgLXgbIHS8GBaeE7--sNyTknNXMA=>

Subject: Heritage Take: What’s at Stake for the U.S. in Ukraine
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.




 

 

What’s at Stake for the U.S. in Ukraine <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt4xwwgTyzf3R0eKURmarlrms_Ikoei20UNTfTTh69bUmqSBSqkyPAZF1cRZYBO15PscY=> - Russia’s continuing assault on Ukraine is a brutal reminder that war remains a feature of international relations. The U.S. and its allies can best support Ukraine by ensuring the continued flow of munitions, expanding Ukraine’s inventory of artillery, providing armor to enable offensive operations, improving defensive capabilities against enemy ground and air attack, and enhancing Ukraine’s ability to understand what the enemy is doing, so that it can make the best use of its resources. Heritage Expert: Dakota Wood <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5IOAmQw6i7-yQw5ZqhK3VLXjcJOHFLR5xsUdFPYiOmsQN4TegaGs9OlZxPMLhD4u2m0=>
Ohio Train Derailment Disaster Reinforces Need For More Pipelines <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5GFup9eOOre5epB2N7pjYdwJrb_atZIPqsO1QXb4g4SHaFmnW3-wDzh-8-R2GjMWb9I=> 
- This frightening incident should lead us to reexamine our pipeline priorities. Although the chemicals on the train could not move by pipeline, pipelines are used for natural gas and petroleum—and we need more of them. Pipelines are the safest way to transport oil and natural gas because the pipeline stays still and the gas moves, away from people, with little risk of accident. New technology shows pipeline operators if there is a pinhole leak in a pipe, and sophisticated pressure gauges can signal if oil pressure is declining. Heritage Expert: Diana Furchtgott-Roth <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5ETB2dAyZhZ7zJ7kzrKaCBY6QfwxQWta9p3DMKPYwj0JpPddCB133acZE0Z0CkTTB0o=>

Protecting Parents’ Rights with the Given Name Act <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt43OKuuPxjWUKJwKEwlxZ8Uygc1L6__Vz-q8-BMxKQrYU6NtKC3Komq4KXcMNNOrxyCk=> - K–12 
schools across the country, including in deeply conservative areas, have started addressing children by names that are not theirs, and using pronouns that differ from their sex—without their parents’ knowledge or consent. Parents know their children best, and their authority should not be superseded by teachers and school administrators. Schools should not make potentially life-altering decisions for a child behind parents’ backs. Lawmakers can support parental rights by enacting legislation, such as the Given Name Act, proposed by The Heritage Foundation. Heritage Expert: Jason Bedrick <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5J8hhC_3kFfx5F1qW19L6qPMGYsILLxMfJ_7Rx3wFJqEnjZLfT8MevIQX71cxTJwKX8=> and Jonathan 
Butcher <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5Hi0T_D3vEsUXJPof-KMCuzwDdbPQzF8OrHwULU2EzePNMbz2tFLo9HAzk8YMKbU4JQ=>
Washington’s Reckless Spending Continues to Imperil Americans’ Financial 
Futures  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5H-r0BeNeHbn0VICgbAz--s2WOQvo_JNFv-K9cclgpMUUCiojGVgFOysO-EmtnCEdjU=>- For the last three years, Congress has spent trillions of dollars that we simply don’t have. The Federal Reserve created the money to finance those unprecedented levels of spending, which caused inflation. As the Federal Reserve belatedly acts to rein in inflation, it continues to work at cross-purposes to Congress, which continues to overspend. The more Congress overspends, the tighter the Federal Reserve will have to squeeze the private economy to bring down inflation, increasing the risk of slowing the economy even further. It is imperative that Congress begin cutting spending immediately. The explosion of deficits and debt over the last three years have put the federal budget in a precarious position where rising interest rates will automatically add an additional $300 billion <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5Lxvp7-Lo6gQnx01wmUvACc-xdw22psXOP2RchwvQB6sSGaWYSqo3GnaCLiqgPi-U38=> to the next budget,” said EJ Antoni, research fellow in regional economics with The Heritage Foundation. Heritage Expert: EJ Antoni <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt4-1g9QdB1_jduKE3NcDEh4pkx_CFdBcZAh9MX0DUmxEWuttuHgxCnDAFYESIJV1bEY8=>

South Dakota’s New Law to Protect Children Should Inspire More States to Follow Suit <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt447pdOv_M3p_HRp2woZWac83VeGWQrHb7IuutahELdIgA6BSJE36QCIMxSyzOT6y1WM=> - Jay Richards <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5KLraOe9rDpvRTGt9ixYd5nG41pP9mpFfGOaQzctPa7N-RNoDSVrlHMvUS481MZXpPs=>, director of the DeVos Center for Life, Religion, and Family at The Heritage Foundation, made the following statement: “The tragic story of Chloe Cole <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt44BPJgilhj1dek9ZgbwF1vJ3A1nP0FYZT7iwgCYauE95q6q5BNWXPL8LPvpwn3VtirM=>—who identified as transgender and submitted to surgery she later regretted—should be an alarm to all parents. Gender ideologues have infiltrated the federal government, the medical industry, and many of our public schools. They are promoting a harmful ideology that creates confusion and distress in children. There’s no solid scientific evidence that the benefits of these so-called ‘treatments’ exceed the risks for children with gender distress. And yet gender ideologues push such kids into a school-to-sterilization pipeline—kids who are not old enough to understand the permanent damage this can do to their bodies and minds.” Heritage Expert: Jay Richards <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5KLraOe9rDpvRTGt9ixYd5nG41pP9mpFfGOaQzctPa7N-RNoDSVrlHMvUS481MZXpPs=>

The United States, Italy, and Winning the Med <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt47g8JOXkqKOCbG32oYLhKx3vS_SnYmFngWiuNxhwekyjdYFmCsLokJxNXfxVAqSLVcI=> - Russia’s brutal invasion of Ukraine is grabbing all the attention. But we need to look South, too. Neither the European Union nor NATO will be the strategic leaders in the Greater Mediterranean. Washington and Rome will have to play that role. Heritage Expert: Jim Carafano <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5L0xXmEuyogc1xaLHTLbD7kLfyJ1FORm-DcGg5fkj16tDiOcsryvtCybcNvR2kMlNYY=>
House Republicans Demand Answers on CDC’s New Database to Monitor Why 
Americans Didn’t Take Covid-19 Vaccine <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5N4O_Gu9is3fYfunZr-SNFdILz38olIL3y3RVPPb81LiQ8C3l5ZmYPRyRVqm3_eCwzQ=> - House Republicans sent a letter Tuesday to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, demanding answers about a new classification system that allows 
the CDC to record the reasons why Americans refused to take one of the COVID-19 vaccines <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5EeitXXC11cZiosS3TpVfz__XXOjv6guRRhtWJy-ohkxH1xRIbbVZYq56NNB_zHS7cM=>. “Naturally, we are concerned about the federal government gathering data on Americans’ personal choices—data that serves no sincere purpose in treating patients’ medical conditions—and how it may be used in the future,” the Republican lawmakers, led by Rep. Chip Roy, R-Texas, wrote. Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5Khlz-Bo4wQ-arN5BvKa3uRgyLDSgSwcN87hi2CtXKdVL0KeD5kG-5gnLQMd41nXKJA=>
 
Defense Expert Provides Chilling Insight Into US-China Relations After Spy Balloon Incident <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt44cwUf-uYvQ2wGfQ31ZlyntK-tSJDakBRG33ujDLHqvl1suIUlyzDLeslr5gylqa6YU=> - Now, the U.S. might be facing a situation with China that could be more dangerous than at any moment in the Cold War, in the wake of the shooting down Feb. 4 of a Chinese spy balloon after it flew over U.S. territory. “Well, one of the more concerning reports out of this whole thing is the fact that the Pentagon rang up their buddies over in China, a hotline, and said, ‘We’re concerned about this thing, whatever it is,’ and nobody on the Chinese side answered the phone,” Dakota Wood, senior research fellow in defense programs in The Heritage Foundation’s Center for 
National Defense, says on today’s episode of “The Daily Signal Podcast.” Heritage Expert: Dakota Wood <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ8_jt5IOAmQw6i7-yQw5ZqhK3VLXjcJOHFLR5xsUdFPYiOmsQN4TegaGs9OlZxPMLhD4u2m0=>

Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

                                                     


How DNA and cell phone evidence in Idaho murders complied with the Fourth Amendment <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZTzrxDtnPOkqMc-yDh9tEyHzeFb5DjbnZpS_Ner4-lc0exWn5AocIuKBOiJA_cW1T9E=> – Did the police violate the Fourth Amendment rights of the man accused of slaying four college students in Idaho? Much has been made of the fact that 
authorities relied, in part, on genetic genealogy and DNA evidence to justify the arrest warrants in this case. But the use of such technology, and the way it was likely used in this case, was lawful, as was the use of cell site location information (CSLI) used to track the movement of the suspect’s phone. Heritage Expert: Cully Stimson <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZaHUc1DOY0CBn9Yy03FeTw0fzqbNHgW8IPXJTh3LpEiU0cGmFg5RSFDCGfoZYlkfc60=>
 
Ohio Train Derailment Disaster Reinforces Need For More Pipelines <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZfcCwjMkg-pJozGE-KXkArmy5P6U3qSxLSJNm-GQZSRhdiihxGeQEAeYgvxI8z69syw=> - This frightening incident should lead us to reexamine our pipeline priorities. Although the chemicals on the train could not move by pipeline, pipelines are used for natural gas and petroleum—and we need more of them. Pipelines are the safest way to transport oil and natural gas because the pipeline stays still and the gas moves, away from people, with little risk of accident. New technology shows pipeline operators if there is a pinhole leak in a pipe, and sophisticated pressure gauges can signal if oil pressure is declining. Heritage Expert: Diana Furchtgott-Roth <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZPgqRRhUgbWuOd12q8W-G0RFFNhWVjwhO-d6ZFB_wNu-wv-y420OABvrQvtTQlu5RuE=>
The big school choice turnaround in Iowa that more states should follow  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZAgC5wqLVZtOMB5VME7fpm2OhACoIgWs7VlMIEneZJ59xJCaQYistErI6HxMHhiJsvM=>- The Student First Act will provide Iowa families education 
saving accounts (ESAs) that they can use for private school tuition, tutoring, textbooks, curricular materials, and a variety of other education expenses. The ESAs, funded with a portion of the state's per-pupil spending, are worth about $7,600 annually. That more than covers the average private elementary school tuition in Iowa (about $5,400) and nearly covers the average private high school tuition (about $9,200). Heritage Expert: Jason Bedrick <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZb-vg979CR9AcRXTHrKfYsNfSvtFdwGPBB7IuTuZNpAu_VBRlbUpLKXoc_vuiVxWzcs=> 
Five Years After Parkland, Florida’s Measured Response Is An Outlier <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZKI7HVInGoKZ-8pk50GNd9T_hqJRRosRJS5UYIjy0R5waLFO2KM5JdoxaJL95iKiNjQ=> – Five years ago today, on February 14, 2018, a teen gunman walked into the halls of Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Florida, and murdered 17 
people. The shooting was all the more tragic for the several layers of official failure surrounding it. There were far too many missed warning signs that should have resulted in intervention, and a bungled emergency response that led to far more deaths and injuries than should have been possible.  Heritage Expert: Amy Swearer <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZD4md-d01oOrMEk6uMGmg3UzAwCyGrW_QzHZr33FbFbSZ86tv1per3F2Lg_t3smYR9U=>

Welcome to Sanctuary City! Feds, pay up <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZcXyk78_cxsM-yTY2PKaUrPk6vuLkHTv7b_iVKVnKNiEHJaN5O_oowue9rVuhSLO5aQ=> – Most recently, Biden has abused his parole authority. The Immigration and Nationality Act expressly limits using this power to deal with individual cases. Yet Biden is applying it to entire nationalities, allowing tens of thousands of immigrants a month into the country without visas, vetting or voter approval. Several states have sued, arguing that the parole “pathways” policy unconstitutionally usurps congressional authority over immigration matters. This could drag on for years. Heritage Expert: Simon Hankinson <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZMKyxz1U2-A2wF40PLYF7mjqY_cavIy2bMWjsX6sdStH_sH7yyc2O-940KChMccuH4Y=>
 
Censorship and Collusion: House Judiciary Subpoenas Big Tech CEOs for Answers <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZAgraYWw9r9_fzVcsvQqeYGZl3AcXn03c1Z2I15YxJr6AC8JPwgtfUV1o24yVrcdRLQ=> - The House Judiciary Committee <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZJLNfw_Kr9tKYO2fksU3CEWfxZvzau5L04tptSz5FytcjK8_j39jbbTtU8rZEUYS99o=> has subpoenaed five Big Tech executives to produce documents by late March about collusion with federal government agencies to suppress free speech. “To develop effective legislation, such as the possible enactment of new statutory limits on the Executive Branch’s ability to work with Big Tech to restrict <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZLhwoUj-NphoAc23D7X0SkYUTySeOAxaPH3cewz9D72Sp4bwm9lPwm8OsrXJsg_Xukc=> the circulation of content and deplatform users, the Committee on the Judiciary must first understand how and to what extent the Executive Branch coerced and colluded with companies and other intermediaries to censor speech,” the letters from 
Judiciary Committee Chairman Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, to the CEOs say. Heritage Expert: Fred Lucas <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZMhv-wk_zbjydxkkuYO2ZA71vhfSZdcB91u_YOE_zitLmm8rVC3FYbJGM0D525fm5oY=>
 
Biden: If you want our help, you must accept our gender ideology <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZBk4-Cl9zUlPgH0hNOhXeirmrGMYKhHCuCCNsF2lnQD53Z4yg6pikOdYeZVbbrlWATw=> - Beneath its euphemisms, gender ideology is irrational, destructive and anti-human. Nevertheless, the left is trying to bully and confuse Americans into accepting it. Heritage Expert: Grace Melton <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZcSNcJoLdX6v_iXhP4MTsancvCTXtrhPmnj6gNQQvl-6oRIIeYOzbIF_jD4YkbSmDtU=>
 
Babies aren’t disposable, at any stage <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZFFCHEf2TXGjlc-WajpNYVUHSxJooxdFqK-MKi1dGx6sNKVUqQRmTV3nWT1nM0MtUJQ=> - So, what’s the big deal? The Pro-Life movement, accused of “forced pregnancies” and rejecting a “woman’s right to choose,” should endorse any method that leads to the birth of 
children, right? Not so fast. As Kristan Hawkins <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZOzTFL_uW8B2r71Fvv79i2Hs2eduskguTh5kDKPsS09qpgVaXPkRqWBmtEjCi-H6cvs=>, president of Students for Life argues, “The issue was not whether we want people to create families (we’re the pro-life movement—we love babies) but whether creating disposable children, a common event with IVF, is a good idea.” They are 
“disposable” babies due to common IVF practices like embryo destruction, freezing, genetic testing, and genetic editing. Heritage Expert: Emma Waters <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ-R9TZUMAeZKIZ27vfzSXX-PElBm84ntx4LXngWa6XrVvJlLvLFH_JSh5HVRA9SZLqogg5UU=>

-

Subject: Why Heritage?
Body:
Fellow Conservative,

What sets The Heritage Foundation apart from all the other policy groups out there?


Founded in 1973 to combat the threat of the liberal agenda, The Heritage Foundation is the brainchild of conservative giants Edwin Feulner, Paul Weyrich, and Joseph Coors.

We really took off once Ronald Reagan became President. He relied heavily on Heritage for sound conservative policy advice. In fact, our Mandate for Leadership report was required reading for all members of President Reagan’s cabinet—and The Heritage Foundation has been making our presence felt in the halls of power ever since.

Our mission is the same today as it was then: to promote the ideas of free enterprise, limited government, individual freedom, traditional American values, and a strong national defense.

Through our policy experts who regularly appear on TV, our scholarly reports, and our Daily Signal news site read by millions every month, The Heritage Foundation has lots of incredible resources to help conservatives articulate their beliefs—and the reasoning behind them.

We’re having a huge impact in shaping federal policy, too. In fact, our experts are invited to testify in front of Congress an average of 40 times a year!

But Heritage is the largest and most effective conservative think tank in America ONLY because of committed conservatives like you, who have stood by us throughout the last 50 years.

I’m glad to be able to count you among our subscribers, and as a key part of this great conservative movement. If you have any questions, please feel free to reply to this email and let me know.

Best,

Alexander HyattMembership Programs

-

Subject: Heritage Take: Shocking Cost of the Illegal Immigration Crisis on Americans
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

                                                     
Shocking Cost of the Illegal Immigration Crisis on Americans <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI5zFQtd1lisNDiepKxTLmaUNLRb9Xuw9KaIlKO1wVymaHtOVcsz-9ep09rQE2mWEpcg=> - As record numbers of illegal aliens 
continue to flood across our southern border, they are being dispersed into every congressional district in the country, making every state a border state. Why do open-borders advocates ignore the enormous toll on Americans that comes in the form of higher taxes, overloaded emergency rooms, increased crime in their communities, and overcrowded classrooms for their children? The financial cost of illegal immigration to Illinois, for example—hardly a border state—was $4.59 billion in 2022. That’s $930 per household. Every year. This piece covers some of the heavy financial and human toll that illegal immigration is taking on the states and their citizens. Heritage Expert: Erin Dwinell <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyIw_gJkyV4bh2rVpKwRXXiZRlyMJ0B8ABxA5PZDn36AaFJdxlgL3Bdpcyw978wj3KMug=>
The ERA Has Just One Purpose Left: Abortion <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyJBV7DC_MbLPtfG5_mVwzISiosmcz_11jkc_KEW3xykR8tPde2VRNYf2nJeixhf-ojBI=> - “The Equal Rights Amendment has absolutely nothing to do with abortion,” insisted Representative Carolyn Maloney (D., N.Y.) in an 
April 2019 Judiciary Committee hearing <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI-uaVh3apIvpkwqDJg78r14QE5G6FFxX2XEIK0lgG6PROyWwnwSnRAQCW3m1LZPinnc=>. Maloney has been the ERA’s primary House sponsor for the past 25 years. Methinks, however, that the representative doth protest way too much. The ERA-abortion connection had already been established for more than 40 years when Maloney tried to deny it. The 1972 ERA <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyIzayj_sehZjCSP7CE_v_ueXwGV-vIOLz9VvF7Z5Ev5YKhNDah_DdgOYeOjwqcvbXl7w=> provided that “equality of rights under the law shall not be denied or abridged by the United States or any state on account of sex.” This was the only resolution, out of more than 1,000 introduced since 1923, to gain the two-thirds support that the Constitution requires to be 
sent to the states for ratification. Heritage Expert: Thomas Jipping <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI1Zfgs4RNdaApmiEDZ6qgqHZhDX1C0YZundH-b8M0nA2t35IInMxB6mxG2vq0G-jqzI=>
Reason, Revelation, and Identity Politics <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI3kxbwKI7r8WBeDdwR73lniENn9EAcuUe8VLoZYYlZzFE5Ywt689oWHOiP4_1xkg4AY=> - By refusing to take seriously the questions that underlie modern rationality, the West continues to undermine itself, to increase its own doubting and internal self-loathing. It makes its politics, its education, and its societies welcoming arenas for the atheism of unreason as mere subjectivity becomes the arbiter of what is ethical and good for man to do. The pathologies of reason and religion with which is plagued should not then be surprising. But the path forward is really the path of recovery of philosophical realism, the rebuilding of biblical faith, and the reawakening of love for constitutional republics. Heritage Expert: Richard Reinsh <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI--HutoHXmL-84UO_tbGTkdU7oxbIj87__jDVlUspR7FSAmpgBBJvRT62nBRbg3AxBU=>
 
Debunking Biden’s Malarkey: 7 Ways He Added a $6 Trillion to Deficits <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI3bwvjo8KlypRbj7ZS0C1s_IxkxW3a9nAkUDDq_r1cZBQnu14zRgbamLR4lT5-hcHZI=> - The deficit for fiscal year 2020 was a record $3.1 trillion. There’s no mystery about why: Lower tax revenue due to pandemic lockdowns <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI76o2WmiWR1NBjYv7D5VSk7blr_6OaRFsedgGpADA2IyFJ249pKnHe2IGGnJ9awGi2w=> reducing economic activity 
combined with increased spending (much of it wasted <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyIzL5YjN01cELutpLlmUfY1AjKZlgqhwwA6Ec_nviKd1Hhm2fvm2mYbCmyMp67jU5Wtw=>) meant the year was a perfect storm 
for adding to the national debt. Although some pandemic-related restrictions lingered <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI4Fjpk8xzXvept_AwltKyk46mMb95Tk04j8I5jGHZQAAK86I4zAztEJ2tPY-8Ehj1-s=>, the end of lockdowns meant the economy (and tax revenue) 
largely bounced back in fiscal year 2021—and this  would have happened regardless of who was president. Similarly, the bulk of stimulus spending enacted in 2020 wasn’t designed to carry over into future years, meaning that federal spending was expected to dip in 2021. Heritage Expert: David Ditch <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI3bwvjo8KlypRbj7ZS0C1s_IxkxW3a9nAkUDDq_r1cZBQnu14zRgbamLR4lT5-hcHZI=>
 
Like It or Not, the U.S. Is in a Nuclear Arms Race With China <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI6nbo--JcyY3YxY8QSJXvWr_1CejvcwBjq_beJapTahyqsOxAtJSJbRw9IJ2xZDC6mM=> - The U.S. is unprepared to deter China’s growing nuclear threat. The current U.S. structure was designed more than a decade ago and is based primarily on the need to deter Russia. Back then, most believed that China would maintain only a couple of hundred nuclear weapons. The Pentagon now projects Beijing will have at least 1,000 weapons by the end of the decade. As China builds up, the U.S. will need a nuclear force that can credibly convince China that the costs of using nuclear weapons would exceed the benefits. Right now, it isn’t clear the U.S. would be able to do that. America’s nuclear force isn’t large enough to take on Russia’s and China’s at the same time, which becomes more concerning when considering the potential for increased cooperation between the two countries. Heritage Expert: Patty-Jane Geller <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI14sb6HRZjp9_-_s96z7JDOk9xaYH84hRI1_dPxLivEBIsVTuzSnFoCm_295LMQaCZw=>
Gov. Youngkin Demands ‘Full Transparency and Accountability’ From FBI in Wake of ‘Radical-Traditional Catholic’ Memo <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI-aNcCsA7s_udekkMWKHlE8wn3Ctuu1gkeP1P-lb5eY5MUJKoTwKIGbHXu6UDEFwBSQ=> - The FBI memo urged agents to probe the supposed nexus between “racially or ethnically motivated violent extremists” and “radical-traditional Catholics,” citing the SPLC and including a list of SPLC-designated “hate groups” for agents to target. Some of Virginia’s representatives in Congress also addressed the memo—which the FBI announced it would remove from its database last week—although Sen. Tim Kaine, D-Va., did not condemn it. “Religious freedom is a foundational tenet of our great nation, and the governor was stunned by the news reports on the FBI memo,” Youngkin spokeswoman Macaulay Porter told The Daily Signal <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI7SZIo6ffPtT44hsMn9A9ZbHpTeZYQZFkyPzHVCOdUX1FS2u8QT6xCfKeGSiNfQXbvk=> in a statement Thursday. “While he is encouraged that the FBI removed the document, he believes there must be full transparency and accountability from FBI leadership as part of the review under way.” Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyJOBNxHl91o4f0xImp9s9YWnynU2-VzTUaNnZrOqr5jehK7V24S3ne3IRFiEfQvQkI3g=>
Biden DOJ is wrong: Federal law bars mailing abortion drugs <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI5GiuVHF7dtynuHKaxGIm0pjvGG5p3C2PR47xNhu66y6dY6hkIIVlOg_MnWVsFpazdE=> - Congress enacted what has become known as the Comstock Act in 1873, as a movement to stop what the American Medical Association 
condemned as the “slaughter of countless children” by abortion that swept the country. Named for Anthony Comstock, the anti-vice crusader who championed its passage, the act prohibited the Postal Service from delivering “any article or thing designed or intended for the … procuring of abortion.” Expert: Thomas Jipping <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGJ_kWyI1Zfgs4RNdaApmiEDZ6qgqHZhDX1C0YZundH-b8M0nA2t35IInMxB6mxG2vq0G-jqzI=>

-

Subject: LA Times Asks: 'What's the Matter With Portland?' Answer: Leftist Ideology.
Body:
* ARTICLES *


** LA Times Asks: 'What's the Matter With Portland?' Answer: Leftist Ideology.
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/19/la-times-asks-whats-matter-with-portland-answer-leftist-ideology/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

 The troubles that the riots of 2020 unleashed are now becoming entrenched and worsened. The ideology of Portland’s leadership and plenty of its residents makes it nearly impossible to fix things. 

=======================================


** Presidents Day Reflections on George Washington’s American Character
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/20/presidents-day-reflections-on-george-washingtons-american-character/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Today, we should come to praise the man who could have been Caesar, in hopes that his deeds will never be buried, but remain first in the hearts of his posterity.

=======================================


** Foundation That Denied Grants to Organizations Because They Had White CEOs Changes Tune After Daily Signal Report
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/17/food-equity-grant-drops-ceo-racial-quota-daily-signal-report/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Under the original rules, some organizations that employ a majority-nonwhite staff and have a majority-nonwhite board of directors were disqualified from the grant because the CEOs are considered white....

=======================================


** ‘Page Not Found’: Teachers Union Won’t Explain Why It Discarded Presidents Day Curriculum 
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/17/page-not-found-teachers-union-wont-explain-why-it-discarded-presidents-day-curriculum/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

The National Education Association removed its resources on Presidents Day from its websites in 2020, according to a Daily Signal review of the Internet Archive’s Wayback Machine. 

=======================================


** Another Study Refutes Left’s False Claims Against Voter ID and Secure Elections
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/10/another-study-refutes-lefts-false-claims-against-voter-id-and-secure-elections/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Trust the science, we’ve all been told. Well, the science has spoken again: Voter ID laws aren’t discriminatory and don’t suppress anyone’s vote.

=======================================


** ICYMI: Americans Die When Merit No Longer Matters
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/16/destroying-meritocracy-is-deadly/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

A recent epidemic of airline near misses deserves both attention and reflection.

Subject: Coming a long way
Body:
Fellow Conservative,

The Left controls the Presidency and half the legislature, and they’re bound and determined to erase our hard-fought gains while ramming through their disastrous agenda. That’s why The Heritage Foundation’s strategy is more relevant than ever.

Through the support of patriotic Americans like you, we’re combining the intellectual power of the best and brightest experts in the nation to research and develop policies that center on our shared conservative values, giving conservative lawmakers the support they will desperately need.

In fact, we’re the go-to resource of conservative lawmakers in Washington. We were also recently ranked as the “#1 think tank for policy impact” in America by the University of Pennsylvania for the third year in a row!

Thank you for standing with us, Fellow Conservative. 

Again, if you have 
any questions please don’t hesitate to reach out.

Best,

Alexander HyattMembership Programs

Subject: The ‘Great Awokening’ Is Transforming Science and Medicine
Body:
* ARTICLES *


** The ‘Great Awokening’ Is Transforming Science and Medicine
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/21/the-great-awokening-is-transforming-science-and-medicine/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

One of the most disturbing and illuminating aspects of today’s cultural revolution is how much it is transforming science and medicine.

=======================================


** ‘Election Fraud … Does Happen,’ Florida Official Says as His Office Charges More Than 20 People With Election Crimes
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/21/election-integrity-major-priority-florida-secretary-state-says/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis established the Office of Election Crimes and Security in August 2022, and since that time 20 people have been charged with election-related crimes.

=======================================


** EXCLUSIVE: Democratic Co-Chair Defends Religious Freedom Summit From SPLC ‘Hate Group’ Attack
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/21/exclusive-democratic-co-chair-defends-religious-freedom-summit-splc-hate-group-attack/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

The Southern Poverty Law Center attacked the summit for providing “a platform for multiple anti-LGBTQ+ hate groups and personalities who cloak their hate in religious rhetoric.”

=======================================


** Supreme Court to Decide Future of Section 230 Protection for Social Media Platforms
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/22/supreme-court-to-decide-future-of-section-230-protection-for-social-media-platforms/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Social media companies might have to make significant changes to their platforms, depending on the outcomes of two Supreme Court cases.

=======================================


** Debunking Biden’s Malarkey: 7 Ways He Added $6 Trillion to Deficits
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/16/debunking-bidens-malarkey-7-ways-he-added-6-trillion-to-deficits/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Deficits through 2031 are on pace to total a staggering $6 trillion more than when the Biden administration began, or about $46,000 for every household in the country.

=======================================


** America’s Pop Culture Is Stagnating. Here’s Why That’s a Problem.
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/16/americas-pop-culture-is-stagnating-heres-why-thats-a-problem/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

In 1981, a mere 16% of the most popular movies in the country were sequels, spinoffs, or remakes of other films. In 2019, that number shot up to 80%.

=======================================


** ‘The Church Cannot Remain Silent’: US Catholic Bishops Receive Instructions on When to Deny Communion to Pro-Abortion Politicians
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/21/41000-catholic-clergy-members-mailed-instructions-denying-communion-pro-abortion-catholic-politicians/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Tens of thousands of clergy members will soon receive a copy of Cardinal Raymond Burke’s instructions to Catholic priests and bishops on when to deny someone Holy Communion.

=======================================


** ICYMI: Rogue Censorship Regime Tries to Shut Down Conservative News Sites Using 'Disinformation' Label
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/21/facts-contradicting-left-wing-narratives-increasingly-labeled-disinformation-rogue-censorship-regime/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

There’s a movement brewing to shut down conservative websites that offer views and information contradicting left-wing orthodoxy.

=======================================

Subject: Heritage Take: Russia’s New START Breach Means U.S. Nuclear Weapons Modernization Is a Must
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

                                                     
Russia’s New START Breach Means U.S. Nuclear Weapons Modernization Is a Must <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1OwAdGoZKyQVKQhXhnmTCJ68Myrm5W378up0IeY7KFwWczr9yW_U55Hn4VYApTgvMqM=> - “Putin’s announcement that Russia is suspending its participation in the flawed New START arms control deal confirms the reality that Russia is uninterested in being a faithful party to international arms agreements. Which is why the US should refuse any concessions to Russia, especially in Ukraine, in response to this violation. Instead, the U.S. must focus on strengthening its nuclear deterrent and accelerating efforts to deal with the PRC’s nuclear breakout,” said Geller. Heritage Expert: Patty-Jane Geller <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1PSisk5zztDqUqlqMaUUSuOS3gLlwEVfeNGVndjK47hZAaAK0OZrKfWOigoIBjc3F3M=> 
Giving School Names That Sound Like Herbal Teas and Day Spas—Rather Than Like Abraham Lincoln <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1b8tebA7eG9FGC7AhbncICuL5urp-c6RAUfPumnrvRkJynxlmpmcXhojxontKck9orw=> - Patriotic school names may be an important tool for fostering patriotism among current and future generations. Patriotic figures can also serve as models of civic virtue. While Americans, in general, have not abandoned patriotism, school boards have become much more reluctant to give schools traditional patriotic names. School boards may have more closely resembled the patriotic preferences of the communities they serve in the past than they do today. This Backgrounder explores current trends in school names and considers what these decisions indicate about the values and priorities of the American public education system. Heritage Experts: Jay Green <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1RV3I_7YN4bbsVoSYI9j0ETk3iHKUivY49vlmXKjnAq1plhlquzDW9tdYB8P4bEdVHE=>
School choice would benefit rural students in Wyoming <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1O1DGbzCJcnHYGdMYEmgEyIppPcymVGMap1G3oEpl3N7ki6FdAaX-M2-2e_cD-KAm2A=> - In her response to President Biden's State of the Union address, Gov. Sarah Huckabee Sanders declared that she would soon unveil "the most far-reaching, bold, conservative education reform in the country." The next day, Sanders announced her "Arkansas LEARNS" initiative, intended to "educate, not indoctrinate our kids, and put students on a path to success." Heritage Expert: Jason Bedrick <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1PJ4AkLvOoyzVHWdinW7bOpvnKfHIQlAkzk1sFZI6t3AFQPFp_Q8wkQMx0F6BdYW_30=>
Respecting Constitution requires acknowledging death of 1972 ERA <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1PQHXNsARdqNn7LeubxePF2zmTcXKnI5d-YU96NSPGiunRhIKe39nUdVuzMMp6fU0rw=> - The current claim that the ERA was only “mostly dead” all those years balances on an exceptionally slim reed. The argument is that the ratification deadline in House Joint Resolution 208, which Congress passed in March 1972, appears not in the text of the proposed ERA but a few inches up the page in the resolutions’ introductory clause. Yup, that’s it. Here’s one of many problems with this weak argument. Article V of the Constitution gives Congress two powers related to constitutional amendments. The Supreme Court has held that Congress’ power to propose constitutional amendments includes the power to set ratification deadlines. Article V also gives Congress the power to dictate whether ratification must be made “by the Legislatures of three fourths of the several States, or by Conventions in three fourths thereof.” Heritage Expert: Thomas Jipping <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1IOBaYlFbj6r7SpZyp0Qt0gHFCP2Xb2l1HE0lhSJ1eJrd-t6zIxv6Zfd2vufLHN3Atw=>
The FBI’s Targeting of “Radical-Traditional Catholics’ Bodes Ill <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1BB9eYUSq7YtaXCw5v2okRTvRwd2MiM8U91QuMmXf8f1bBnsvT2B9pea-lWRn7-sPVY=> - The Federal Bureau of Investigation publicly rescinded <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1apkuQW5IoU_aTtVmcu5BcUxz7_tOn8zrQ544Tk2Z7TMWq17f5YzH63kuvWYrHrZ1bc=> an internal memo on "radical-traditionalist Catholic ideology" the day after a whistleblower had published it. The memo suggests that the FBI <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1fTSh_HAHJm_BbeDNIn91COR-uYaJYMzqCKY4cng50ZqrZBnNSoTeuyIIWFkLjeTb0g=> should monitor these Catholics through "the development of sources with access," including in "places of worship." It presents a list of "hate groups" published by the SPLC as a place to start this work. Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKGAWA1DVZaxlnvvxm9ZBkEioKkYQOlsLl1I8H449lk_ICK7HNcvX1dZgqOeQDIv-4dLjdFsw=>

-

Subject: Heritage Take: Think you left a smothering tax climate behind when you moved? Think again
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

                                                     

 
Think you left a smothering tax climate behind when you moved? Think again <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-xoNGM3nfWm--B2kgAR-gT2z9K8dMX0vOUDGGLBFcbggIYeXEHsdwvUkX9tJhg-1HOw=> - Teacher unions have never been known to stay in their lane. Conflict in the Middle East <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-jZliFajJGrjLx_w6dM6AMJ6OzoWOMxnoXjJQ8DEIVrjoNZ3AG421_mJ5YjgmwsuhSg=>, so-called “climate change,” <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-43bEpuq2KreChHyCaIgL6UN8XM-9RMlxqUOx2tjEkAe1l-j5kIvBuRYYXI1K8H6Rn4=> and abortion <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-_VZ6V_-YkgzL3rMjouQgTowjLqSf4fMIOtIvgkB7TSVs7yqYsdJUlTsO0F9evT6eGU=> are just a few of the policies outside education on which the American Federation of Teachers and their locals <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-y22Y8OQWyzwIXma2Vqj0Ctcyw0g_TrEDm7agh1jUcRjLKqfH1rrWq5ytrIwM607cRs=> take a position. No surprise, then, that an AFT campaign has been resurrected by activists to try to steer state lawmakers on tax policy. But what they get may be the opposite of what they intended. Heritage Expert: Jonathan Butcher <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-361hmsGP3l859B9fgeAcvHkq4laNrgXAxBslMeCkf5kV_lh0GktXyrE4ubZKkBfmh0=> and Preston Brashers <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-9yUROnjWWapwIhQcGuiIFMTDbL6OY3-_luvHENcOPKKt_mRl6EPhUA7EGPFDa0N3kI=>
Respecting Constitution requires acknowledging death of 1972 ERA <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-xPrh7Xt6trm8QEYk2MKwfFIw5YOZuFhb5Hnemhu8od4jl7zh_Z9bSZN996Jifx_4Sk=> - Was Michigan Democratic Rep. Martha Griffiths, the 1972 ERA’s own sponsor, wrong when she agreed to add a binding seven-year deadline to gain further support? Was Rep. Elizabeth Holtzman, New York Democrat, wrong to introduce the deadline extension resolution because the original deadline was binding? Were the U.S. District Court, acting solicitor general, and Congressional Research Service all wrong that the 35 ratifying states fell short when the deadlines passed? Virginia Deputy Attorney General Walter S. Felton Jr. said in 1994 that “the ERA was not currently before the states for ratification because its original and extended time limits had expired.” Even National Public Radio has reported that the 1972 ERA “fell short and expired in 1982.” Were they all wrong? No. What did they all miss? Nothing. Heritage Expert: Thomas Jipping <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-0nBp8k6AWwrgbTWtRvTXCzeC81jUECymMqRDcBqMpBlWzilUPdOL0MyawaUONJepC8=>
China’s Xi Jinping Plans Russia Visit as Putin Wages War in Ukraine <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-_DAkjDdBPyYKFoCH7zWjBU_oLU81CTFZjluCHU7Eii7Uy16RDrSX2G3E1h7vnSn8hc=> - Chinese leader Xi Jinping is preparing to visit Moscow for a summit with Russia’s president in the coming months, according to people familiar with the plan, 
as Vladimir Putin <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-rE_o56S8eox-K1eTM4MZf7heMTqWNHWAgog4g-wKArmy5M3EBgVreXG9TZyDM9Ddpw=> wages war in Ukraine <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-_cQwXEUL5cXBDbTlflv3AWTbbfPU4XbguL4HuAHLxde4bra4JZnMyRunBkPrj1u0FA=> and portrays himself as a standard-bearer 
against a U.S.-led global order. Beijing says it wants to play a more active role aimed at ending the conflict, and the people familiar with Mr. Xi’s trip plans said a meeting with Mr. Putin would be part of a push for multiparty peace talks and allow China to reiterate its calls that nuclear weapons <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-wbJMf2RSWiGXmIpblYSW2OkNNuTb56uw7kB9KgJvbs_v6bj83Ye6MGJYNLMUTwGlRA=> not be used. Heritage Expert: Brent Sadler <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-0mY2cgiO_ngWAG-1rTj27DuIzVOQ12HvkJYwp1n3AVudgXpShfYNgyzzchp4YHQUHs=> and Michael Cunningham <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-6jHMLRW_DGu3_NONeA4CJ8XzhEHGI1nL6Xv2Uila-uau1rf5ctHBCI9DZLdoP3ujto=> 
‘Imperative’ – Chip Roy Calls On GOP To Move Forward On Bill Cracking Down On Illegal Immigration <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc--I-sNMj6GTKwt01-aUXoGmiMQAPXLRvwXvpHsAqIFV1sl7ZujFrXTX4kzlmIUPGcmM=> - The Daily Caller obtained the letter Roy sent to the caucus, which focuses on, H.R. 29, the Border Safety and Security Act. Roy also explains the legislation, which he introduced, and the importance of passing it. H.R. 29 would require the Secretary of Homeland Security (DHS) to turn away migrants seeking asylum or else detain them until their claims have been adjudicated. “As we consider important border security legislation, there has been a great deal of confusion about both the goal and the substance of a number of proposals that are central to our efforts to find solutions to the border crisis harming Americans, migrants, and our national security,” Roy wrote in the letter. “Specifically, there has been much debate – both internally and externally – about H.R. 29, the Border Safety and Security Act, as well as questions surrounding overall efforts to secure our southern border.” Heritage Expert: Jim Carafano <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-0jzejE7_Zu-2sZrLaUyPp2izgp64C5nXccGJWHI3KNzmvBQXR8PXWzeaM6E9DTiAf4=>
Russia’s New START Breach Means U.S. Nuclear Weapons Modernization Is a Must <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-2JRcGew4lZ4a50q4aMIqsBzdd3K5oXDPkY4KyqfT4g89PDT2eYKFYcX6ElUfcnMYOI=> - “Putin’s announcement that Russia is suspending its participation in the flawed New START arms control deal confirms the reality that Russia is uninterested in being a faithful party to international arms agreements. Which is why the US should refuse any concessions to Russia, especially in Ukraine, in response to this violation. Instead, the U.S. must focus on strengthening its nuclear deterrent and accelerating efforts to deal with the PRC’s nuclear breakout,” said Geller. Heritage Expert: Patty-Jane Geller <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-52dyxjnPu_QSQ4srZVLJi2MJAer2Lk8dIKRXbKCEUvCIDHvBX1nyWbgxD1xOZ9HoSU=>
Ohio’s New Voting Law Balance Secure Elections With Ballot Access <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-2G3m1WGHLoeHJZ0kldXzIkww57PDAR_gmYfXRRd8LaZ7T3hF9cV_SQZ5F9gwDpX9Jo=> - To understand how Ohio improved, let’s look into some of the new law’s particulars. Central to the reform was a focus on photo IDs.  All Ohio voters casting their ballots in person must now provide a government-issued photo ID at their polling place. That enables poll workers to authenticate the identity of each person and ensure that only eligible voters are casting ballots. Of course, many voters no longer show up on Election Day, preferring instead to vote by mail. Now, mail-in voting will be subject to the same voter-verification standards as in-person voting. Applicants for an absentee ballot must include a copy of their government-issued photo identification with their application to receive a mail-in ballot, along with other unique identifying information, such as the last four digits of the voter’s Social Security number. Heritage Expert: Jack Fitzhenry <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-8a6MowfeapdJvk9DF4uMuzlInasfniGTzCSaXMkQhmMYmpkkdaes945eueZzZ3yaHQ=> 

DOJ Forced to Reveal Secret Communications on Georgia Elections With Groups on Left - In June 2021, the U.S. Justice Department announced a lawsuit <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-_8XF7fZ--GemczbbFkKN8Wb2BQPjC-7w6OuaouvcAcsQwi-_JGkGKZ6zMC8st7AvZw=> to overturn parts of Georgia’s law, claiming it violated the 1965 Voting Rights Act.  President Joe Biden and other Democrats falsely labeled the law “Jim Crow 2.0 <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-74K2nVazEryF0xAHFvhM4kMoZZun3mt4pNOVkW27ko3um6hZYOr58qwH0evrWaVzVg=>,” a reference to the era of racist laws and segregation in southern states that suggested an official effort to prevent blacks from voting.  In response to the Justice Department’s lawsuit against Georgia, Raffensperger requested any communications that may have influenced its decision to 
challenge his state’s law. After the department refused to comply with a request under the Freedom of Information Act, Raffensperger’s office sued. Heritage Expert: Fred Lucas <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKHSvc-yYFNaiVLHfvNCXDty3XxwIA3C8S_4HG5KlHwhkzq1UMcFJaNlEJV0cFrJKs6dlQLBQ=>

* ARTICLES *


** Library Features Clarence Thomas Books After Daily Signal Inquiry
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/23/clarence-thomas-gets-prominent-placement-from-his-local-library-after-initial-snub/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Virginia’s largest public library revamped its Black History Month reading list to include three Clarence Thomas books after an inquiry from The Daily Signal.

Subject: Library Features Clarence Thomas Book After Daily Signal Inquiry
Body:
* ARTICLES *


** Ohio Train Disaster Exposes Hollowness, Incompetence of Identity-Obsessed Ruling Class
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/24/ohio-train-disaster-exposes-hollowness-incompetence-of-identity-obsessed-ruling-class/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Biden didn’t show up in East Palestine, nor did his administration or the media seem to pay much attention to the derailment of a train carrying toxic chemicals. And then Trump arrived.

=======================================


** EXCLUSIVE: Mike Pence’s Advancing American Freedom Demands Answers on FBI Targeting ‘Radical-Traditional Catholics’
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/24/exclusive-mike-pences-advancing-american-freedom-demands-answers-fbi-targeting-radical-traditional-catholics/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

“This leaked document targeting traditional Catholics is disturbing to all people of faith,” the Pence group’s general counsel, J. Marc Wheat, tells The Daily Signal.

=======================================


** EXCLUSIVE: This Bill Would Eliminate Biden’s $27B Green ‘Slush Fund’
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/24/exclusive-this-bill-would-eliminate-bidens-27b-green-slush-fund/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

House Republicans want to roll back a $27 billion “green bank,” a grant program in the massive spending bill dubbed the Inflation Reduction Act.

=======================================


** Colorado School District Revises Transgender Student Policy in Face of Parent Opposition
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/24/colorado-school-district-revises-transgender-student-policy-face-parent-opposition/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

The new policy does not require teachers to explicitly relay a student’s gender identity to parents, and it makes “trans-identifying” male access to girls’ restrooms the norm, not the exception.

=======================================


** Biden’s Misleading New Asylum Rule Is a Gimmick Atop a Shell Game
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/24/bidens-misleading-new-asylum-rule-is-a-gimmick-atop-a-shell-game/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

The Biden administration proposes a rule to avoid more bad optics. The Left is wrong to attack it and the Right is wrong to praise it.

=======================================


** Which Does Secretary of State Blinken Think Is Worse: Chinese Uyghur Genocide or Spy Balloon?
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/08/which-does-secretary-of-state-blinken-think-is-worse-chinese-uyghur-genocide-or-spy-balloon/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

His administration made cosmetic changes after the Chinese spy balloon incident, but will Biden do anything about America’s massive and mounting trade deficit?

=======================================


** ICYMI: Clarence Thomas Book Gets Prominent Placement From His Local Library After Initial Snub
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/02/23/clarence-thomas-gets-prominent-placement-from-his-local-library-after-initial-snub/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Virginia’s largest public library revamped its Black History Month reading list to include three Clarence Thomas books after an inquiry from The Daily Signal.

Subject: Heritage Take: Senate Judiciary Committee to Ponder Congress’s Non-Existent Power to Revive Long-Dead ERA
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

                                                     


Senate Judiciary Committee to Ponder Congress’s Non-Existent Power to Revive Long-Dead ERA <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVvIAOBmiZ-ucb4VkjaCTSxL2cyzckTrhbGi1OVSDjttYhjcPs6PrsV78_LlEtnYCifE=> - The Senate Judiciary Committee will hold an unusual hearing on February 28 titled, 
“The Equal Rights Amendment: How Congress Can Recognize Ratification and Enshrine Equality in Our Constitution.” It’s unusual because it focuses on a power that Congress doesn’t possess and a proposed amendment that doesn’t exist. Heritage Expert: Tom Jipping <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVrw_XptuEikZ305ugUvbuGmbuWpYhVFOuzBKojDxHfqxWpMkRVT-b2jOM4gsw2Za_ko=>and Emma Waters <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVgM3vZDzuvx9kIDbimhwhxW1RKtAtPeUMuK0_H4XAPTyLXJT671uIO92RV-UB91WAoI=>
Index of Economic Freedom Reveals ‘How Fragile the World’s Economy Has Become,’ Even as Taiwan Rises <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVqdb4DiCBPUn4SyrcTP8ZtT-YAbEdOX5aQBe4NBG9koMi8GWJKS-uvFDxAL6ImbfVEo=> - Taiwan’s economic freedom ranking has risen to an all-time high, 
according to The Heritage Foundation’s 2023 Index of Economic Freedom <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVg39wJQsqvr_oZlJc_EcBzoepMiICbvJcqbBRA4-v-AXCv2Rbxzhs7zyK-LETeGn5Mc=> released on Monday. The index ranks Taiwan No. 4 <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVkdRzdHumPCXYCu4882X8me25gTkw9SlaXQjhM7pfN-ceqNhJ9oeXSOVwJgkwFjQOpM=> with an overall economic freedom score of 80.7 and No. 2 out of the 39 economies in the Asia-Pacific region. The region’s average overall economic score is 58.2 while the world’s average is 59.3, or “the lowest it has been over the past two decades,” according to the index’s executive summary. Heritage Expert: Samantha Aschieris  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVnq85KRbWcmLg16YmSZlq8f0Z9GZeOq04uqbVx29tqu4R4e8TyFCCFpPArFpevSGtwE=> 
 
Biden’s Student Loan “Forgiveness” Plan Is a Raw Deal for Taxpayers <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuV-wunCVXKVOO6InSrd_WR75TVWMrQQeOz-ewvikeIMZF7Q3NddXrVelvSV5tqDrCVrQ=> - Biden’s student loan debt cancellation plan is an abuse of power and a costly one, which must be stopped. This program punishes Americans who decided not to go to college or who responsibly paid off their student loans—forcing them to take on the debt of others who willingly took out loans. Biden’s student debt cancellation is based entirely on a 20-year-old statute (the HEROES Act) that has never been used to forgive any student debt and nowhere mentions a unilateral executive 
power to cancel debt. A strong decision from the Supreme Court holding that the Constitution gives the power of the purse to the legislature alone might stop presidents from treating the federal budget like a slush fund. Canceling student loan debt overwhelmingly benefits the wealthiest Americans at the expense of the poor and working class. More than half (56%) of student loan debt is held by households whose borrowers earned graduate degrees. Canceling these loans will make college more expensive, as schools hike tuition because future loan cancellations are factored into students’ financial decisions. Biden’s irresponsible policy will exacerbate costs without improving the value of degrees. American workers, who make this country great, largely reject these radical bailouts that reward woke universities, and they will make their voices heard. Heritage Expert: Jack Fitzhenry <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVqoWsRp02UAEjaHLPKuAwiKfNHQOdHTbfSGH_vVnoNw1_W7kxhhOcFfhuPdaY6iJArc=>, GianCarlo Canaparo <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVv1ZST5axuF_4NhkO-vGAqcA2JQ1MrjYpO1J3l9otHpRm1KXtnmWZyDvOPdOdaIWj_A=>, Adam 
Kissel  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVhEoCbAPBXXc1vOvm8LkWE8nGjXyYao2le6ilSxgiIp03sfHjZUcWuyLu6zDIgxnKzE=>
 
Earmark Spending: Bad Fruit from Rotten Trees <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVleSZy-__ntwXBW1wvEFsEcyt5OndsvZSAU8Dv6MG41lXlHRjwXyAUBDwm7hXlQr-w4=> - The return of earmarks to appropriations legislation, following a decade-long absence, is part of a troubling trend of fiscal irresponsibility in 
Washington. Earmarks are used almost exclusively on local projects that have no connection to true federal responsibilities. An increase in transparency does not meaningfully change the inherently corrupt nature of earmarks. Congress should reinstate the earmark ban and reduce or eliminate spending on the programs and bureaus that are subject to the most earmarking. Heritage Expert: David Ditch <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVn5VOCDkxWb7NmmOOpTWpOL0uqyeSMG4OK_-j153Ht3U-MKeTn4_IRhh5-LbSnvjptU=>
 
Why the U.S. Should Oppose the New Draft WHO Pandemic Treaty <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuV9NO0JK4F695ON8XhVGhKK7XB_2r7Zt155TZq54ILBviFJNaLYD9y88SImUakeMn_QE=> - The World Health Organization’s (WHO’s) “zero draft” of a new agreement on pandemic prevention, preparedness, and response, called WHO CA+, is significantly flawed. Even though the WHO failed miserably in preventing the spread of COVID-19, the WHO CA+ draft would dramatically expand WHO authority to declare a pandemic and, thereby, trigger provisions in the treaty that would re-allocate resources and encourage governments to waive intellectual property rights. If the U.S. joined the treaty, it would be required to increase its domestic funding by “allocating in its annual budgets not lower than 5% of its current health expenditure to pandemic prevention,” resulting in the annual expenditure of tens, if not hundreds, of billions of dollars on treaty compliance. Heritage Expert: Brett D. Schaefer <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVtEVUvvpMVc5e_ACrij92C7SEg2n9udcqrMOtLBXKHSx8EGVqdPQjUrCsKL-a11s4T4=> and Steven Groves <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVtyfTf9Up3T72DJxHgvu2vzTt8E2S3WvvLuW485ZXACCPwWyUgR1IVpQBl4Y5C7Q0PI=>
 
Bad Research Mars Legal Briefs at Supreme Court, as 2 Racial Admissions Cases Show <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVrorjZO5N5OtMzDLWsc4pF1njx-HSl0JfNwushmb2pdz36EA2pp2DZqDyI6RvRwN0U4=>- In the two cases challenging the race-based admissions practices of Harvard College and the University of North Carolina, 
more than a dozen briefs cite “The Shape of the River,” a 1998 book by William Bowen and Derek Bok, to support such race-based admissions. That research, however, largely has been discredited. The authors of the briefs citing it either haven’t done their research or think they can pull a fast one on the Supreme Court as the justices consider the two cases, Students for Fair Admissions v. President and Fellows of Harvard College and Students for Fair Admissions v. University of North Carolina. Heritage Expert: GianCarlo Canaparo <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVrorjZO5N5OtMzDLWsc4pF1njx-HSl0JfNwushmb2pdz36EA2pp2DZqDyI6RvRwN0U4=>
Biden’s Misleading New Asylum Rule Is a Gimmick Atop a Shell Game <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVghFYhlLJ5bJiUM0h-BW9sSXW0qsdbjT26SCus8HXtGwAlBErQ1iUff64Uo69BlTwZo=> - The Left is wrong to complain about the rule, and the Right is wrong to praise it. President Joe Biden may be happy with those reactions as he prepares to announce his reelection campaign, but for everyone else, some explanation is sorely needed about the compounded mess his administration is creating. For two years, the Biden administration has denied <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVohTST5jXSnCYK_Ti2fhMdz20UoW6dvxh7_eAtXxXZ3InrDwWAwo93wKN0b7nJtiZS4=> there was a border crisis <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVhNxQnoPsrm_K2T6ZwfkI85Tzy1SsT5K4y253XNOS0gnbk-Kg-BdQRNkBNyFyj8ecBE=> despite monthly record numbers of illegal alien crossings at our southern border. However, when the December numbers hit yet another new high of nearly 252,000 encounters <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVh4ZiPWP9zEjyqXy4mVwwAsl8X3hDQtAwLxASi1SN-yCAjVWbbSXydg_7r7oQBqxVc4=> just between the ports of entry on the southern border, the administration tried a new tactic. Heritage Expert: Lora Ries <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuV7qIFiafwnUI3kKsQY0l5ehL-g8mGmDE21eNAOohMev1SEiF4oT9A02xyq6rlqYMAKM=> 
On the debt limit fight, it’s time to end business as usual <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVif851oePX2v1URIj2Qk890fzqzuXEnlp9PRHuPlzZoGsRh_L1FaUFkGu6wt1xXlcZE=> - President Joe Biden has called for an increase in the debt ceiling. But Biden does not simply want a higher debt limit. He wants it to be “suspended,” unaccompanied by reforms. Congress should reject Biden’s bid and instead use the debt limit to strengthen the economy. Heritage Expert: Paul Winfree <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKNuuuVqju8ZqPHXnrwFukmnY-gsdGKY1rOuC0yhJEeOSQA-T9eTs45ec8rRJ7Tx5oxZ3rDaA=>

-

Subject: YOU'RE INVITED: Edwin Meese III Originalism Lecture (Mar. 21)
Body:
Edwin Meese III Originalism Lecture
Tuesday, March 21, 2023
Reception: 5:30 - 6:30 p.m. ET
Program: 6:30 - 7:30 p.m. ET
The Heritage Foundation 214 Massachusetts Avenue, NE Washington, DC 20002
REGISTER >> <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKN2epKnNVjhfIL2GCCF-cAiGsNo6KXVf5uA2Gsm_0jiwCnuzXYkMOeW6J-UcUYRFWkc9O0eU=>
Featuring
Kurt Lash
E. Claiborne Robins Distinguished Chair in Law at the University of Richmond School of Law
Hosted by
John Malcolm
Vice President, Institute for Constitutional Government,
The Heritage Foundation
The Heritage Foundation is honored to announce that Professor Kurt Lash, the E. Claiborne Robins Distinguished Chair in Law at the University of Richmond School of Law, will deliver this year's Edwin Meese III Originalism Lecture for his speech titled, “Originalism and Fixing the Fourteenth Amendment.” 

 This annual lecture seeks to honor former Attorney General Ed Meese’s legacy of advancing an understanding and jurisprudence of originalism. When the Framers wrote the Constitution, “Their intention was to write a document not just for their times but for posterity,” Meese said in a 1985 speech to the D.C. Chapter of the Federalist Society Lawyers Division. Meese reiterated the theme of Original Intention in several speeches, warning of the danger of “seeing the Constitution as an empty vessel into which each generation may pour its passion and prejudice.” The Great Debate that he launched over three decades ago placed the idea of judicial originalism at the center of American jurisprudence and fundamentally altered the constitutional 
landscape of this nation. 

 Today, originalism is no longer a novel concept; instead, it is now widely embraced in legal circles, including academia and the judiciary. Building on the work of Ed Meese, this lecture aims to continue the conversation he started and examine new trends and themes in originalist thought today. Please join us for our second annual lecture. 

 Professor Kurt Lash: Professor Lash is the E. Claiborne Robins Distinguished Professor of Law at the University of Richmond where he teaches and writes about constitutional law. He is also the founder and director of the Richmond Program on the American Constitution. He has published numerous works on the subjects of constitutional history, theory, and law, including The Fourteenth Amendment and the Privileges or Immunities of American Citizenship (Cambridge University Press, 2014), The Lost History of the Ninth Amendment (Oxford University Press, 2009), and The American First Amendment in the Twenty-first Century: Cases and 
Materials (with William W. Van Alstyne) (5th ed., Foundation Press). In 2021, University of Chicago Press published Professor Lash’s two-volume collection of original documents relating to the framing and ratification of the Thirteenth, Fourteenth, and Fifteenth Amendments. Titled The Reconstruction Amendments: Essential Documents, the collection is the first of its kind. He is currently working on A Troubled Birth of Freedom: The Struggle to Amend the Constitution in the Aftermath of the Civil War (forthcoming, Yale University Press).
SHARE >> <[[http://click.heritage.org/v/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKN2epKoBSc6rfKJg8QCvzOqQ1PkCxhcQkaZzC0N7kQ7NFECHnMhl-fLBBUVGOrNfSHqXjhks=]]>
