Subject: Heritage Take: Senate Panel Turns to Defunct Constitutional Amendment Phyllis Schlafly Helped Defeat 40 Years Ago
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

                                                     


Senate Panel Turns to Defunct Constitutional Amendment Phyllis Schlafly Helped Defeat 40 
Years Ago - <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCnSa5R8Xq-lTeDhzK3i_PVQWyv7CpHzCZKCWK9poPCmreFwt-wd5TEKvX-IrFGFVcyE=> The Equal Rights Amendment has been a topic of debate in the halls of Congress <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC8THpYvoNTfBKhucx7KxMNcAXYcMNDOyX66nAawyekTMmtUwhF1f4DcF_hzPEVJLs2M=> on and off for 50 years. On Tuesday, the controversial amendment will again be up for debate during a Senate committee hearing.  Despite the deadline for ratification having expired—depending on who you ask—in either 1979 or 1982, the Senate Judiciary Committee <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCx5Oa0iAzjM207qPoPT16C8TNNcJO4dpftfGEnCsoAc4p-KTFR1XQgA0QifUOvewCDI=> is set to hold a hearing to consider removing the ratification expiration date on the ERA altogether. The Equal Rights Amendment <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC4Yc6j67aBgxKRaND__BF44Tjn0IIfAG7ZpxvJovzUDXlJxAKJGZBx4d8OYF05_474Q=>, or the ERA, would guarantee that “Equality of rights under the law shall not be denied or abridged by the United States or by any State on account of sex.” But, now as then, opponents of the 
amendment argue it would harm women’s rights by removing all distinctions between men and women. Heritage Experts: Tom Jipping <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC5_XE1IjtJWREkadgh-tvKk2euFuh-HJBxrsGgjWwmUrjHc1V9tQx1S_eukoBCW1EZg=> and Emma Waters <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCn0Rvq0TCgNdx1F5EFd2XhwpyC6-kqZLov-b-y8mlV42KYm2XKX9i6oTTIdJnjxzNLo=>
 
Biden’s Misleading New Asylum Rule Is a Gimmick Atop a Shell Game <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCo91kQAdj092f1S4vYR2Wd_9pS-9mFbd2_MEj9AYqos_3TRRkFlIzwkhUnNIPbZ1XfI=> - Now, in anticipation <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCkd22XhJ6UdKuHW8-QxPgH12Py7PJr0R2sZsESQU1BLQG-dP6HaVv6YJNOdFnob0WpY=> of even higher numbers of illegal alien encounters with the coming termination <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC-ZCPIWXx-tozKc84gAIiacSdua528qQ9-1FznTSRWHHH9Tw84DmoWa82HerpeMdoFc=> of the Title 42 public health authority used to expel migrants during the COVID-19 pandemic, the departments of  Homeland Security and Justice have proposed a joint rule to avoid more bad optics. In it, the departments “encourage” illegal aliens to “avail themselves of [the] lawful, safe, and orderly pathways” the Biden administration created, or “seek asylum or other protection in countries through which they travel.” Heritage Expert: Lora Ries <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC89JpgvRWz1q1VVCTbT4Q3BpNHIdWRiUHRy-1sQKvoPruxMRYdwwJV5RZQ73b-wAad8=>
DHS Flouts Law on Student Visas and D.C. Circuit Judges Yawn <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC3g8IaaCtBkAqMDRihiKeSaZH9yHKZeeR6WKmYr1KDRir9bZyJ3NUzvGaF5CF0RAAV4=> -  The Immigration and Naturalization Act, 8 U.S.C. § 1101 <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCyva2i1yOyNut5uZSZNP1_oqHWF0p9hfax1qFY8S3Q92z0g6xce67QN2ospZLgsZMiY=>, is the law governing student visas <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCgTKRHEkn5-WR8ZMYKhxwx_zKU5_F-b1ILKALWHws-CWfYkweDDdaxqaGDmSrDEg8Ow=> and it’s very specific. It stipulates that the Department of Homeland Security can issue student visas to a “bona fide student qualified to pursue a full course of study” who “seeks to enter the United States temporarily and solely for the purpose of pursuing such a course of study” (emphasis added). Yet despite the clear language of this provision that permits foreign students only to study in the U.S., DHS <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC4Fch1NatSNv8FaujpyJzNquYqr5XGyEwvK3H7rwC62RecFITXE9QneK4J9gTFAvAxg=> promulgated a new regulation <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC6FLRiZE1cO61s9xlOIYAP29HOUIDNsQGDJHbn7FjePfUJaLXXMSX4jHWihdF8RIbBQ=> in 2016. It amended similar, existing regulations first issued in 1992 to allow foreign students to remain and work in the country for up to a year after their studies end.  DHS also allows students in science, technology, or engineering to work while remaining in the U.S. for an additional 24 months. Heritage Experts: Hans von Spakovsky <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC7oUwafxFkj-HohM9zFLCWWsUqfR8ZyCk_5zKW300jdAjNWZZTAo2C3utHd5CxLth9w=> and Cully Stimson <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC87x2qLaKg-b22KB-7yS5n2a4pdUWCYS12lcxHCDg-v0IinrYf6nXhSdOTAhO_4-id0=>
Biden’s Student Loan “Forgiveness” Plan Is a Raw Deal for Taxpayers <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCv5QLlxweQkkvyKL0SY24A9K1SLV--5hE-_C71YonPIWHa41VQcB1Z4W_V7SzQJPqcU=> - Biden’s student loan debt cancellation plan is an abuse of power and a costly one, which must be stopped. This program punishes Americans who decided not to go to college or who responsibly paid off their student loans—forcing them to take on the debt of others who willingly took out loans. Biden’s student debt cancellation is based entirely on a 20-year-old statute (the HEROES Act) that has never been used to forgive any student debt and nowhere mentions a unilateral executive 
power to cancel debt. A strong decision from the Supreme Court holding that the Constitution gives the power of the purse to the legislature alone might stop presidents from treating the federal budget like a slush fund. Canceling student loan debt overwhelmingly benefits the wealthiest Americans at the expense of the poor and working class. More than half (56%) of student loan debt is held by households whose borrowers earned graduate degrees. Canceling these loans will make college more expensive, as schools hike tuition because future loan cancellations are factored into students’ financial decisions. Heritage Experts: Jack Fitzhenry <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCszQ_UvKehYS6urJTpWxq52B9JmlRP_ekSdOS0kdBW9pr4AdTnsVC2rQ2UG4k7wdOwQ=>, GianCarlo Canaparo <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC47qOsIItRuCzNlFgVQKofc_a7oqJeVYELMgAzexEMSO1c7QsbunZMmCq41ukHEV3KU=>, Adam Kissel  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC_ViClUwDpoXVTEc66MAn8CkEvOmoBolxAWDeKrfW7cypWQ4VdTpZv_5dUMW1dQ8Dqw=>
 
Index of Economic Freedom Reveals ‘How Fragile the World’s Economy Has Become,’ Even as Taiwan Rises <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC1af6JNd7xJmmL134SaCF-lm4IQfkq5KLlghwWGIJQb4aDZHeSAddyDGDfuXIUflHUE=> - Taiwan’s economic freedom ranking has risen to an all-time high, according to The Heritage Foundation’s 2023 Index of Economic Freedom <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCxYLYet-0fNvNUQ940RqvOxXS-FdJfuMnCr_dQX3ey0rcCXdJFlueBQ3jYI6no0yiDE=> released on Monday. The index ranks Taiwan No. 4 <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCupj3fwpz5gh67ijtX_x38Hk8IRPsPH45TkEUyqZd9g3KxQAvS7DUoamRfefjF_J01Y=> with an overall economic freedom score of 80.7 and No. 2 out of the 39 economies in the Asia-Pacific region. The region’s average overall economic score is 58.2 while the world’s average is 59.3, or “the lowest it has been over the past two decades,” according to the index’s executive summary. Heritage Expert: Samantha Aschieris  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCxXVXUXzEEiu6czQ2waPZ5fsDj2WcIRX_mziTpQM8vCH7OmMDownX07BGuZYgULLGH8=> 
 
‘Too Important to Screw Up’: Trump USAID Chief Explains Need for Oversight of US Billions for Ukraine  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCzLRuFXKNNBNyPe0ZsuOm7QMkxgoltTjsanUFSD-Ep1X4G3v3RlPoj1m0jV97OSUH6g=>- Aid to Ukraine is an important priority for the United States, and that’s why there must be congressional oversight <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC6Wg68sMEk7-kTG-F-w0n1ifKb89DmaTlkHWmbz8u9xaLBZ4g5x-7qfCi6HNDPTPaoc=> of it, the former chief of international humanitarian assistance during the Trump administration says.  “The response to [Russian President Vladimir] Putin’s invasion of Ukraine <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC1lqrpdc9OAMCdLZl9oTJq5OAjuIJRruAueWYABJxNZDAcTbeHzdI-HDEiV-1skgsCI=>, by USAID and the rest of the U.S. government, is too important to screw up,” John Barsa, who was acting administrator for the U.S. Agency for International Development, told The Daily Signal. But he added, “Nobody or no cause should get a pass” when it comes to scrutiny of how tax dollars are spent. Since the Russian invasion of Ukraine on Feb. 24, 2022, the United States has given $113 billion <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCnmfdsbGnDkUAn3v-Rb96ysA3-eaAjqNLEn8jvjxScebyhI-4IeFkAUZsLyv0BDpzNU=> in humanitarian and military assistance to Ukraine <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCsWPj-emKsRQHMSni079yLpTeIiDvBb3JHHGuX4ej2fQR3NsMvsMe8dhgqS_cffsuCY=>. On Tuesday, the House Armed Services Committee and the House Appropriations subcommittee on defense held separate hearings into how the money is being spent. Heritage Expert: Fred Lucas <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCzhelmhiT4Kp5jWHINohXqVHGHM1dan3lE2EatTP6-buB8M0Vr5e5XUGctyTBsMKjM0=>
 
CDC Refuses to Answer House GOP Questions About Codes to Track Reasons Why Americans Turn Down the COVID-19 Jabs <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCyBNLWndYomLHgw5Kox4Wex4-UCszxwbUpFR0sGICq0iP8JH-ocYkHlj18OjQQwwDn8=> - The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention told The Daily Signal that it “will not be tracking” the reasons Americans give for refusing to take a COVID-19 vaccine <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC8524m6SP6wJ_Ulf0Hy_tN7OikLoiF8v0j95OrccRnzQe9O9JEdwStiek_jyNRincBg=>, after House Republicans demanded answers about a new classification system that tracks the reasons for vaccine refusal. Meanwhile, congressional Republicans told The Daily Signal that the CDC failed to respond to their questions by a deadline last week. “Two weeks ago, we sent a letter to the CDC demanding answers about its new COVID-19 vaccine database,” Rep. Josh Brecheen, R-Okla., told The Daily Signal <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzC7dKkKhMct18peDp-8tliGc9bFWolKFJLB6CHDC78XbotV4_OzfJ0f5gpDmUDtNh6Rg=> in a statement Monday. “The CDC is stonewalling us and refusing to respond. Why won’t the CDC explain why it’s gathering data about Americans’ personal choices? House Republicans are not afraid to use the budgetary process to keep the CDC accountable to the American people,” Brecheen warned. Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKPBHzCpQ8g_b4oYhMJUP8gbkj-eiJ8eUQILznN1F31cjsPMk4iKF6VN-PEAuKoiy9UusTvk4=>

-

Subject: A reflection on Dr. Rev Martin Luther King, Jr.; his life and legacy
From: "Darryl! LC Moch, National Black Caucus Co-Chair" <funcom@gp.org>
Body:
Hello Friend,

As I reflect on this "King Day" and the weekend of service projects, commemorative marches, and also the series of anti-war activities that honor his legacy and where we are in this country and the world on this 54th anniversary of his death it seems that so much has changed but so little has changed.  We are still fighting the issues in many of our communities.  Hate crimes, violence, criminalization of the poor, racism, sexism, and homophobia and even transphobia are on the rise.  The planet is dying, and people are hurting, and there are those who play politics with our lives as if no one really matters. While the rich get richer, and the poor get poorer.



This year also marks the 60th anniversary of the March on Washington where Dr. King delivered the famous "I Have a Dream" speech. But lesser-known speeches about the Vietnam War and war in general, about poverty and equality, would be appropriate now and these messages and warnings from Dr. King would most likely make King the closest to being a Green than many other civil rights leaders of his day.  I am certain that if he were alive, he would "get us" and even fight for us to be present at all the tables where justice was discussed or being fought for.  





Knowing this and living in the shadow of his legacy is what has inspired me.I was born the yearRev.Dr.Kingwas murdered.In many ways, it feels like I was born at the right time to be a living heir to his message. So yes,I am trying to be the dream, to fulfill the dream and to carryonhis legacy that lives in all of us.It is also his legacy that compels me to be Green. To fight fascism, warmongering, Neo-colonialism, hatred, oppression, poverty, and the destruction of our planet.



His legacy compels me above all else to fight for our common humanity, realizing that our progressive movements and communities can only survive and thrive if we build together, to tear down the walls that divide us.As we think about and reflect on the man and the legacy, each of us should figure out where we fit in. And if you are like me, you probably will see that you fit in right here in the Green Party.



So, if you are out there and you see yourself as I do, we need you. We need you to be active in your local areas, in your states, in our caucuses. We need you to be the Green Party every day, in every way.



So, if you are out there and you see yourself as I do, if you can help us build a strong Green Party that stands for people and planet over profit and politics.

 <https://www.gp.org/donate_stripe>

Give us your time. Give us your vote. And give us your support. I am urging you to support the National Green <https://www.gp.org/donate_stripe> Party <https://www.gp.org/donate_stripe>and the National Black Caucus <https://www.gp.org/bc_donate> as we lift up our voices and make the legacy of Dr. Rev. Martin Luther King a reality for our communities and yours.



In solidarity,

Darryl! LC Moch

Co-chair, National Black Caucus 

Chair,DCStatehoodGreenParty



P.S. We need all of our allies across the nation, to stand with us as we fight for DC Statehood; The colony of nearly 700,000 disenfranchised people in the Nation's Capitol of these United States of America with no representation in congress and no autonomy of our own affairs or government. 


The Green Party of the United States
 <http://www.gp.org/> <http://www.gp.org/> <http://www.gp.org/> <http://www.gp.org/>http://www.gp.org/



-=-=-

Subject: Heritage Take: A Pro-Life Agenda for the 118th Congress
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

                                                   
 
A Pro-Life Agenda for the 118th Congress <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJjO6rlgwYMETnj9DLTDLQ7luP5AGUfUD4Ts1kYXpFUGZr8T_nw9lhClxtSUlFL8RU_k=> - In June 2022, the Supreme Court righted a grave wrong when it 
overturned Roe v. Wade and opened the door for policymakers to pass more pro-life measures at the state and federal levels. This opportunity should not be squandered. The 118th Congress has a constitutional duty to protect the most vulnerable and innocent members of the human family. This report provides a road map for Congress to advance pro-life policies in this challenging political setting. Congress should make the case for life to the American people, hold the Biden Administration accountable, and build on the pro-life movement’s momentum, moving America closer to the day when abortion is unthinkable. Heritage Experts: Emma Waters <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJo-PcHxhMlux7L8y5EX6gXG0oyepbBhXX-wqVtbDXNw9UaboeXLw47g8CFTCe8xpXuI=>
 
Conservative Groups Are Building An Army Of Personnel To Take Over The Government <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJryC-ctpf2UYVfOXGgk2zw-Y2rfU_mwRfNIH4DmuL6GkaV3CUKCLVhVpRjkDzBFwHj0=> – Conservative organizations are coming together to develop well-trained personnel and a detailed policy agenda for the next presidential administration. Project 2025, organized by The Heritage Foundation, is bringing together 45 conservative groups to develop policy and personnel for the next administration, Associate director Spencer Chretien said in an editorial for The American Conservative. “For decades, as the left has continued its march through America’s institutions, conservatives have been outgunned and outmatched when it comes to the art of government,” Chretien writes. “More and more of our politicians are willing to use the government to achieve our vision, because the neutrality of ‘keeping the government out of it’ will lose every time to the left’s vast power.” Heritage Expert: Paul Dans <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJvcPPPCTjwDkFKJBFL0BhxYhU4FNkA8DtFm5eXoO79SyMGkV5SvFz2fpSkjxSzUI_kA=> and Spencer Chretien <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJhIH8F3o-Z8uEU4O2EWi_kEHmIGHoGIAx3RnKOStlGEoBZiIBU0n305TP4KfvK9jdaY=>
 
School administrators undermine excellence to promote ‘equity’ <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJlcrnAGfu7--qtmPI81Aq1Z0SdgBfKJIsOQ10yXTeHT-4bOib1hUyTwg-Ev-ZRVkF-8=> – The American education system is being rigged by hard-core, radical leftist administrators and teachers and their unions. But their efforts go beyond implementing racist policies, corrupting our children with anti-American, pro-Marxist propaganda, sowing gender confusion and canceling parental rights. They’re also diminishing and curtailing hard work and success. The latest example: 17 schools in Virginia did not notify students and their parents of National Merit awards those students had earned. That outrageous behavior was based on the bizarre claim that letting the students know about their commendations would not promote the school administrators’ stated objective of “equal outcomes for every student, without exceptions,” regardless of academic performance or lack of dedication to their studies. Heritage Expert: Hans von Spakovsky <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJikg-BAT2_E6KBLsIYmPTR40EA3BpnNJS7jmKqOfHIiEt8cM1ZHND9FWogrdRwqZRMo=>
Appeals Court Steals Show on ERA Amid Senate Panel’s Bid 
to Resurrect Dead Amendment <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJkqDGtSVnLFzOIyQXrFQGX0j1f6EI6UmFp5PPrbKG8Q2UvzhUl0V8dosfs3VkTc05yc=> - Advocates of the ERA want Congress to “recognize ratification” of the ERA that Congress proposed in 1972 even though the states refused to ratify it. The ERA died when its ratification deadline passed with fewer than the requisite three-fourths of the states ratifying it, as stipulated in the Constitution. Article V <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJSBCxHj0MAx2WN7SBw7CEhzZKTL4-LAm1RLvjYr4f9sejCCaY6fJquBoZZRYXfvxtbg=> of the Constitution spells out the amendment process. Votes of two-thirds of both houses of Congress may propose an amendment and specify whether states must ratify it through their legislatures or by state conventions. A proposed amendment becomes part of the Constitution when ratified by 38 states. Heritage Expert: Tom Jipping <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJmp_3_02Oxo02TPFu-rdMNjIg_ByEpsgEIE5DtDmwW49RBXeWW1ZqId62DCqYbswkd0=> 
Biden’s Misleading New Asylum Rule Is a Gimmick Atop a Shell Game <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJmW0gA7VRwSWwAgQECj1aJX2A1yeENwPoPLZGeH8RkRs7xQ8JAIh-lTF8FsHJbKzk6E=> - Now, in anticipation <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJlZ20c_Tgb571zGvj6KXIFdc1Sc7_023lBTwt3HXoaA2G0f9oFAQ7CYdZfy51eNgksY=> of even higher numbers of illegal alien encounters with the coming termination <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJuRS2copCpBd0d2WIVtOSRextUGlRiM-cNcRT7GhsGUm4J1SHTJf3f-bMTtj2aJHk_8=> of the Title 42 public health authority used to expel migrants during the COVID-19 pandemic, the departments of  Homeland Security and Justice have proposed a joint rule to avoid more bad optics. In it, the departments “encourage” illegal aliens to “avail themselves of [the] lawful, safe, and orderly pathways” the Biden administration created, or “seek asylum or other protection in countries through which they travel.” Heritage Expert: Lora Ries <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJjrvxcT0EsZ9OpLz1hDnnTOPR5pwcc_KaSDX3WnisqZiaoSLo0P1Yw7gv7m_VLriVbg=>
10 New Cases of Vote Fraud Again Demonstrate Imperative of Election Security - <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJhvdU67ksxX6vM0kuhziblSFkNynQ7xaofFDiRYK00rwqCCva1prWiVHNCi7ylsxz38=> While not an exhaustive or comprehensive list, the database presents a sampling of cases from across the country that demonstrate the reality that fraud <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJiwOYQ3WLNPC573_GE0LUbpU_E_etVjfwXvfPYwicRPaJsFC9lLkul8DOQ9N1shJWmU=> does occur and that lawmakers need to implement the types of safeguards outlined in Heritage’s Election Integrity Scorecard <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJt5Ph9r1BO-8RkLDa_08VS_qPC7oCrmWL4Hwdpcodmrez4PqF2-8ucLES9WBFkDhorg=> that can help secure both access to, and the integrity of, the election process <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJuMm-Dqvk-_I_LLCyJiD7B1NUKvv8QuEiVyKYxaxqrOZdoZmPuZGZeGzrC9p-4nHYO4=>. (The Daily Signal is the news outlet of The Heritage Foundation.) Here are the latest highlights, which occurred in several states ranging from New York and Michigan to Florida, Indiana, North Carolina, and Wisconsin, and which also demonstrate that election fraud <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJrJpRQU9TRlK_tqfxJUU_BjV5v27SdkK_BftiHxR4UYzhSsdV_HxipZE7b_76aLQ7kY=> is a bipartisan activity. Heritage Expert: Hans von Spakovsky <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJikg-BAT2_E6KBLsIYmPTR40EA3BpnNJS7jmKqOfHIiEt8cM1ZHND9FWogrdRwqZRMo=>
Unpacking the Oral Arguments Against 
Biden’s Student Loan Cancellation <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJu1R6uDZMYfBvm3DQR-20kbi8_Jr7kXpSu5KGqcUv8sRi8X6nATEo6FPrvXgx_j4Et4=> - The Supreme Court heard two cases Tuesday challenging the Biden administration’s claim that it could use a law meant to provide relief to first responders and military personnel after 9/11 to cancel $430 billion in student loan debt for over 40 
million borrowers. The administration has relied on an emergency-powers law called the HEROES Act <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJgL7rIH8VCJ49SfPDNWdqH0FrGNQTRJCIxWmmcFHe92Wm_L_YO1otHzpCVPk9l2ycQo=>, which was passed in response to the September 11, 2001, terrorist attacks. President Joe Biden claims that he can use that law to cancel student loan debt for more than 95% of all borrowers. At oral argument, the justices and lawyers debated a wide range of questions, but at the core of the sprawling dispute were two questions that arose again and again in different forms: First, does any challenger opposed to what the administration is doing have a right to sue; and, if so, is mass debt cancellation a question that only Congress can decide <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJkdeMfU0tekRi06wLYqwyx7rm0aqSHM-MmclG_xgU-asSGCA0oFynvJX3zHZE9AawGg=>? Heritage Experts: Jack Fitzhenry <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJmk6iepSAMdXp_NceUpi_KHDLdop6_lEGj-6WNoxERhQE6bNV5FF-copj9KjaH0eslQ=> and GianCarlo Canaparo <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKQTiBJhuCE7b5h30PU-drnf4hbp8fdTMEwjY6EpY4jXlx2g4dSQRyDQbLUmMysN_1hcr7Xg4=>

-

Subject: Now is the time
Body:
Dear Fellow Patriot,

“Freedom is never more than one generation away from extinction.”

This quote from America’s great conservative President, Ronald Reagan, almost seems prophetic. Recent studies all point to the fact that, right now, we are losing the battle for the heart and soul of the next generation to the siren song of socialism and big government programs.



Our Founders wisely built America on the core principles of limited government, free enterprise, and every person’s inalienable rights to life, liberty, and the pursuit of happiness.

Meanwhile, you only need look to the Soviet Union, Cuba, and Venezuela to see that socialism fosters nothing but social turmoil, limited individual freedom, and eventually total economic collapse!

I don’t want to see that happen here. Not in America.

That’s why I proudly serve The Heritage Foundation as its President. I’m determined to help The Heritage Foundation’s mission to cut through the great demographic divide in our country.

And while we’re making great strides in this area, we still have a long way to go.

Moving forward, we must tend to our core mission of developing and advancing conservative policy solutions in Washington while stemming the rising tide of socialism and demands for big government programs from the younger generation.

I’m so thankful that I can count you among those who are standing up for our founding principles. As long as America has patriots like you standing together and fighting on her behalf, we can continue to protect that freedom Reagan spoke about for many generations to come.

All the best,

Kevin D. Roberts, Ph.D.
President, The Heritage Foundation

-

Most Google News Results Skewed in 1 Direction Ahead of 2022 
Election, Stud <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX5ShD0gPwK14iNf4LWABpNhya18bUELBA0wfTFEzfUzsxTzrVcAXRvAZrWIKyLikVCc=>y Claims - Google News <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX2v6Hr8sTjuOSGw22ZQD-Z8HXTuAgn7OVd2XFPxiz7blGarD_zuEZeO9403AiabUXvA=> heavily skewed in favor of left-leaning media outlets—both in the news articles featured on its 
homepage and in the search results for specific topics—in five of the days leading up to the 2022 midterm elections, according to an AllSides study Google criticized as “deeply flawed” in comments to The Daily Signal. “Imbalanced or heavily biased news search results can have a negative impact on our democracy and elections,” Julie Mastrine, director of marketing and media bias ratings at AllSides, told The Daily Signal <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX2kdyGeNaQ6UQEAPk0zCYErwwRdoyRpxnUMHSpHAuBqt0Cpj6N8hqxqOhoIAME1stSM=> in a 
statement Tuesday. “When people cannot access the full range of views on political and societal issues, they are subject to partisan manipulation and cannot truly decide for themselves.” Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nXz4v8BHxgMM5vvrmCY_vXIsmQ5CgSS0W6FwIanv7-G8HEhdGzXTB_P_5IHaKFSIxykc=>

Why US Should Roll Out Red Carpet for South Korean 
President <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX0wj6edxWH_C4mwr8aJyOaAQiGb7hojD7R9OsjxxG1I88pgD39DBvLH31bbtKCb_lzk=> - South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol’s visit to Washington in late April will provide an opportunity for the U.S. to affirm and strengthen its bilateral relationship with an important ally <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX4OfNd3UT0bsXHx_ltHNstDZGFQXMiWDZR3yQmlVjEv7ivij7Mp6E55F42jvMfas2nk=>. The Biden administration should receive Yoon with all the trappings of a state visit, the highest-level visit by a head of state, and Congress should invite Yoon to address a joint session. The timing of the visit is particularly apropos, since 2023 marks the 70th anniversary of the creation of the U.S.-South Korean <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX3o5AlyF1PP1gZalG9RzUkWZThrnSmSjQGHDsQeD0xlUB6k5LgRA79XldSBBUGlJ9DU=> military alliance. Upon his inauguration last May, Yoon energized <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX_vl6_E8qJzFFbe0onn5WVzf0OerjsSizFJIS6mHjyyTcrMkgqb9WUpRurbQifMR0JI=> bilateral relations with Washington and brought 
South Korean foreign and security policies into close alignment with those of the United States. Heritage Expert: Bruce Klingner <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX9gmti4v4v-3NYRxct9Cr_uvNvJz2VZkLPawU-NMpIRM_cgmMosEaVCkV9Pu5N_50BQ=>
 
5 Takeaways From House GOP’s First Hearing on COVID-19 <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX2z2KAZb8yvd1fUx7uOhrE5KbJziAA96NrlFiQUxHtWk2Q5VgzpcvfcJb7WXnnbN-1s=> - Long-awaited congressional investigations into COVID-19 are underway, with results so far that are wide ranging and informative. Among those testifying during the initial inquiry under the House’s new Republican leadership were Dr. Lawrence Tabak, acting director of the National Institutes of Health; Dr. Rochelle Walensky, director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention; and Dr. Robert Califf, administrator of the U.S. Food and Drug Administration. Here are five particularly noteworthy revelations, based on the transcript of sworn testimony in the hearing held Feb. 8 by two House subcommittees. Heritage Expert: Bob Moffit <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nXzt9xpgTYDqWv3TiEMKXqGz60qgZkBzmzXBQfwE0gR7xPPYArpeT4xsTr4UNOcIn4_I=>
The scary Fed idea to turn your dollars into a digital power 
grab <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nXyZ_5-y8eROC96bxRqEWrg0noUG_pVDS2cHbKeT1D895cXe6Dgfgmr_sITFho0hdRB4=> - The digital dollar being advocated by members of the Treasury and Federal Reserve <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX-S0C2cj1srmPzK9H_l_UXJGQQbNmsQye_Li_006e6NGh05-7QEiv8BWVpAm7jZQaoY=> is an example of a central bank digital currency (CBDC). At first blush, our currency already appears to be digitized. Many people no longer carry physical cash and instead use digital payment methods like a chipped credit card or their smartphones. Likewise, direct deposit has become the standard method of payment for labor. Dollars are transferred in a stream of ones and zeros, not paper bills and metal coins. But those dollars are inherently fungible. It’s irrelevant if you accept or pay with any particular dollar, because each one functions exactly the same way as any other. CBDCs are different. They are programmable, traceable, trackable and taxable. Heritage Expert: EJ Antoni <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nXy-A6nwuHLih1XO4gCtSuM-OItQUHiJxA5c_kxxK-TOq4w1Ka7FFsQamDZ8kA0N8GFo=>
 
It’s past time to end COVID 
health insurance subsidies <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nX9rKEIycq2zO8TQM5WjPnUP6r1mh8OQo8iIK2utjzEOipVe9s9vR6k91G8dID6AFcbI=> - No, I don’t mean the cost to patients. I’m talking about the cost to taxpayers. And no, I’m not referring to government spending on COVID vaccines and treatments. Rather, I’m talking about the much larger cost of the “temporary” increases in federal health insurance subsidies. When COVID emerged in early 2020, the panicked response of most government officials, both at home and abroad, was to impose restrictions and lockdowns. Essentially, governments reacted to COVID by slamming the brakes on the economy — and then keeping them on long past the point of any possible public health benefit. Heritage Expert: Ed Haislmaier <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKRl6nXyYpz6oPFa6BiEMoAj2ff_N0QGb1noNgO4UUTOQOGJu7IhlcazDrvBY-cszlsxVWohs=>

-

Subject: Heritage Take: DC criminal code isn't reform; it's insanity
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

                                                   
DC criminal code isn't reform; it's insanity  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb0BMkxEZWKUh1ZwyKLXWajxvimB9_KMUBw-NBf-UQKuWjmRUdNgjn79r6BAWpO-x-AI=>–The DC Council’s latest move to withdraw their radical criminal code shortly before the Senate is expected to override it with bipartisan support shows the unseriousness with which they have approached the very serious task of protecting the District’s visitors and residents. Despite the Mayor, the Chief of Police, and the U.S. Attorney for the District all expressing grave concerns about the contents of this bill, D.C.’s local elected leaders pushed forward anyway, at a time when homicides, car thefts, carjackings, sexual assaults, and a host of other violent crimes are spiking within the District. Fortunately, the Framers of our Constitution gave Congress the responsibility of overseeing our nation’s capital precisely so that those visiting and working there on our nation’s business would not be held hostage by the whims of a few local radical legislators. Heritage Expert: Zach Smith <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb_uGyESB3QJ_YN5ytX6xMbquVrzcBSJfBvXYhhXZbxj0sOSYcsEMRUX_DYJobKnA_kk=> and Cully Stimson <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb_zHdet6mvUh1EMAdJJwUcJy4jbBqqozXwYbmid3bSJ_YraEjcyBITHopYKhSvMvbMI=>
 
Memo to President Biden: Lots of Dems Want to Sunset 
Medicare – No Joke! <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb4QJAsZScP7JV8ilYd9Xf2omeZy9ZMjudkTpw6XRM-JOYgQ2nq0qRcK-NnlJWsT2w-0=> - Last year, more than half of all House Democrats joined Rep. Pramila Jayapal (D-Wash.) in cosponsoring H.R. 1976 <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb9YajvLD3ZkcH9VrLB0IJXkrb-naXlWCdA7PRwaL6VcC5i4bBQiPVcYFwwrPDjLGJrA=> , the “Medicare for All Act,” which would have “sunset” Medicare. In the Senate, 14 Democrats cosponsored <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb8UJHHXyKyg0tHJxAClC_lkI36aySbqeLAdBb2B2Q_fVuTtNMBbZF4d2s00OsODzjU4=> companion legislation by Sen. Bernie Sanders (I-Vt).  Of course, these politicians do not advertise the fact that their legislation would abolish Medicare. Instead, they played word games by entitling it “Medicare for All.” That way, people would think the bills aimed expanding Medicare as we know it. Heritage Expert: Robert Moffit <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUbwF9BgWVechidBn_BlEqjc1TVbk7JWo4gIOfqXnIf9A-s9-driuYId_yfWTzZYWOZS0=>
 
North Carolina lawmakers must support this bill to empower 
families <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb3IZs02pTEYGj4gRjXPPLT-z5aWAXWqJstQIoc8mqNgwZaar650dXP__0EMJZ5MXDMI=> - No one can say “parents’ rights” aren’t popular in North Carolina, with state lawmakers introducing more than one proposal this year to advance them. But there are stark contrasts between the competing pitches to empower parents. Heritage Expert: Jonathan Butcher <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb4Agd9fc_kfibRNbg1LhgL4ltWwJK4J-q2Omm0Br6oXCRhqYuq6oBCpuzrMtD7wMGuY=>
 
The scary Fed idea to turn your dollars into a digital power grab <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb2QhaqvsqTnLt2wgN9LdUURAtxU-Hxp6xguGkiLctX68d3D5hOkGZpRFE-oCWJ-svCs=> - The digital dollar being advocated by members of the Treasury and Federal Reserve <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb0sMOVi91y6UBLowgPpB2FjtvKciX6QhWDXriRkcBez0yeRnLM8rhTI1qPJh4W0PWbk=> is 
an example of a central bank digital currency (CBDC). At first blush, our currency already appears to be digitized. Many people no longer carry physical cash and instead use digital payment methods like a chipped credit card or their smartphones. Likewise, direct deposit has become the standard method of payment for labor. Dollars are transferred in a stream of ones and zeros, not paper bills and metal coins. But those dollars are inherently fungible. It’s irrelevant if you accept or pay with any particular dollar, because each one functions exactly the same way as any other. CBDCs are different. They are programmable, traceable, trackable and taxable. Heritage Expert: EJ Antoni <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUbyoIpRB4dBWyNVbGUc97PoyTU4d5_dBVeTeJtQVxjzpP_tNhUpVHb243Kxh_osPJcMU=>
 
SPLC Lawyer Arrested in Atlanta Molotov Cocktail Riot, Faces Terrorism 
Charges <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb3nfTEGuQBTJZ4_MjdAiYrCdYhA1lE9KekzDFK8gOn6OSJ8W0esLr-GBpS9HsXZbhYk=> - A staff attorney at the Southern Poverty Law Center <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb1Cxm5GQOmp27ybdPV-JFmWNpQ1WXvdhA1_JRxBbXHyfdJRc3EFdCt2dMNvTgBswjiE=>, a left-leaning civil rights group notorious for branding 
mainstream conservative and Christians nonprofits “hate groups” and putting them on a map with Ku Klux Klan chapters, was arrested Sunday on terrorism charges for allegedly taking part in a violent riot where agitators threw rocks, Molotov cocktails, and fireworks at police. According to DeKalb County Jail records, the Georgia Bureau of Investigation arrested Thomas Webb Jurgens, a 6-foot male with brown hair and brown eyes, on Sunday, March 5. He faces one charge of “domestic terrorism.” Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb4pDTIW-k8bY5gG0DxOarp0y3uI25kDkL-kdGnw6X9UcFun3uMPSE4BXys05vfoBjd4=>
Thwarting the push to make inflation permanent <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb2DINNA_fPCNkrFYaP1PjwAAJ-Hv6yGmOpWLR4o7v3AvR3JWoBjQuyBXulg9yF_naQQ=> - Today, this fallacy is making a comeback among left-wing radicals who bill their permanent inflation “Modern Money Theory” (MMT). The idea in MMT is that the government can take as much as it wants by simply printing money, because government dollars will magically grow the economy and any resulting inflation can be magicked away by taxing the people into oblivion. This means the federal government can spend endless trillions on Green New Deals, mass welfare, crony capitalism or any new utopias that come bouncing down the pike. All those trillions would be on top of our current deficit running over $8.3 trillion over the past four years — levels not seen since the World Wars. Heritage Expert: Peter St. Onge <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKWvgUb19VyqFL00b6wPvI4Nv9U9GpDTlJaM72I0GQv9Y9TMQ80IXEQN4zbockSpZOKQIs2Ag=>

-

Subject: Heritage Take: DC Council chairman withdraws controversial crime bill, but Senate may still consider it
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.

DC Council chairman withdraws controversial crime bill, but Senate may still consider it <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5jawGlpo0blTOx-4eofC5F6vRwgBEVI-Z9vj3ypgZlYgkUa8NNRukNxJjVvvcFGqkUz74=> –The DC Council’s latest move to withdraw their radical criminal code shortly before the Senate is expected to override it with bipartisan support shows the unseriousness with which they have approached the very serious task of protecting the District’s visitors and residents. Despite the Mayor, the Chief of Police, and the U.S. Attorney for the District all expressing grave concerns about the contents of this bill, D.C.’s local elected leaders pushed forward anyway, at a time when homicides, car thefts, carjackings, sexual assaults, and a host of other violent crimes are spiking within the District. Fortunately, the Framers of our Constitution gave Congress the responsibility of overseeing our nation’s capital precisely so that those visiting and working there on our nation’s business would not be held hostage by the whims of a few local radical legislators. Heritage Expert: Zach Smith <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5jayVmWZsMcyb8ySjHc74Lkngf-lTIEvjSceXGfeVF-tGeyJulL1PnCEiJr95mIsXX7ZU=> and Cully Stimson <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja0y27jebMApxtDHADjQY8t6yLiKxRqQLvVYNu0wzUKx78shcmNWyR_4HHWNxJ5ReeWg=>
Promoting U.S. Security Cooperation from the Eastern Mediterranean to the Caucuses <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja2RwXlNneDpzcbVlUhYSSFmPzyexwUk33XyW9JbROqnNuWrX6p48djnB627zDbFpjIo=> - Congress has considered notable legislation to improve the U.S. contribution to Black Sea security and stability. This effort is laudable and should be supplemented with a broader array of security cooperation initiatives to ensure U.S. actions match the level of U.S. interests. Focusing diplomatic and security engagement activities to build maritime security capacities in the wider eastern Mediterranean region can best position the United States to navigate the myriad and often conflicting national interests of regional partners. In this strategic environment, a maritime approach can bring lightly aligned nations together for common cause. Heritage Expert: Brent Sadler <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja2xqFwov1qxWBylM92iEr8cVAjK-CM_JolApf-FCQi6upgE5jF83qNDCrGjmG_WmG6o=> 
Climate-Driven Technology Forces Out Europe’s Farmers <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5jaximrG8YfSj4RCMX7EGPdEuF1_Iw2K9kFhsZ3NqwHkJRUydedw66LemnR3iC10DtiC0=> - Thousands of Belgian and Dutch farmers are being sacrificed on the altar of climate change. They are losing their livelihoods as their governments crack down on emissions of nitrogen oxide (from manure) and the use of ammonia in fertilization. Heritage Foundation: Diana Furchtgott-Roth <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja5K7DWYL7oBNAwGj16rUot9AcJF7tVu_Jb_TJtIvm4pmNdr-ZLZ-LCgy2FfiUyffUj0=>
Southern Poverty Law Center Has Long History of Carrying Water for Antifa Extremists <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja9z91dNuQ0LLR5SPDDu3ga-lW5daHnc5JKV9iWBiT-DaBEg4v-9j-3Scbyy31K3MfqY=> - The Georgia 
Bureau of Investigation charged a staff attorney at the Southern Poverty Law Center with domestic terrorism for his involvement <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja7UaniTHzlR7lEWjeHqmfUAN18qdIoW5VXZHVgtlNcBQEfxgcTKdWuIXHo5Y0HK4HyA=> Sunday in a violent attack on police officers at 
the construction site for a police training facility near Atlanta. Although the SPLC claimed the attorney was a legal observer, the agitators were dressed in Antifa-style black bloc for the attack on the facility they call Cop City, and the SPLC has a long history of carrying water for Antifa rioters The SPLC claimed <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja6YuYz4VMVMRF4q7QJO8ceiIU2iu_zVCHx19rWo9g1mDrALjt1GWlmQ6HuMiC88uLb8=> that the lawyer’s arrest “is not evidence of any crime, but of heavy-handed law enforcement intervention against protesters.” Heritage Expert: Tyler O’Neil <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5jay_PhQSE1hX9M6J0z3pku45GIsLUUDTdEiZYIKW6V2HH7-cr-_aRWDXIn3KUgvAezN8=> 
                                        
Memo to President Biden: Lots of Dems Want to Sunset Medicare – No Joke! <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja3F3OBsk-Xwl1vyc0hHXaEVGUU1784CVD0j-6rk6lJyqy-O5vJPMUsxI5Ja7i2IA3xA=> - Last year, more than half of all House Democrats joined Rep. Pramila Jayapal (D-Wash.) in cosponsoring H.R. 1976 <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja50WsPIdD9q6kUEJ0n4y3cE80uwLwI44s65HDx7y3CmDiy9oiRNuOAkStYoLI5M-ldw=>, the “Medicare for All Act,” which would have “sunset” Medicare. In the Senate, 14 Democrats cosponsored <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja6gUTBcu9EvqHxgEVn3_A3xDTEhwT0wBg20KVUUiLqswFkZwOiqvp-b1wlZ8BpfvtGM=> companion legislation by Sen. Bernie Sanders (I-Vt).  Of course, these politicians do not advertise the fact that their legislation would abolish Medicare. Instead, they played word games by entitling it “Medicare for All.” That way, people would think the bills aimed expanding Medicare as we know it. Heritage Expert: Robert Moffit <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYB5ja5goiSQX30Rdb1-7ioFNg9aHJEGWZ7VVaORC6dfpkvAFmv4g6UTmjPqKgTrregQI7f4=>

Subject: The key to fighting socialism
Body:
Hi Fellow Conservative,

Every day, more and more of young Americans are heeding the siren song of socialism.

Because of the breakdown of education and the extraction of our founding principles from American classrooms, young people – tomorrow’s leaders – believe the bold lie that government is the solution to any economic problem.

If we want to preserve the America we know and love, we need to stop the lie—immediately. And the best way to counter this lie is to share the truth.

That’s why the team at The Heritage Foundation put together an exclusive e-booklet called The 9 Ways Socialism Will Morally Bankrupt America. It has all the arguments you’ll need to explain the dangers of socialism—and to expose the heartlessness and cruelty of a socialist regime.

Get your free copy today by clicking here. <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKYDBu3ynEj9aU0vBUKBKhwSC9twaciF0S4TuLFKqGDT2oSEMz3GhgPWp01Kl3GwMLn5Pfu0Y=>

Thank you for standing up for conservative values when they’re needed most.

Best,

Alexander HyattMembership Programs

Subject: Judge Forces USA Powerlifting to Let Biological Men Compete Against Women
Body:
* ARTICLES *


** Judge Forces USA Powerlifting to Let Biological Men Compete Against Women
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/07/judge-rules-usa-powerlifting-must-let-transgender-males-compete-in-womens-division/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=CapitolBell

A state court judge rules that USA Powerlifting discriminated against a biological male athlete who identifies as a woman when it banned him from competing in its women’s division.

=======================================


** Congressional Hearings About Team Biden Die in Liberal Media Darkness

Body:

“I think there is no doubt [National Institutes of Health] was funding gain-of-function research,” says Dr. Robert Redfield, who was CDC chief during the Trump administration.

=======================================


** The ‘Sainted Junior Senator From New York’ Turns 100
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/08/the-sainted-junior-senator-from-new-york-turns-100/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Jim Buckley took on campus radicals, anti-Vietnam War protesters, and what can only be described as the rank anti-Americanism of the New Left.

=======================================


** America Is Less Safe Under Biden Administration
https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/08/intelligence-community-testimony-shows-america-is-less-safe-under-biden/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=MorningBell

Subject: Heritage Take: Heritage Experts Laud Arkansas for Becoming Eleventh State with Education Savings Accounts
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.


Heritage Experts Laud Arkansas for Becoming Eleventh State with Education Savings Accounts <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wrnxsb41pxo87lEcq97zbiuT92h6pWVYamxPlqpA3_8HAu_9K_fksbkzCnqVUudmRHE=>- Arkansas Gov. Sarah Huckabee Sanders today is expected to sign into law the Arkansas LEARNS Act, which among other things would create education saving accounts for low-income families that would expand to all K-12 students in the next three years. Heritage Experts: Lindsey Burke <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wbNN6yzrdRmfHvz-WrVC80Y1-IeFLbL7JKBa4SdGH1zg6AGtmxWAnP-TIxaE7JxHfn8=> and Jason Bedrick <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wk0ws9Bx9iYHflyDAR2xVh5FHnTn4tXD-v3E9E-lxOiG3X77mccusq4mAmxock1TVUI=>
 
FDA Lacks Authority to Approve Abortion Pills, Claims First-of-Its-Kind Lawsuit. The Left Is Apoplectic. <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wiM_CL5qmt0HyevxRO4DNnnD6J9wp0DwuYQ2EFBu1aPyNNpOHKZPG_hMukFlNwx--Sg=> - The FDA’s stated mission <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wtGnD89IQINYukCWSfvEwTioUkuc6F6nqycCCPjB_bH12DsxMVp5MpH6EQDrLz8sILI=> is to protect the public health by ensuring the safety, efficacy, and security of drugs, biological products, and medical devices. But the plaintiffs in Alliance for Hippocratic Medicine v. U.S. Food and Drug Administration <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wi6zikKRVUZ95cx_IZAmvi0w2M0qfSpTx-JLqoFbAVhT99DxgSQWk2NSWuC23t3JY-w=> argue that the agency ignored that mission in pushing mifepristone through its accelerated approval process and ignoring the relevant law and science governing chemical abortions <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_woEDvbCkXSJX7d05P6tX_SWt-XagPlNCxw2LRS40PFmXpkk2hDMx6gUwMAj210lXHaU=>. Because FDA regulations <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wnNpXdIiD8QK5g-Q_KRpFo-rHRNJ7Hv3Ayg0Yzn9QuGwWoij88CuYBINIsnw7ah_U_c=> on accelerated approval of drugs require that “new drugs [be] studied for their safety and effectiveness in treating serious or life-threatening illness and … provide meaningful therapeutic benefit to patients over existing 
treatments,” the FDA would have had to classify pregnancy as an “illness.” And not just an “illness,” but a “serious or life-threatening” one at that. Heritage Expert: Sarah Parshall Perry <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wp49GtLZFayI8mQ38dBekV83-HMOIotkfyOjVq710cN8LjXGg7IdZ7_gCt7NFReC-1U=>
 
The Heritage Foundation's Budget Blueprint: Going on Offense on America’s Most Important Challenges <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wr3Iw9_6DjUCeFUA33gOba9VYJJYeUcmPBPcMThKTpnoFDhvIj-V0HfRvP6Fru3ggkE=> - The 
budget of the federal government is more than a list of line items and charts: It is a statement of the values of its drafters. The Heritage Foundation’s Budget Blueprint for Fiscal Year 2023 is a representation of Heritage’s proud commitment to those values and the fight to save America. Unfortunately, many who have wielded the power of the federal government have sought to reap the benefits of free enterprise while rejecting the principles that created it. They have bloated the government, consumed more and more of the resources and wealth generated by the American people, and sought to regulate and micromanage the American public. These leaders chose to take on a staggering amount of debt, squandering trillions of dollars on projects and programs designed to yield political benefits rather than benefitting the public within the core constitutional responsibilities of the federal government. The cost and regulatory burdens of the federal government harm our nation, injecting politics into the most important aspects 
of American civil life and eroding communities and liberty. Further, the unsustainable financing of major benefit programs and current debt level will, left unaltered, force a crippling tax burden that would rob the U.S. of cherished economic vitality. Heritage Experts: Richard Stern <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wtEQ0AylR1_kVVQr8qzFTNTKWRlYTqj9DKrlXJ_aWSDLDHKHm90b4J6yaxbczMo29jc=> and David Ditch <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wgcxgsNSQgg-xn8-Nw3w5BzxpoeRM9VOHbWLx4mEalk0lBf68QXYxxkw4KqfEOTSmas=> 
 
Promoting U.S. Security Cooperation from the Eastern Mediterranean to the Caucuses <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wp4CJrjinBSslYUiU21IFF1FWOsJxtcJ5ltFEVUGySzPNZ5CV2fn9Y-VBeEOHAEG2uo=> - Congress has considered notable legislation to improve the U.S. contribution to Black Sea security and stability. This effort is laudable and should be supplemented with a broader array of security cooperation initiatives to ensure U.S. actions match the level of U.S. interests. Focusing diplomatic and security engagement activities to build maritime security capacities in the wider eastern Mediterranean region can best position the United States to navigate the myriad and often conflicting national interests of regional partners. In this strategic environment, a maritime approach can bring lightly aligned nations together for common cause. Heritage Expert: Brent Sadler <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wq_oABOHGaHbbzVzSirm9yYJ9y9WTHQDaH-xHy8DrqP5u4LgSYLlDnMXxEmKtEZU6sY=>
 
When energy markets and geopolitics collide <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wiMVOeeI9syihe4rgegR-KdcgYiVHnUS5lcnmWQ34kkl9huF1AToCjcIESSHW6Zm75o=> - The usually discrete spheres of energy markets and geopolitics collided when Chevron Corporation announced it was 
buying Noble Energy for five billion dollars <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wuXsnN5Beu1z4Q333BF4i3Iqd894oV8dSqPQmGUnV3VgUGaw4B_ANdGPGJ1IN_SrKG8=>—a deal that meant every bit as much to establishing a sustainable peace in the Middle East as the Abraham Accords signed some six weeks later. Heritage Expert: Victoria Coates <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZUS_wnNvxaceKG9_t_Da35W2-W_OfFkJalJLOFhhMGshyp5h2-IOAHVizwg5VU3no874i6o=>

-

 Celebrate Women’s History Month and International Women’s Day with us! Join 
Reshma Saujani as she leads a conversation with Blessing Adesiyan, Sung Yeon 
Choimorrow, and Vivian Nava-Schellinger on what equity truly means for women — 
and particularly for women of color. Embracing Equity at Work and at Home will 
be a candid discussion about how equity has advanced (or not) for women, the 
residual impact of the pandemic on the struggle for equity, and the challenges 
and opportunities women face overall and within individual communities. Most 
importantly, we’ll discuss how we can learn from and support each other at 
work, at home and within our communities so women everywhere can rise.

Subject: Newly Released: The ‘Sainted Junior Senator From New York’ Turns 100
From: "The B. Kenneth Simon Center for American Studies" <richardreinsch@heritage.org>
Body:
Dear Friend,


We are currently engaged in a war: a war on memory. So many of our fellow citizens are unaware of our past or have heard a skewed version of our history. That’s why The Feulner Institute’s B. Kenneth Simon Center for American Studies decided to produce a series of videos on, " <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZreMggS_E10z7suAxIflMuH_Up9jeBB-0EpkC7Qu1BvbTA1RI3qvw1-mq3UzP3HGQ_CYdls=>America and the Struggle for Freedom" <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZreMggS_E10z7suAxIflMuH_Up9jeBB-0EpkC7Qu1BvbTA1RI3qvw1-mq3UzP3HGQ_CYdls=> to tell the true story of the great "experiment in self-government."      These short documentaries unpack the 
theme of freedom in Western civilization, culminating in the founding of America. We discuss how American democracy grew out of the classical-Christian tradition, how exceptional the American Revolution was in world history, and how the Founding Fathers produced what would become the most enduring and successful written Constitution in the world.       I invite you to view these videos <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKZreMggS_E10z7suAxIflMuH_Up9jeBB-0EpkC7Qu1BvbTA1RI3qvw1-mq3UzP3HGQ_CYdls=> on the Simon Center website.       Sincerely,   Joseph Loconte, Ph.D.   Director, B. Kenneth Simon Center for American Studies and AWC Family  Foundation Fellow   The Heritage 
 Foundation

-

Body:

“Many grassroots conservative activists around the country are very enthusiastic for Governor DeSantis to run for president in 2024,” Ken Cuccinelli says.

Despite Iran’s bad behavior at home and abroad (including its support for Russia’s war on Ukraine), the Biden administration seems blissfully unconcerned about it.

=======================================

Philanthropy Roundtable ranks all 50 states on the compliance costs charities face and found that more charity regulations may mean fewer charities in a state.

https://www.dailysignal.com/2023/03/08/6-takeaways-as-house-covid-19-panel-investigates-china-lab-leak/?utm_source=TDS_Email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=CapitolBell

Subject: Heritage Take: House Republicans push helpful earmark reforms
Body:
Here is the Heritage Take on the top issues today.Please reply to this email to arrange an interview.



House Republicans push helpful earmark reforms <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMcEJf4GfeJa1hxyqaGeb1n3X6a0qUB-d8QEa5IT0LlWQib2smx-Lq0iG61ROcJ7uMR0=> - House Republicans are taking a step toward restoring spending sanity. On Feb. 28, the House Appropriations Committee released rules and guidelines for so-called “earmark” items in upcoming spending bills. Heritage Expert: David Ditch <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMQ-jRFCO-RasF95oUWiLeVn9KkYRN8qQ-6GakusUJepUs0OoOe69YHSI3d9GnmQlXlc=>




Poll: Americans Believe Excessive 
Government Spending Weakens National Security Amid China Threat <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMZmXjrd8r6Cwg_IYfGjVMTy_QznRc4Ea3EUtEYaKRrpLK3xp5t9xXOeMOMtJ0Gi-owU=> - Simply raising the debt ceiling without addressing the reasons why the government keeps plunging deeper and deeper into red ink will only further 
endanger the nation’s long-term fiscal health. According to recent TIPP polling <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMSWCDjt7cskOXRr94JJkgwxTxj6Mm9pAUj_t6CfPPUWwoFWQuvXIxOW7J9wPVAzyGO8=>, Americans are tracking the spending debate closely—and not just due to economic concerns. Many also worry that reckless federal spending and the debt it creates up could threaten our national security. Heritage Expert: Victoria Coates <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMRLsW8FFNPE-bL8ikjNSGrcuOuqZjOgfY5QN-zaG2bk4kclBwSXfZ4dm7RaB8ysimec=>

 
Heritage Experts Laud Arkansas for Becoming Eleventh State with Education Savings Accounts <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMQPn_DA2zNKq3u0mbh2v1noQmNPQfi9FSdRStmX8vICYRqb3Pl6lqmLYkdhM8Ep2acQ=>- Arkansas Gov. Sarah Huckabee Sanders today is expected to sign into law the Arkansas LEARNS Act, which among other things would create education saving accounts for low-income families that would expand to all K-12 students in the next three years. Heritage Experts: Lindsey Burke <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMex-6BGnSa-pG6WzWvFlk6ULSxTc1dB72uSzpN67ZL7MgAqWiEruKpyCP1ACqtXG1eY=> and Jason Bedrick <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMcDFD4pyEmp9_SQxScicOcRt8qalsB2siyzsLCEOYRzDZAu_F4Q14FpW9ziwLWOZFMM=>

 
FDA Lacks Authority to Approve Abortion Pills, Claims First-of-Its-Kind Lawsuit. The Left Is Apoplectic. <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMcWICos6RGhP89V__sAAKUtq4O6l04CtsH-RuGcbR8OOlHXgGHynGRAd_ZtntvQiVx4=> - The FDA’s stated mission <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMTpl8Po4F3PuTrbajelLyIrGnbAh_IYHlh3q5AWMhU6TQhWDvt1cLN5MThwT6g_4Id4=> is to protect the public health by ensuring the safety, efficacy, and security of drugs, biological products, and medical devices. But the plaintiffs in Alliance for Hippocratic Medicine v. U.S. Food and Drug Administration <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMRGni3OleWgnNQP0Pd-bm6A1ue2QUvklRlI1P5cvHxWIXLa5w5F1gLZ1YpT7ERY2S7E=> argue that the agency ignored that mission in pushing mifepristone through its accelerated approval process and ignoring the relevant law and science governing chemical abortions <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMQXRtTrXId9p5c3s6ozMR-IZBI_4dxu2sTC6QahzXCHVMw6Grupsd0HJ68xBmBki0FQ=>. Because FDA regulations <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMdhO0GV3y5EBEAvx2s8gWIJRHmC_VDpTve_3SkBnVcyaBseqKglU6FR2gQUPFdbXUvc=> on accelerated approval of drugs require that “new drugs [be] studied for their safety and effectiveness in treating serious or life-threatening illness and … provide meaningful therapeutic benefit to patients over existing 
treatments,” the FDA would have had to classify pregnancy as an “illness.” And not just an “illness,” but a “serious or life-threatening” one at that. Heritage Expert: Sarah Parshall Perry <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMa3r2rWvcj8POohgiIfsMc2lWrA0jWo0VEVSCE2oi1-ijbvAUWdk6npAw-d_vh9Nn94=>

 
Fighting human trafficking and battling Biden’s open border <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMbBce-IXpl4SwyNvONI8Z3JpinOOPZW7i86WbXTKxo-MRNJ8wQiEAkZBYNs337KBaZ4=> – 
Human trafficking is a global business generating $150 billion in illegal profits. It encompasses forced labor, sex trafficking, organ trafficking and more. President Biden has professed a commitment to fight this multifaceted criminal enterprise, yet his immigration policies have only exacerbated the problem. Heritage Expert: Hannah Davis <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMScN9l7BwPVl23Un6P2taO1HiqAfFetudiMk0jqHv-cXTXUEpHjWhtFmQpujTtBTq6s=>

 
Forget Parents, Here’s What This ‘Whole Child’ Ideology Really Promotes <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMVEa2krmK_tjnfwY7aWv5MVlLIpbOqkL2eO1HqqNRZ7DK1aykA1m0ZS5EDXDHQVpi-E=> - In January, the American Academy of Pediatrics (AAP) released a new study on childhood obesity <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMezVNocqUOLCH8dr93_KjPfRp-IhFYl37geiiJiTGK8dwGdzbH8XWhr_zkxQTvKKxXM=>. Their recommendation sparked outrage: beginning at age 12, obese kids are eligible for weight loss drugs. By age 13 they qualify for weight loss surgery. Heritage Expert: Emma Waters <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKamtsMQpiLXMEwfP_vuEiS2dpgsk3XKJ8CAJwNquPlIow_2OA1T2JKRmzCG2YancIDahim7w=>

-

Subject: Heritage Events LIVE: Upcoming Events on Missile Defense, the Radical Rise in Crime, and More This Month
Body:
The 2023 Russell Kirk Lecture Featuring Bishop Robert Barron
March 14, 2023
6:00 p.m. – 7:00 p.m. ET
Heritage is honored to have the Most Reverend Bishop Robert Barron deliver the 2023 Russell Kirk Lecture. Bishop Barron is known for his highly influential Word on Fire ministerial organization and is one of the most followed Catholics on social media.
REGISTER NOW  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKa3gzQHAqbaS0VJUV9KTKfOBLDbOHBqIwTxAshBgIoHepTcK8BWA-zolMW9bh-sRZLF595Yw=>
Edwin Meese III Originalism Lecture
March 21, 2023
6:30 p.m. – 7:30 p.m. ET
This annual lecture seeks to honor former Attorney General Ed Meese’s legacy of advancing an understanding and jurisprudence of originalism. Professor Kurt Lash, the E. Claiborne Robins Distinguished Chair in Law at the University of Richmond School of Law, will deliver this year’s lecture on “Originalism and Fixing the Fourteenth Amendment.”
REGISTER NOW  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKa3gzQSREt079-hf0MRY9I4uKNxd4WBN3TFeZZojk0igPpowGPrGSuHByaAznGgYVDuIvkbE=>
Ronald Reagan's Strategic Defense Initiative

40 Years Later
March 23, 2023
10:00 a.m. – 11:00 a.m. ET
Forty years ago on March 23, President Ronald Reagan announced to the world his plans to develop a missile defense system that would make Soviet ballistic missiles “impotent and obsolete,” yet in the years since his Strategic Defense Initiative, plans for a comprehensive homeland missile defense system have deteriorated. Join us as we discuss options for the future of U.S. missile defense.
REGISTER NOW  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKa3gzQdm-kYBkgoHRHs49PVMG50Sr-zgw2czziF6jgQJivZFyonLKcHOxC7SjP_YfigC4B-0=>
The District of Disorder

Crime and the District of Columbia
March 23, 2023
1:00 p.m. – 2:30 p.m. ET
The crime problem in our nation’s capital seems to grow worse by the day. Senator Bill Hagerty, Congressman Andrew Clyde, and former U.S. Attorney for D.C. Jessie Liu discuss what can be done to stop the radical rise in crime in the District—and around the country.
REGISTER NOW  <http://click.heritage.org/ODI0LU1IVC0zMDQAAAGKa3gzQeyV6H1Lj9-2uAcXwmQ2Fg-f0u4OBD5w4s1p4TaKk5PWQmGYNNmZOycKGbiSbqxka0o=>
Restoring the Military’s Focus on Warfighting
March 30, 2023
3:00 p.m. – 4:00 p.m. ET
The National Independent Panel on Military Service and Readiness was formed in October 2022 and tasked with identifying policies or practices in the Defense Department that reduce military readiness and recommending remedies. Join us as the panel’s chairman, Congressman Mike Waltz, and panel members release their final report and recommendations.
